title: spiced franks
directions: Combine flour and water to make a thickening.
Add remaining ingredients in order given, mixing well before adding franks. Simmer 20 minutes.

title: sour cream lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and
cornstarch;
whisk in milk until smooth. Add yolks until blended; stir in lemon juice, peel and butter. Cook over medium heat
in
double
boiler, until thick. Do not beat! Cool to room
temperature.	Add
1	cup
sour cream and stir in well. Pour	into
baked pie shell. Refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.

title: foolproof meringue
directions: Blend cold water and cornstarch.
Add to boiling water and cook until clear and thick.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat until stiff, not dry. Add cornstarch mixture.
Beat at high speed until thick; spread on pie.
Bring meringue all the way to edges of crust.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: roasted pepper dip(almost fat free)
directions: In blender or food processor, blend red pepper, basil, garlic and seasoning.
Add cottage cheese and blend until smooth.
Chill 1 hour.
Garnish with fresh basil.
Serve with toasted pita chips.

title: pineapple supreme cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in long pan.
Punch holes in cake.
In a medium saucepan, bring pineapple and sugar to a boil.
Pour over cake.
Mix pudding as directed.
Spread over pineapple.
Mix cheese, Cool Whip and sugar.
Spread this on top of pudding. Sprinkle with coconut and top with pecans.
Chill before serving.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water; then add cold water.
Mix.
Add pineapple.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with marshmallows. Refrigerate until set.
Then slice bananas over set jello.
Mix pudding as directed on box and spread over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: p t a punch
directions: To prepare a punch bowl size amount of punch, mix juices with 1/2 of the bottle of Hawaiian Punch; stir and add water to finish filling punch bowl.

title: pennsylvania dutch shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix flour, 1 cup brown sugar and butter to make crumbs.
Mix molasses, hot water, soda and other cup of brown sugar.
Sprinkle a layer of crumbs in bottom of each tin, then pour in half of liquid. Add a few more crumbs, rest of liquid, then top with crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) until firm.

title: aggie's biscuits(never fail)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Measure oil and milk together and stir into dry ingredients until all is moist.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut out biscuits with a cutter or glass 2 inches in diameter.
Dip glass into flour to prevent it from sticking. Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: chocolate mashed potato cake
directions: In a small bowl, combine flour, cocoa powder, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and cloves.
Set aside.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter or margarine to soften.
Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beating well.
Add mashed potatoes and vanilla; alternately add flour mixture and buttermilk, beating after each addition until batter is smooth.

title: ice cream crunch
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add soft oleo and mix well.
Spread mixture into large baking pan.
Cook 30 minutes at 325°, stirring every 5 minutes.
Allow to cool.

title: orange slice candy cake
directions: Cream butter and add sugar. Add eggs and beat well. Mix flour, dates,

orange slices, coconut and nuts. Add half of flour and fruit mixture to the creamed mixture with buttermilk. Blend remaining half of flour mixture and fruit mixture. Bake in a well-greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: five flavored cake
directions: Mix milk, butter, Crisco and sugar together and then add 1 egg at a time and then add the flour and baking powder, alternating with milk until it is all used.
Then add flavoring.
Mix well; put into a tube pan.
Bake it at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let cake set in pan until cooled.

title: chex after school mix
directions: Place cereal in large bowl; set aside.
In small saucepan over low heat melt Nestle Toll House semi-sweet chocolate morsels, peanut butter and margarine until smooth, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal mixture and sugar in a large resealable plastic bag.
Shake until all pieces are well coated.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.
Store in resealable plastic bag or other airtight container.

title: shawn's favorite chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt pan or tube pan.
Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water and oil in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan 25 minutes. Invert onto serving plate. Cool completely.

title: hot jalapeno salsa
directions: Cook peppers in oil on medium heat until toasted (4 to 5 minutes). Put cut onions, jalapenos with oil and salt into blender and liquefy until completely mixed.
If you want this recipe very hot, keep all seeds in peppers.
If you want it milder, take out all seeds from peppers.

title: hot veggie stew
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add zucchini, mushrooms, kidney beans and green beans.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients and cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Beat shortening with hand mixer.
Add about 1 cup of flour, 1/2 of the buttermilk, sugar, cocoa, egg, baking soda, vanilla and salt.
Beat until thoroughly combined.
Beat in remaining cup of flour and remaining buttermilk.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoon 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10
minutes or until the edges are firm.
Do not overbake.
Cool on wire rack.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, bread crumbs, Worcestershire sauce, beaten egg, salt and pepper together.
Shape mixture into small balls.
Place grape jelly and chili sauce in saucepan.
Place meatballs into jelly and sauce mixture.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: potato for super bowl
directions: Apply cooking oil on potato skins.
Bake until done.
Melt butter and milk over low fire, and set aside.
Slice the potatoes lengthwise.
Scoop middle of potatoes without breaking the skin. Mash potatoes; add onions and hash browns.
Mix in diced celery, salt and soy sauce.
Add nutmeg and melted butter.
Fill potato skins with the mixture.
Cover the filled potato with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and form into balls the size of walnuts.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: coating for fish or chicken
directions: Dry fish or chicken before coating.

title: canadian brownies
directions: Mix 1/2 cup flour, confectioners sugar and butter well. Spread in greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 425° until brown.
Mix remaining 1/4 cup flour with remaining ingredients. Pour over hot crust and bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: macaroni baked with mushrooms, ham and cheese
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, melt 3 tablespoons of the butter.

When it foams, add the cremini and shiitake and season with 1 teaspoon of the salt and 1/4 teaspoon of the pepper; cover and cook, tossing and stirring, once or twice, until the mushrooms begin to render their juices, about 5 minutes.
Transfer the mushrooms to a strainer set over a bowl.

title: apple salad
directions: Take sugar, flour, butter, water, vinegar and egg; cook until thick.
Pour over apples, celery, nuts and cut up grapes.
Mix well; let cool, then add marshmallows.
Let cool in refrigerator for 4 hours and serve.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: In a small bowl, stir together yogurt, applesauce, powdered sugar, vanilla and cinnamon, nutmeg or ginger.
To serve, spear fruit with toothpicks, then dip into yogurt mixture.
Makes 6 (3 tablespoon) servings with 87 calories each.

title: baked hot chicken salad
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Place in greased baking dish. Top with cheese and potato chips.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Brown onion and garlic in oil.
Add beef broth, tomatoes, picante and basil.
Boil.
Stir in tortellini.
Simmer 15 minutes uncovered.
Stir in peppers.
Simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.

title: uncle wayne's hodge podge
directions: Brown ground beef & chopped onions together till onion is tender. Stir in 3 cans of Minestrone Soup, Pork & Beans, 3 cups water, celery,
worcester shire sauce, and oregano. Cover and simmer until celery is tender. I cook the celery with the ground beef and onion. It gets tender that way. Refrigerates well.

title: oriental chews
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place noodles and coconut on cookie sheet in single layer.
Bake 10 minutes or until crisp.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips in top of double boiler over hot, not boiling, water.
Remove from heat; stir in almonds, coconut and noodles.
Drop mixture by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Cool until set.
Makes about 5 dozen chews.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake as directed and add the coconut.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan until done.
Wait 5 minutes.
Punch holes in cake and pour 1 can of Coco Casa (cream of coconut) over cake.
Frost with whipped cream.
Sprinkle coconut over whipped cream.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook over low heat.

title: brownie baked alaska
directions: Spread brownie layer with ice cream to within 1/2-inch of edges.
Freeze.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar in mixer bowl until foamy.
Add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating well after each addition until stiff and glossy.
Spread over ice cream, sealing to edges.
Bake at 500° for 3 minutes or until browned.
Serve immediately.

title: brown-eyed susans
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Roll into balls and cover with white sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets for 10 to 12 minutes.
While hot, top with Hershey's Kisses.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar,
baking
powder, eggs, oil and orange juice until smooth.
Combine
sugar
and
cinnamon
in a small bowl. Pour 1/2 of the
batter into a greased tube pan.
Layer with 1/2 of the
apples.
Sprinkle
with
sugar
and
cinnamon mixture. Use remaining batter
and repeat as above.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, baking soda and spices (in food processor).
Cream butter, sugar, orange rind and egg.
Mix persimmon pulp in lightly.
Drop batter by tablespoon on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with anise seed and bake 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 3 dozen.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix water and soup mix, bring to a boil for 7 minutes.
Add rice and cook 7 minutes more.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
In skillet, brown sausage and drain.
Stir in onion, pepper and celery; cook until onions are tender.
Add meat mixture to rice mixture.
Stir in water chestnuts.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Spread pimento over top.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: stuffed peppers to can
directions: Shred cabbage and add salt.
Let stand until cabbage has wilted a bit.
Stuff cabbage into cored, whole peppers.
Put peppers as upright as possible into jars.
Mix remaining ingredients together and add to peppers.
Seal and cold pack for 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: 4 layer delight
directions: Mix flour and nuts together.
Melt oleo and pour into mixture. Blend well.
Press mixture out in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Remove and let cool completely.
Blend the cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1 of the
cartons of Cool Whip together.
Spread on top of crust.
Mix milk with both packages of pudding and spread over second layer.
Spread the last carton of Cool Whip over pudding and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: barbecue wieners
directions: Slice wieners.
Cook with barbecue sauce.
Place in microwave. Cook for 2 minutes on High.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: corn and bean soup
directions: Slice salt pork almost through in several places; place in large kettle.
Add 2 quarts boiling water, beans, tomatoes, onion, salt, pepper and sugar.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Add corn, cook for 3 minutes longer.
Yields 6 servings.

title: orance ice sorbet
directions: Using Cuisinart: Insert metal blade; add orange peel, 1 cup juice, sugar and Grand Marnier to work bowl.
Process until peel is finely chopped.
Add processed ingredients to remaining juice and mix well.
Pour into ice cube trays or similar sized metal pans.
Freeze until firm.

title: kahlua candied yams
directions: Boil yams until tender, but firm; peel and halve lengthwise. In heavy frying pan, melt butter and sugar.
Add Kahlua; stir and cook 1 minute.
Add yams; turn until brown on all sides.
Cover; reduce heat and cook 15 minutes.
Turn once before serving. Serves
4 to 6 people.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Put rhubarb in bottom of pan.
Pour cake mix over it.
Bring to boil water, sugar and food coloring.
Spoon in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Leave set for 5 or 10 minutes.
Turn upside-down on cookie sheet.

title: corn balls
directions: Saute onion and celery.
Add to stuffing mix.
Add corn, egg and water.
Make into balls.
Place in baking dish.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo and pour over.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine the yogurt, peanut butter and cinnamon.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Serve with apples and pretzels.
Yield: 1 cup.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
Slightly beat eggs.
Mix in margarine, onion and cottage cheese; blend well.
Stir in cornbread mix.
Pour mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan and bake 25 minutes at 400°.

title: cabbage burgers
directions: Mix package of hot roll mix according to package directions or frozen bread dough directions.

title: hot pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 5 tablespoons juice.
In a 2-quart baking dish, combine 5 tablespoons pineapple juice and flour.
Mix in sugar and cheese.
Add drained pineapple.
Mix well.

title: crumb cake
directions: In 9 x 12-inch dish, place apples in bottom of dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top of apples. Slice butter over top of dry mix. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: lemon zucchini muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

Mix flour, baking powder, sugar, salt, lemon peel and nutmeg in a large bowl. Stir in nuts and raisins. In small bowl, beat the eggs, then beat in the milk and oil. Add to the flour mixture, then sprinkle the zucchini on top. Stir until just blended.
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake for 15 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: puff cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with a fork.
Leave lumpy.
Preheat oven to 450° and melt 1/4 stick of butter in 8-inch cast-iron skillet. When melted, swirl around to coat bottom and sides of skillet. Pour batter in.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove carefully and serve Puff Cake with maple syrup.

title: no sugar apple pie
directions: Combine juice, cornstarch, cinnamon and salt.
Heat until thickened.
Add sliced apples and simmer until partially cooked. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cover with top shell and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tamale pie
directions: Lightly grease 2-quart casserole.
Tear tortillas and put 1/2 in bottom of dish for first layer.
Put a layer of meat, cheese, then onion on top of tortillas.
Repeat.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Combine jello and pineapple and its juice and heat until jello dissolves.
Cool. Add buttermilk and Cool Whip and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until congealed.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: chocolate turtles cheesecake(cardiologists special)
directions: Crust:
Melt butter over low heat; add wafers and mix until moistened with butter.
Press wafers into bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Spread pecans evenly on crust.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl and beat well.
Drop by small dips into hot fat at 350°.
Be sure they cook long enough that centers are done.
Serve with maple syrup.

title: french meat pie
directions: Roll pie crust out and put in refrigerator for 10 minutes to rest before filling.
The crust will not shrink.

title: new orleans chicken gumbo
directions: In dutch oven, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove with slotted spoon, drain on paper towels.
Brown chicken in drippings.
Add water, celery, carrot, onion, bay leaves, and salt.
Bring to a boil over high heat; reduce heat and simmer uncovered 35 minutes. Remove chicken from broth.
When cool, remove meat from bones and cut into cubes.
Strain broth and skim off fat.
Meanwhile, for roux, heat oil in saucepan over low heat.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Cook, stirring frequently, until medium brown, about 30 minutes.
Return chicken broth to dutch oven.
Stir in roux.
Add chicken, bacon, and remaining ingredients except shrimp and rice. Cover and simmer over low heat about 1-1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add shrimp; simmer about 10 minutes more.
Taste for seasoning.
Serve with steamed rice.
Makes 14 cups, about 190 calories per cup.

title: sausage souffle(do a day ahead)
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with butter.
Place bread cubes in dish and top with cheese.
Brown and drain sausage and place on top of cheese.
Beat eggs with 2 1/4 cups milk and mustard; pour over sausage.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine pineapple and jello in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Cool to lukewarm; add nuts, cheese and cream.
Chill.

title: heavenly congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; partly chill.
Mix in other ingredients; fold in whipped Dream Whip and chill until firm.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix vinegar, lemon juice, salt and Worcestershire sauce in small bowl.
Heat in top of double boiler.
Brown butter and fold into sauce just before serving.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs. Add milk, sugar and salt.
Combine corn with other ingredients.
Add to milk mixture.
Mix well and bake in casserole dish for 1 hour at 325°.

title: pecan raisin cookies(diabetic)
directions: Combine all ingredients. These can be dropped by tsp.
on cookie sheet, or spread on cookie sheet, or shaped any way you like. Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: tuna bake(microwave)
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart glass baking dish.
Arrange potatoes in bottom of dish.
Bake, covered, with a paper towel for about 10 minutes.
The potatoes should be almost done.
Combine soup and milk in 4-cup glass bowl, microwave 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Spread tuna and cheese over potatoes.
Pour heated soup mixture over tuna. Top with French-fried onions and microwave, uncovered, 5 to 7 minutes or until casserole is heated through and cheese is melted.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Mix the yolks with the pumpkin, then add milk. Mix dry ingredients together and add the pumpkin mixture.

title: three cheese chicken bake
directions: Cook lasagna noodles in boiling, salted water according to package directions.
Drain well.
Cook onion and green pepper in diet margarine until tender.
Stir in condensed soup, mushrooms, pimento, skim milk and chili powder.

title: scalloped corn supreme
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Melt butter and pour over 1/2 cup cracker crumbs. Sprinkle buttered crumbs over corn.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until testing straw comes out of center clean.

title: san diego salad
directions: Place greens on serving platter; top with all remaining ingredients except dressing.
Serve with dressing.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: In a medium bowl with a mixer at low speed or in food processor, beat or process beef soup, salsa, Cheddar cheese and hot pepper sauce until as smooth as possible.
Cover and chill overnight.
On waxed paper, place chopped walnuts.
Shape cheese mixture into a ball and roll in coating until well coated.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 1 ball, about 16 servings.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim fat from meat; cut meat into strips 2 x 1/4-inches.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Cook meat in oil.
Turn frequently until brown, about 5 minutes.
Stir in water, onion, garlic salt and ginger.
Heat to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover; simmer 12 to 15 minutes.
Add green pepper strips during last 5 minutes of simmering.
Blend sugar and soy sauce; stir into meat mixture. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and boils. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Cut each tomato into 1/4-inch wedges. Place on meat mixture.
Cover and cook over low heat until tomatoes are heated, about 3 minutes.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups brown sugar and the oil. Stir in egg, buttermilk and vanilla.
Sift together flour and soda.
Add to sugar mixture; blend well.
Stir in rhubarb. Divide batter between two glass loaf pans (medium size).

title: taco dip
directions: Spread bean dip on 9-inch plate.
Peel and mash avocado and mix with lemon juice and garlic powder, then spread over bean dip. Mix sour cream and mayonnaise with taco seasoning mix and spread over avocado.
Spread cheese next and put tomatoes on top.
Serve with Mexican style chips.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt candy bars with a small amount of milk.
After this is melted, add the Pet milk, whipping cream and sugar.
Stir well. Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate or grind potatoes and onions.
Drain in colander for a few minutes.
Meanwhile, separate eggs.
Beat whites until stiff. Mix together ground potatoes, onions, egg yolks, flour, salt and pepper.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Fry in hot fat over medium heat until golden on one side.
Turn over and fry second side. Drain on paper towels.
Keep checking temperature so pancakes don't fry too fast or too slow.
Wonderful with applesauce and/or sour cream.
Serves 6.

title: fiesta pie
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Stir in milk; add remaining ingredients, except salsa and sour cream.
Mix well.
Pour mix into 9-inch microwavable pie plate.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir edges of mixture, toward center and from center to outside.
Smooth, cover and cook 4 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes and serve with salsa and sour cream.
tags: Stove Top corn bread stuffing mix

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add crumbs and milk and beat until smooth.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Then fold in coconut, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into an oblong pan (one that has been coated with oil) and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: clam chowder
directions: Chop bacon and render. When bacon is crisp, remove from skillet and discard fat, except for 1 tablespoon. Cook onions in bacon fat until soft. Add potatoes, juice from clams and 1 cup of water. Boil until potatoes are soft. Add clams, clam chowder, half and half and bring to a boil. Taste for seasoning. Add 1/4 pound butter to melt and add the bacon. Set aside for a couple of hours to allow flavors to combine. If too thick, add a small bottle of clam juice. (I add just a little cayenne and Worcestershire sauce.) Reheat slowly.

title: apple rolls
directions: Boil water and 1 1/2 cups sugar slowly and pour in cake pan. Sift flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix in the shortening.
Then add enough milk to make a soft dough.
Roll out quite thin.
Cover with apple slices.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll up and cut 1 1/2-inch slices like cinnamon rolls. Place rolls in hot syrup and bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven. Serve hot with whipped cream.

title: edible play dough(serves 14 kids)
directions: Mix ingredients to get a good consistency for modeling.
Let kids create yummy sculptures, then gobble 'em up.

title: italian casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Add onion, bell pepper, Ro-Tel and seasonings. Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Unroll crescent rolls and press into a greased casserole dish.
Pour meat mixture over uncooked dough and top with cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese bubbles.

title: mixed fruit salad
directions: Combine bananas and lemon juice.
Add grapes, cherries, Mandarin oranges, pineapple, fruit cocktail, and peaches.
Combine reserved orange, pineapple, fruit cocktail and peach juices with pudding mix, blending well.
Pour pudding liquid over fruit.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into serving bowl.
Chill until ready to serve. (Serves 12-16.)

title: honey butter
directions: Mix
ingredients
until smooth and spreadable.	Keeps a long time in refrigerator.

title: mama carrol's chicken adobo(great with fried rice)
directions: Wash chicken and place in large pot.
Add all other ingredients.
Liquid should cover chicken, if it does not add equal parts of each ingredient until it does.
Boil until chicken is tender and falling from bone.
Remove from liquid to serve.

title: ginger-broiled fish
directions: Preheat broiler for 5 minutes.
Arrange fish in a single layer in a well oiled preheated pan.
Combine all ingredients except fish.
Pour sauce over fish and broil 10 to 12 minutes about 2 inches from the heat, turning once and basting several times. Fish is done when it flakes easily with a fork.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moist.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup nuts and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 well greased and floured 9 inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove and cool.
You can bake at 350° for one hour in a tube pan.
I
ice with cream cheese frosting.

title: easy casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with a salad.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot and simmer for 30 minutes.
Can be kept in a jar and refrigerated until all used. Good on chicken, lamb or pork.

title: carrot walnut bread
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Combine oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla in large bowl.
Sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt together.
Add to sugar mixture.
Stir in carrots and walnuts.
Mix just until blended.
Turn into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until center springs back when lightly pressed with fingertip.
Cool in pan 10 minutes. Turn out onto wire rack; cool completely.

title: taco pizza
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasoning mix; simmer 5 minutes.
Press dough onto bottom and sides of ungreased 12-inch pizza pan, pressing edges together to seal.
Bake dough at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Drain all fruit and put in casserole dish.
In double boiler melt butter, sugar, flour and sherry.
Stir until thick.
Pour over fruit.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake next day at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken with 1/2 cup celery, onion, salt and pepper until tender.
Debone chicken.
Add pickles, pecans, celery and pineapple.
Moisten with mayonnaise to suit taste.

title: saturday chicken
directions: Chicken:
Use salt and garlic salt lightly over chicken, add paprika thoroughly.
Chicken must be spread out in one layer in a shallow pan.
Dilute soup with cream; pour it over chicken and sprinkle chopped parsley on top.
Bake it uncovered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: anthony's biscuit donuts
directions: You can cut holes from center of biscuit or you can cut biscuit into quarters and deep fry until brown.
Roll in powdered sugar or granulated sugar.

title: pineapple baked salad
directions: Melt margarine, then add all the other ingredients.
Spray a casserole dish with Pam spray.
Pour in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until the top is lightly browned.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Use 3/4 of cheese in filling.
Heat tortillas.
Fill and fold. Place in greased dish.
Pour Old El Paso enchilada sauce (hot or mild) over top.
Put remaining cheese on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover with aluminum foil.

title: glazed orange-pecan bread
directions: Cream butter; gradually add 3/4 cup sugar, beating well.
Add the beaten eggs and grated orange rind; mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with 3/4 cup orange juice, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Mix well after each addition.
Stir in pecans.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour.
Beat eggs and mix with milk, sugar and meal.
Then stir all together.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour until firm and brown.

title: old fashioned ice cream
directions: Heat cream, half and half and sugar until sugar melts and mixture heats.
Beat egg yolks, pour some of the hot cream into beaten yolks, mix well.
Add yolks to hot cream mixture and cook, stirring constantly until thickens, about 8 minutes.
Do not boil. Pour into bowl and add vanilla.
Cover and chill.
Stir before pouring into ice cream freezer and process by manufacturers directions.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Combine eggs, flour, sugars and oleo in a large bowl.
Mix. Add chips and nuts and mix by hand.
Put mix into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.
Can use milk chocolate chips, mint chips or peanut butter chips.

title: meltaway yummies
directions: Cream the butter, salt and extracts.
Add confectioners sugar gradually.
Mix well. Blend in flour.
Chill. Shape into rolls 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 3/4-inch lengths.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with bottom of glass that has been covered with a damp cloth.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: the world's richest pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together in a large bowl.
Sift the flour, baking powder and salt into the bowl.
Gradually add the milk, stirring it in completely.
Add the eggs one at a time, stirring each one in completely.
With the final egg, add the vanilla.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a loaf pan that you have previously buttered and lightly floured.

title: great baked fish
directions: Arrange fish in 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish; turn under thin edges.
Salt and pepper as desired.
Slice thin the lemon or lime and onion.
Place citrus slices over fish.
Separate onion into rings and place over fish-citrus.

title: put-in-pan crust
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl until crumbly.
Press in bottom of ungreased pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch. Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, buttermilk and oil.
Add creamed corn, soda, salt and eggs.
Pour half of cornbread in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Put chopped green chilies and 1/2 cheese over cornbread.
Top with remaining cornmeal mixture.
Add remaining cheese to second cornmeal layer.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: tequilaberry salad
directions: Chop up ingredients and mix together.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Beat eggs, then beat in sugar; mix well.
Add other ingredients, beating well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Mix together sugar, eggs, milk, and margarine. If batter is to thick add a little more milk. Stir in flour and baking powder. Pour cherries into two greased 9 x 17 inch pan. Bake at 350 degrees for about 30 to 45 minutes. Serving about 120.

title: sausage cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Mix well; knead lightly.
Pinch off dough and form into balls to make a biscuit about 1 3/4-inch in width. Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° about 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: holiday punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Bring just to a boil. Serve warm.
Red wine may be added if desired.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add beaten eggs and mashed bananas.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour milk and beat until smooth.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.
Cool well before slicing.

title: nail soup(spikersuppe)
directions: Clean and slice potatoes and boil to a soft mash.
Clean leeks; cut into long strips and boil with the soup for 15 minutes.
Add seasonings and butter.
An inexpensive everyday soup.
Serves 4.

title: cordon-rose banana cake
directions: For extra moistness, you can use up to 1/2 cup sour cream.

title: toffee squares
directions: Cream butter; add brown sugar and work until light and fluffy. Add beaten egg yolk and sifted flour. Spread thinly on a greased cookie sheet and bake on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes. Melt chocolate and spread on cookie surface while warm. Sprinkle with chopped nuts and cut into squares while warm.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Shape into ball and chill 1 hour.
Roll in pecans.

title: red velvet cake and icing
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix food coloring, vanilla and cocoa.
Blend into cream mixture.
Add flour alternately with the buttermilk to the creamed mixture.
Mix soda, salt and vinegar; add to the mixture.
Mix very well.
Pour into 3 cake pans.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool on racks.

title: pineapple nut cheesecake
directions: Drain pineapple, measuring 1/4 cup juice.
Set pineapple and juice aside.

title: cheese tarts
directions: Mix cream
cheese,
eggs,
sugar
and vanilla together. Use cupcake pan.
Put
liners in pan.
Place one vanilla wafer in the bottom of
each liner.
Put tablespoon of mix on top of each cookie; then put
a
teaspoon
of cherries on top of each one. Bake at
for	15
minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.
(Note: Keep in refrigerator.)

title: artichoke crab spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a shallow pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spanish hominy
directions: Cook onions in melted oleo, stirring constantly, until tender - do not brown.
Add flour, mix well.
Add hominy.
Mix green peppers, cheese and milk; stir over low heat until thick and cheese is melted.
Mix together.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake 25 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup, milk and dash of pepper.
In a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish, alternate layers of potatoes, onion, soup mixture and cheese.
Dot top with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover.
Bake 15 minutes more or until done.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Prepare pudding with 3 c. milk until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13 dish with graham crackers.
Pour 1/2 of pudding mixture over crackers.
Place another layer of crackers over pudding.
Pour remaining pudding over crackers.
Place final layer of crackers over pudding.
Soften icing in microwave and spread
over crackers.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease pie pan, rectangular pan or Corning Ware.
Bake about 45 minutes.
The top will be golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Mix as you would a pie and bake on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° or 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Blend in flour, soda and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into round balls.
Roll in sugar.

title: baked apples
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Core apples and peel 1/3 of the way down.
Arrange in baking dish.
Fill cavities with cinnamon candies and top with generous sprinkling of brown sugar.
Pour the ginger ale into the dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes, basting apples with liquid from time to time.

title: dreamy tuna sandwich
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Spread on lightly buttered toast points.

title: danish apple dessert
directions: Make dough by combining flour, shortening, salt and egg-milk mixture.
Use 1/2 dough and roll out to fill 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Roll other half and cut vents.
Crush corn flakes and sprinkle on bottom crust.
Peel and slice apples on top of crumbs. Put sugar, mixed with cinnamon and nutmeg, on top of apples.

title: hot tamales
directions: Mix meal, salt, warm shortening and water to a thick dough. Mix sausage and ground beef together.
Cut square cloths about 5-inch square; wet and spread on table.
Pat a layer of dough real thin; flatten a ball of meat to cover dough.
Sprinkle chili over meat; sprinkle garlic powder over chili.
Roll up and tie each end and in the middle.
Put into boiling water and boil for 1 hour.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; continue beating until creamy.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add to the sugar mixture.
Mix in cereals and coconut.
Bake at 400° on a greased cookie sheet until lightly browned.

title: chicken curry with mushrooms
directions: Skin and wash chicken pieces.
Put them in a covered baking pan.

title: chicken with tomatoes, olives & cheese
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry.
Dredge chicken in flour; shake off excess.
Heat butter and oil together in deep skillet or Dutch oven. Brown chicken well on all sides.
Remove chicken from pan. Lightly brown garlic, onion, carrots, and celery in pan drippings. Add tomatoes and wine to vegetables in pan or skillet.
Add seasonings; stir well.
Place chicken in sauce. Simmer over low heat 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Add olives; heat through.
Sprinkle cheese on top and let melt.

title: pasta a la chef andre(low-fat)
directions: In 1 tablespoon olive oil, saute onions, garlic and mushrooms, then add turkey sausage, basil and oregano.
Cook until lightly browned.
Add peeled shrimp and cook 3 to 5 minutes longer until shrimp are pink.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Drain crabmeat.
Combine with other ingredients.
Serve on buttered party rye.

title: texas cow patties
directions: Mix together first 9 ingredients.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet with an ice cream scoop.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
These are oversize cookies. Allow only 6 to a sheet.
Yields 4 1/2 to 5 dozen.

title: very blueberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, water and salt to a smooth paste.
Bring 1 cup blueberries, sugar and water to a boil.
Add to paste mixture. Stir until thickened.
Let cool.
Add remaining blueberries to berry mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate.
When cool, garnish with whipped cream or whipped topping.

title: egg and sausage souffle
directions: Grease 2-quart casserole.
Mix all ingredients; pour into casserole.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: pimiento cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Spread on rolls or crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: southern pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Blend in one egg at a time, then beat well.
Sift salt, flour and baking powder together.
Add to batter alternating dry mix and milk.
Grease and flour tube pan well.
Place in cold oven and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Do not open door until cake is done.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground meat and onions; drain grease. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until bubbly.

title: caramel cake icing
directions: Melt butter and sugar and stir in cream.
Cook to a soft ball. Take off stove and let stand 5 minutes.
Beat and add 1/2 teaspoon soda; spread on cake.

title: orange blossoms
directions: Beat eggs lightly; add sugar and beat.
Add flour, salt, baking powder, vanilla (little lemon extract added is good) and 1/2 cup water.
Grease and flour small muffin tins; 1 teaspoon batter in each tin.
While hot, dip in 1 pound powdered sugar, juice of 2 oranges and 1 lemon with rinds (or small can of frozen orange juice and 1 can of water; use about 1/2 cup of juice).
Add dash of salt. Place on wax paper to set.

title: coconut dream pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping mix with 1 cup of milk and vanilla as directed on package, using large mixing bowl.
Add remaining 1 1/2 cups of milk into the pudding mix.
Blend, then beat at high speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in coconut. Spoon into pie shell.
Chill 4 hours.

title: beautiful cake!
directions: Bake cake as directions state.
When cool, split layers in half so that you have 4 layers.
Mix other ingredients and spread between layers, on sides and top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: wedding mints
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and peppermint oil.
(Color mints with food coloring.)
Work powdered sugar in gradually until stiff (not too stiff).
If dough is too stiff, add a few drops of water until it's the right consistency.
Put granulated sugar in mold each time to prevent sticking.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill 1 hour.
Place on cookie sheet. Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: turkey pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine turkey, dressing and vegetables. Toss gently to coat.
Cover.
Refrigerate until serving time. Before serving, gently toss turkey mixture to coat.
Spoon over cooked spaghetti.
Makes 7 cups of 5 servings.

title: persimmon pudding(heirloom)
directions: Stir soda into buttermilk before adding to pudding mix.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cucumber spread
directions: Chop cucumbers into fine pieces (do not put into blender).
Add cream cheese, Tabasco, salt, and garlic.
Yields 1 1/2 cups dip.

title: beef pot pie
directions: Stove Top:
Place chuck roast in large pot and cover with water.
Season.
Bring to full boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and cook for 2 hours.
Watch and add water as needed.
Mix flour, egg, oil, salt and pepper and milk as needed.
Mix until stiff (like pie crust).
Roll out thin and cut into squares.
Drop into boiling broth and cook approximately 20 minutes.
Remove roast.
Cut up and remove fat.
Add back to boiling mixture.
May add more water, if needed.
Can also use chicken in place of beef, if desired.

title: paprika chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Add a piece or 2 of chicken at a time and shake to coat.
Then brown in skillet in hot Crisco.
Add onion, water and paprika.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Remove chicken and keep warm.
Make sour cream gravy.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Heat all the ingredients, then cool.
Pour over sliced or chunk pickles.
Add water to finish to the top of jug.
Stir each day for one week.
Can also add onions, bell peppers, carrots, cauliflower, celery and cabbage.

title: kansas corn scallop
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Drain liquid from whole kernel corn into a cup.

Beat eggs slightly in a large bowl; stir in corn, 1/4 cup of the liquid, cream-style corn, evaporated milk, melted butter, onion, salt and pepper; fold in saltines and diced cheese. Spoon into a greased 8-cup baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour or until set.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract.
Stir in almonds.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Garnish with candied cherry halves.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Remove from baking sheets immediately. Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Season well with salt, black and red pepper.
Coat with flour.
Melt fat in an iron skillet or heavy aluminum pot.
Fry chicken until brown, then remove from skillet.
To the fat, add onions, celery, garlic and bell peppers; cook until wilted.
Put the chicken back in the skillet and cover. Cook slowly until chicken is tender (about 30 minutes).
Add rice to chicken; stir thoroughly for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add salt and cook slowly for 30 minutes, until rice is cooked.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown bacon, onion and green pepper; cook until done.
Add beans,
tomato sauce and sugar; simmer for 2 hours.

title: orange-glazed back ribs
directions: Combine barbecue sauce, orange juice, lemon juice, brown sugar, soy sauce, instant minced onion and salt.
Bring to boil, lower heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally until sauce thickens.
Stir in orange peel.
Place ribs on grill over low to moderate heat and broil 1 hour, turning to brown evenly.
Brush ribs with sauce and continue broiling 20 to 30 minutes or until done, turning and brushing with sauce occasionally.
Yields 6 servings.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cover eggs with water an inch above.
Add salt and eggs. Cover.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Let stand, covered, for 15 minutes in hot water.
Remove from hot water.
Rinse with cold water.
Peel and cut lengthwise.
Remove yolks with fork and blend in other ingredients.
Re-fill whites using about 1 tablespoon yolk mixture for each egg half.

title: creamy cucumber and onion salad
directions: Combine vinegar, water, sugar and pepper to make marinade. Peel cucumber and cut into 1/8-inch slices.
Cut onion very thin. Add to marinade, cover and let marinate 2 hours.
Mix yogurt and dill in large bowl.
Drain cucumbers and onion slices, discard marinade, then add to the yogurt dressing and mix well.
Makes 4 (3/4 cup) servings.
Contains 29 calories each serving.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Pour in drained green beans and tomato soup; stir.
Place in greased 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 Corning Ware dish.
Cook potatoes and mash; add egg and milk.
Spread potatoes over hamburger mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° uncovered.

title: homemade waffles or pancakes
directions: Mix flour, milk, water, eggs and oil with wire whisk or electric beater until well mixed.

title: cool rise dinner rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, thoroughly mix 1 cup flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Combine milk, water and margarine in small saucepan.
Heat over medium heat until bubbles appear around the edge of the liquid (do not boil).
Gradually add hot liquid to dry ingredients and beat for 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally with rubber scraper.
Add egg and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat on high speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
By hand, using wooden spoon, stir in enough additional flour to make a stiff dough. Turn out onto a lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Cover with plastic wrap, then a towel.
Let rest 20 minutes.
Punch dough down. Shape as directed.

title: icebox muffins
directions: Pour water over All-Bran and raisins; let stand.
Mix oil, sugar and eggs; blend in buttermilk with dry ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or can be stored, covered, in refrigerator 3 to 4 weeks.
Bake as needed or bake all and freeze.
Freezes well.

title: shrimp appetizer
directions: Mix all but the cheese together.
Put in a small casserole. Lay cheese slices on top.
Put in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Crab or lobster may be used also.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk; let come to a boil on medium heat, stirring constantly 5 minutes.
Take off heat.
Add peanut butter morsels and stir until smooth, then all marshmallow cream, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well; pour into 13 x 9-inch foil lined pan and chill before serving.

title: chocolate swirl cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Over hot (not boiling) water, combine chocolate chips and 1/2 cup sugar; heat until chips melt and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat; set aside.
In a small bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and the butter; mix well. Pat firmly into a 9-inch spring-form pan, covering bottom and 1-inch up sides; set aside.
In a large bowl beat cream cheese until light and creamy.
Gradually beat in 3/4 cup sugar.
Mix in sour cream and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Divide batter in half.
Pour into crumb-lined pan; cover with plain batter.
With a knife, swirl chocolate batter through plain batter to marbelize. Bake 50 minutes, or until only a 2 to 3-inch circle in center will shake. Cool at room temperature.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Boil potatoes; peel and mash.
Mix well with margarine, sugar and nuts.
Form a ball around one large marshmallow, then roll in crushed corn flakes.
Just before serving, warm balls in a 350° oven for about 15 minutes or until marshmallow has softened or melted.
(May be made ahead of time and refrigerated or frozen for later use.)
Makes 12 balls.

title: orange smoothie
directions: Place in blender and process on high until well mixed and frothy.
Serve at once.
This may be placed in quart jar with a tight lid and shake until well mixed and frothy.
It makes 6 (3/4 cup) servings.

title: rice krispies marshmallow treats
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows. Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies. Stir until well coated. Press mixture into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cool completely.

title: canadian bacon
directions: Bring water to boiling point; add honey.
Stir until well mixed, then add raisins and simmer for 10 minutes.
When bacon has been in oven for 30 minutes, place pineapple slice over each piece, then pour syrup with raisins over bacon.
Return to oven for another 15 minutes.

title: marinated beets
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill at least 1 hour or overnight is better.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: banana bread
directions: Use 3 mixing bowls.
In the first bowl, combine the flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In the second bowl, blend with mixer the bananas, shortening and milk.
In the third bowl, beat eggs.
Add the second bowl to the first bowl.
Mix until blended.
Beat on high for 2 minutes.
Add beaten eggs and remaining 3/4 cup flour.
Beat until blended.
Bake in greased and floured bread pan at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and sour cream together. Fold in marbled cheese. Gently fold in grapes. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sawdust pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and stir by hand. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in preheated 325° oven until glossy and set (about 25 to 30 minutes). Do not overbake! Center should be gooey. Serve warm with sliced bananas and Cool Whip.

title: hot dog, potato and corn casserole
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in the oil in frying pan until tender. Add hot dogs and corn and cook 5 more minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste and sprinkle top with chili powder.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: corn soup in bread bowls
directions: Cut top off loaves, using serrated knife.
Hollow out bread, leaving 3/4-inch border.
Set aside.

title: harleysville chocolate cake
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Make a well and add oil, water and vinegar.
Beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pina colada bread pudding
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine eggs, cream cheese and brown sugar.
Stir in bread cubes, undrained pineapple, coconut and milk.
Place in a greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch dish.
Bake in a 325° oven about 30 minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Remove to wire rack; cool slightly.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut, reserving liquid.
Rinse sauerkraut under cold water.
Drain well.
Combine sauerkraut, celery, carrot and onion.
In saucepan, combine reserved liquid, sugar and vinegar; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; pour over vegetable mixture.
Chill overnight.

title: ann landers' angel biscuits
directions: Night before serving, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons of warm water.
Add to dry ingredients along with buttermilk.
Stir into ball and knead until nearly smooth.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in large bowl.
Add all other ingredients and stir by hand until mixed.
(Do not beat.)
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: s'mores
directions: Break graham crackers in half.
Place one half on paper plate. Top with marshmallows and chocolate morsels.
Top with remaining half of graham cracker.
Place in microwave on High for about 30 seconds until marshmallows and chocolate are melted.
Yum!

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add juices from peach can. Pour this mix into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drop sliced peaches into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour which has been sifted with soda, salt and spices.
Mix in mashed bananas, raisins and nuts.
Bake in muffin cups at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake!
Makes 2 dozen.

title: hot taco rice
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Add tomato sauce and bouillon cube.
Bring to full boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Prepare rice as package directs.
Serve meat mixture over rice.
Garnish with chopped tomatoes, sour cream, shredded Cheddar, tortilla chips and sliced ripe olives.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients well and form into 1-inch balls.
Fry in skillet.
Pour off fat.
Remove from skillet.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Cut onion in slices and place in bottom of baking dish.
Pour 1 cup of water over onion.
Put meatballs on top of onion (fry meatballs first, just enough to get the grease out).

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add the strawberries and stir until berries are thawed.
Add sliced bananas and pecans. Pour half of the mixture in an 8 x 8 x 2 pan and hold in refrigerator until firm.
Jell the remaining half to a thick pouring consistency.
Spread the sour cream over the set jello and carefully spoon the remaining mixture on top of this.
Place the entire mixture in refrigerator until it is well set.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown stew meat in electric skillet or in deep pan. After meat is brown on all sides, add the beef stew mix. Stir this in meat until it starts to thicken, about 30 seconds.
Now add the water, enough to cover the meat real good.

Add the peeled potatoes (cut into small cubes) and sliced carrots. Canned carrots may be used. Now make sure you have enough water for the size pot you are using. Bring to a boil and then turn down to simmer.
Let simmer for several hours or until beef is very tender.

title: nancy's italian stew
directions: In large saucepan combine all liquid ingredients except water. Thin sauce with water to your liking.
Add garlic cloves and powder and pepper; cook on low heat 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and let stew for about 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: crustless microwave hot fudge pie
directions: In a microwave-safe dish, melt cocoa and butter until butter is melted.
Mix well.
Combine eggs, sugar, flour, vanilla and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Add chocolate mixture to egg mixture. Stir well.
Pour into buttered 8-inch pie plate.
Microwave approximately 8 minutes on High power.
Serve hot with ice cream. Delicious!

title: red velvet topping
directions: Cook together flour and milk.
It will be like pudding.
Cover with wax paper and let cool completely.
In mixing bowl mix Crisco and butter.
Cream this together.
Add sugar and vanilla and the pudding mixture.
Beat until creamy, so that you can't feel the sugar granules.
Ice the cake and if desired, sprinkle with flaked coconut.

title: meat loaf (low-fat but tasty)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and put in a 7 or 8-inch loaf pan.
Bake 40 minutes until firm and brown on top.

title: potatoes murphy
directions: Boil or steam potatoes.
Cook until tender.
Let cool. Leaving skins on, cut potatoes in quarters or small size pieces. Using a 3-quart casserole dish, put a layer of potatoes in bottom of dish.
Dot with slices of margarine.
Sprinkle on part of cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Repeat process.
Bake in covered dish for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable combo
directions: *Additional vegetables to consider: Fresh string beans, mushrooms and zucchini.

title: beef macaroni casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion, salt, pepper and oregano together.
Add tomatoes and catsup.
Mix well and simmer 15 minutes.
In casserole dish, layer macaroni, cheese and tomato, ground beef mixture, ending up with cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until bubbling.

title: quick salmon mousse
directions: Mix all ingredients, except salmon, in a saucepan.
Cook mixture over low heat until heavy cream consistency.
Fold in the salmon.
Chill well overnight.

title: beverage fruit punch *
directions: Combine juices and sugar; mix well.
Refrigerate at least one hour or until serving.
To serve, add chilled ginger ale.
Mix well.
Makes 12 (4 ounce) servings.

title: ground beef dinner
directions: In large pot, brown ground beef and chopped onion.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes or until liquid is reduced.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: zesty carrots
directions: Cook carrots until just crisp-tender (about 10 minutes). Drain, rinse in cold water and drain.
In serving bowl, layer carrots, onions and pepper.
In small bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over carrot mixture.
Cover and refrigerate for 4 hours or until next day.
Stir several times.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Use a 3-quart saucepan to brown.
Drain fat and let simmer for 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients, except noodles. Pour 1 cup sauce in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Layer lasagne noodles over sauce.
Cover with 1 1/2 cups of sauce. Spread 1/2 of cheese filling over sauce.
Repeat lasagne, 1 1/2 cups sauce, rest of cheese filling, lasagne and rest of sauce.

title: corn and green bean casserole
directions: Put green beans in the bottom of baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients together, except margarine, and spread on top of beans.
Top with enough crushed Ritz crackers to cover the top. Melt margarine and pour over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is brown.

title: cheese broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli,
onions,
butter and 1/4 cup water. Add rice, soup,
1/2	stick
butter,	milk and 1/2 of cheese. Cook over medium
heat
until cheese melts.
Pour into baking dish. Top with remaining cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 425°.

title: champagne punch
directions: Pour ginger ale in a plastic container.
Freeze until slushy (optional).
Mix with champagne and ginger ale.
Serve.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions, making 2 (8-inch) layers. Cook and let cool. Split horizontally. Blend together sugar, sour cream and coconut. Spread all except for 1 cup of this mixture between the layers. Blend the remaining cup of mixture with the Cool Whip and spread on top and sides of cake. Seal in airtight container and refrigerate for 3 days before serving.

title: nuggets
directions: Cut chicken into 1 x 1 1/2-inch pieces; set aside.
Combine flour, water, egg, sesame seed and salt; mix well.
Dip chicken in batter to coat.
Fry in hot oil (375°) until golden brown (about 8 minutes).
Drain.
Mix honey and mustard and serve with Nuggets.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well all ingredients together.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped pecans. Chill in refrigerator for a couple of hours.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Simmer onions and mushrooms in large skillet with butter; cook until tender.
Stir in rice, chicken, broccoli and soup.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with cheese, then bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato dumpling
directions: Wrap small pieces of sweet potatoes in crescent roll and place in oven safe dish.
Bring to boil water, butter, sugar, vanilla and cinnamon.
Pour over the potato dumplings. Bake at 350° until bread is brown.
Enjoy; it is great!

title: eggplant soup(greek)
directions: Put all in saucepan, except milk; add water "half way up" and boil until soft.
Remove bay leaf.
Have eggplant, skin on, cut in chunks, and potato, cut in chunks.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb dessert cake with caramel sauce
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, water and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in nuts and rhubarb.
Bake at 350° in greased 9-inch square pan for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: hot cider punch
directions: Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve hot in punch bowl.

title: alleyne's cheese ball
directions: While
cream cheese softens to room temperature combine dried beef,
green
onions,
Worcestershire
sauce and m.s.g. Work
this mixture into the softened cream cheese.
Shape into a
ball.
For added
flavor
and	decoration,
roll
in pecan pieces.
Place
in refrigerator
overnight to let the flavors blend together.
If you don't have that much time, the process can
be	speeded
up by adding extra onions and Worcestershire sauce to taste.
Serve on snack crackers.

title: cinnamon coffee
directions: Add two teaspoons ground cinnamon to coffee in a filter coffee-maker.
Brew as usual.

title: cranberry mousse
directions: In a saucepan, heat cranberry juice cocktail to boiling; remove from heat.
Stir in jello until dissolved.
In a bowl, beat the cranberry sauce with electric beater on high
for 1 minute. Stir into gelatin mixture.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 1/2 hours, until thickened but not set.
Fold in Cool Whip topping until mixture is thoroughly blended.
Spoon into dessert dishes or 9-inch prepared pie shell.
Chill until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: popcorn munchies
directions: Pop corn as directed.
Mix all ingredients except popcorn and boil for 4 minutes.
Pour over popcorn and stir.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Let cool and store in a sealed container.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done.
Drain and set aside.
Thinly slice onion in a large mixing bowl.
Add parsley, salt, pepper, vinegar and oil.
Stir together and set aside.
Peel potatoes.
Slice potatoes in bowl with onion.
Turn easy after adding each sliced potato so all is coated with dressing when you are finished slicing.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Do not refrigerate. Before serving, taste and add more salt, if needed.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain and rinse until cooled.
Add chopped vegetables, salt and pepper; mix well.
Stir in enough Ranch dressing to make moist.

title: chipped beef and noodles
directions: Melt fat or drippings in top of double boiler.
Add onion; brown lightly.
Stir in flour.
Add milk gradually; cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheese; stir until melted. Stir in chipped beef and lima beans.
Place over boiling water; heat thoroughly.

title: hot olive cheese balls
directions: Blend butter and cheese.
Mix in flour, paprika and salt. Shape about 1 teaspoon dough around each olive.
Freeze.
Place frozen balls on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Makes 30.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli in minimum of water with 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon lemon juice until tender; drain.
Saute mushrooms and onion with 1 tablespoon butter until tender.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Combine all of the ingredients except for beets.
Heat the mixture until it boils.
Pour this mixture over the sliced beets; let stand 6 hours.

title: italian hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion, garlic powder and salt. Combine in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish the meat, soup, water and noodles.
Add oregano and Italian seasoning.
Place cheese slices on top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: turkey and sausage canapes
directions: Grate cheese ahead.
Also, mince onions.
Saute turkey, onions and sausage ahead and drain well.

title: ham and raisin sauce
directions: Bake ham in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt cheese and margarine.
Empty sugar and cocoa in a large bowl.
Pour in melted margarine and cheese; mix well.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Spread on a large buttered pan; refrigerate until well cooled.
Cut into squares.
Yields 5 pounds.

title: can't stop eatin' dip
directions: Heat cream cheese over low heat until it melts.
Add chili; mix well.
Serve with Fritos.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time with a little flour each time.
Beat good after each egg and flour addition.
Add lemon juice, almond, and vanilla.
Pour in greased tube pan.
Bake 325 degrees for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and let cool and nearly congeal.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into dish and jell.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.

title: french lace cookies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
In bowl, mix butter, oats, sugar, flour, corn syrup, milk and vanilla until well blended.
Drop by level teaspoon, 3 inches apart onto foil-covered cookie sheets. Spread thin with a spatula.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Melt chocolate morsels over hot water.
Spread chocolate onto the flat side of one cookie.
Add another cookie to top to make a sandwich.

title: quality pot roast
directions: Brown onions and garlic in oil.
Brown meat on all sides.
Add raisins, bay leaves and water.
Cover tightly and simmer 3 hours or until tender on very low heat.
Remove meat; strain and measure liquid.
For each cup of liquid, add 2 tablespoons of flour.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Serve gravy with meat and a side dish of corn and spiced red crab apples.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: orange sweet potato souffle
directions: Peel and chunk sweet potatoes; cook.
Drain.
Mash through sieve to get strings out, if necessary.
Add margarine, beaten eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Put in orange shells or baking dish.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, salt, milk and corn.
Place in casserole.
Bake at 500° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tomato pasta sauce
directions: In food processor bowl with metal blade or blender container, combine chopped tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Process until smooth.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Melt margarine in soup pot.
Add onion, carrot and celery and saute until soft.
Add flour and cornstarch and cook until bubbly. Add chicken stock and milk, stirring until smooth.
Add soda and Cheddar cheese, stirring until a smooth blend.
Taste for seasoning; add salt and pepper if needed.
About 15 minutes before serving, stir in 1 cup of beer.

title: cornia's chicken breast casserole
directions: Parboil chicken breasts and remove bones.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix soup and water and pour over chicken.
Add broth to stuffing mix and mix well.
Spoon over chicken and soup. Bake 35 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese get soft.
When soft, mix with other ingredients except for pecans.
Form mixture into logs or balls. Roll logs or balls in finely chopped pecans to cover evenly.
Roll in plastic wrap and refrigerate.

title: famous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter and white and brown sugars at slow speed for 2 minutes. Add vanilla, salt and eggs.
Mix ingredients for 1 minute at slow speed, then for 2 minutes at high speed.
Add flour and baking soda.
Mix until flour is blended into a smooth dough.
Add chocolate chips and mix for 1 minute at low speed.
Spoon off cookies onto cookie pan and bake for approximately 8 minutes.

title: tamale pie
directions: Chop up tamales. Add the cans of chili, olives, corn and Fritos.
Top with Cheese.
Heat, uncovered, at 350° until hot, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Store in an airtight container.
To serve, place 1/3 cup mix into 1 cup boiling water. Stir well.

title: spaghetti supreme
directions: Cook spaghetti; rinse and drain.
Brown onion; add ground beef and brown.
Add tomato soup and mix.
Grease dish.
Place in layers the spaghetti, cheese and meat mixture.
Pour over all the diluted mushroom soup.
Cook at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: grandmother's punch
directions: Mix and cool.
Goes a long way!

title: hot taco rice
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Add salsa, tomato sauce and bouillon cube.
Bring to a full boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, prepare rice as directed on package.
Serve beef mixture over rice; top with garnishes.

title: grilled chicken wings
directions: Mix dry ingredients in saucepan.
Stir in water, lemon juice, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring until mixture thickens.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Cook wings over slow fire for 20 to 30 minutes.
Spread glaze on wings for last 10 minutes.

title: good party punch
directions: Put Kool-Aid in punch bowl.
Add ice cream.
Pour ginger ale in punch bowl last.
Be sure all ingredients are cold.

title: 24 hour pickles
directions: Cut pickles in quarters or smaller pieces. Put in stone crock alternately with a layer of dill and sliced onions. Boil brine well. Pour boiling hot over pickles. In
24 hours
these pickles are ready to eat. Will keep in an open jar in refrigerator. To can, in hot jars, reheat same juice, pour on hot and seal.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Mix
nuts
and	flour.	Pour melted margarine over nuts and flour.
Mix
well.	Spread	on
bottom
of 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan. Use
fork or fingertips.
Cook in 325° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or	until
light
brown.
Let
cool.
Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Fold
in
Cool
Whip.
Spread on cooled crust. Spread blueberry
pie
filling over the cream cheese mixture. Refrigerate for 6 hours before serving.

title: soft pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Add pumpkin and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients. Mix well.
Add nuts or raisins.
Stir well.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop by tablespoons 2 inches apart on a greased baking sheet (I use Pam).
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Store in a tightly covered container.
Use in 3 days or freeze.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: fruit cake ala marie
directions: Chop pineapple, cherries and nuts.
Cream butter and sugar. Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Separate eggs.
Beat yolks. Add the lemon flavoring.
Add alternately the egg yolks and flour mixture to butter and sugar.
Continue beating.
Begin and end with flour.
Flour fruit and nuts.
Add to batter and mix well. Beat egg whites and fold in mixture.
Let stand overnight.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Heat oil in skillet on medium heat.
Add onions and bell peppers.
Cook and stir until tender.
Remove to serving platter. Cover to keep warm.
Combine meat, bread crumbs and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix in egg white.
Shape into four 1/2-inch thick oval patties.
Place patties in same skillet.
Cook on low heat on both sides until desired doneness.
Transfer to serving platter with onions and peppers.
Re-cover.
Stir flour and some salt and pepper to taste into skillet.
Cook one minute.
Add water, ketchup or tomatoes, pinch of sugar and soy sauce.
If you use tomatoes, use less water.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Pour over patties and vegetables.

title: chocolate christmas balls
directions: Melt butter in condensed milk over low heat.
Add salt and vanilla.
Mix in sugar.
Mixture will be very thick.
Add nuts and coconut.

title: hamburger salsa dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Microwave Velveeta and picante sauce or salsa in a microwave-safe bowl, at least 1 1/2-quart size, for 5 minutes or until Velveeta spread is melted. (Stir after 3 minutes.)
Stir in cilantro.
Makes 3 cups.
Serve hot with tortilla chips or vegetable dippers.
Easy and fun!

title: frosted brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and shortening.
Add sugar to eggs.
Add to chocolate mixture.
Sift all dry ingredients and add to mixture. Beat well.
Fold in nuts and flavoring.
Pour in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Mix liquid ingredients and add to flour mixture, stirring just enough to moisten.
Fold in raisins, chopped apples, etc., as desired.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: banana split pie
directions: Melt the butter and then mix it with the graham cracker crumbs. Spread this mixture on the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch dish. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes. Cool.

title: green tomato pickles(serves 4 or 5 per quart)
directions: Put all ingredients in large pot; mix well.
Do not place lid on pot, heat over open fire.
When it barely starts to boil, remove from heat.
Immediately
place in quart jars (pints may be used) and seal.

title: garlic spread
directions: Mix
in
bowl.
Spread on sliced bread and bake at 400° for 15 minutes to make garlic bread.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together with blender, except 7-Up. Lastly, add 7-Up.
Makes 58 cups.

title: french crepes
directions: Mix together flour and salt in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center of the mixture.

Add eggs, butter and 1/2 of milk. With a whisk gradually stir the flour into the liquid mixture and as you do slowly add more milk until consistency is that of cream. When all is at this stage whisk lumps out.
Pour 1/4 of batter into pre-heated fry pan or crepe pan (preferred).
Cook both sides on low heat until lightly brown.

title: cornucopia snacks
directions: Place a dab of Cool Whip, peanut butter or cream cheese onto Bugle snack.
Add a few pieces of cereal.
Serve same day.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream oleo and 1 cup flour mixed with salt, soda and fructose. Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Add rest of flour and buttermilk alternately, then vanilla and mashed bananas.
Put in greased pan (bottom only) and bake at 350°.

title: stained glass salad
directions: Mix all the above together and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat in large pan.
Add hot water and onion soup. Cover and let come to
a	boil.
Add
rest
of ingredients and simmer 1 1/2 hours.	I add spaetzle before serving.

title: butterfinger pie
directions: Crush Butterfingers.
Save a small amount to sprinkle on top. Stir crushed Butterfingers into Cool Whip.
Pour into the crust. Makes 2 pies.

title: banana orange muffincake
directions: Heat
oven
to
Grease
bottom
of
9-inch round spring-form
pan
or
cake pan.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add combined banana, juice, margarine, egg and grated orange peel, mixing just until moistened.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 10 minutes on wire rack; remove from pan.
Combine remaining ingredients; drizzle evenly over
cake while still warm.
Makes 12 servings.
Each serving (1/12 of cake) has 190 calories, 32 g carbohydrates, 3 g protein and 6 g fat.

title: german's sweet chocolate cake(old original recipe)
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat well. Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Mix well.

title: baked stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.

Stems should be chopped finely. Saute onion in melted butter until transparent. Add chopped mushroom stems and saute for 2 minutes. Place bread crumbs in a bowl with mushroom stems, onion, salt, pepper, lemon juice, tomato paste and oregano. Mix well and stuff into mushrooms. Leave at room temperature for 1/2 hour before baking at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Stir water, sugar and cornstarch until well blended.
Boil 2 minutes, then add jello.
Pour this mixture over sliced, fresh strawberries in a baked pie shell.
Stir gently with fork. Cool. Finish by using whipped topping.
This will make 2 pies.

title: chocolate dream dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in glass baking dish (8 1/2 x 11-inches).
Add flour to butter paste.
Add pecans (1/2).
Bake until brown.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Mix all but beans in a large stockpot.
Simmer for 3 hours. Spoon off fat while cooking.
Add kidney beans for the last 30 minutes of simmer time.
Serve over corn chips or cornbread topped with grated sharp Cheddar cheese.
Can be frozen for later use.

title: confetti scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter over medium heat.
Saute onion until tender.
Stir in potatoes, soup and milk.
Add cheese, green pepper, pimento, pepper and 1/2 cup crumbs.
Pour into shallow casserole; top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pickles like "babcia" used to make
directions: To make your own Polish-style pickles (or pickled cucumbers as they are also known), you should start with fresh pickling cucumbers of roughly 4 to 5 inches in length.
The best are those grown without chemical fertilizers.
Soak cucumbers in a sink of cold water 30 minutes if they are freshly picked or up to 3 hours if they are not.
Scrub well, then scald with boiling water and allow to drip-dry in an earthenware crock of glass jar large enough to accommodate 4 pounds of cucumbers.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: meat and potato quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Stir together the oil and potato. Press evenly into a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake for 15 minutes until just beginning to brown.
Remove the crust from the oven and place the cheese, meat and onion in layers.
Beat together the milk, eggs, salt and pepper and pour onto the other ingredients. Sprinkle with parsley flakes (optional) and return to the oven and bake about 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Allow to cool 5 minutes before cutting.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mash avocados. Add onion, lemon juice, garlic salt and salad dressing. Mix together and serve.

title: pineapple quickie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and soda together and add eggs, vanilla, pineapple and juice.
Mix thoroughly and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook bacon and crumble.
Combine salad dressing, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over other ingredients.

title: pecan cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans.
Mix well.
Shape into an oblong loaf and roll in pecans.
Chill overnight.

title: green pepper casserole
directions: Cook rice in melted butter in skillet until lightly toasted, stirring frequently.
Spread in greased baking dish.
Arrange green pepper on top.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water; pour over rice mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook ground beef, onion, celery, and garlic in skillet until meat is browned.
Stir in tomato puree, oregano, salt, and pepper.
Simmer covered for 5 minutes.
Pour over rice mixture.
Cover with foil.
Continue baking for 15 minutes. Remove cover, sprinkle with cheese and bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: microwavable yam and ham dinner
directions: Score edges of ham slice to prevent curling.
Place ham in glass baking dish.
