Arrange yams over ham.
Spoon on pineapple and marmalade.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap.
Cook for 13 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes, then serve.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: cream puffs
directions: Put water and butter into heavy 1 quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling,
melting
margarine, reduce heat to very low.
Add flour all
at
once.
Stir
until mixture leaves sides of pan, looks dry and
forms
a
ball.
Remove from heat, let cool 10 minutes.
Add eggs,
one
at
a time, beating well after each addition.	Beat until
mixture
is	smooth and velvety.
Drop from spoon
onto ungreased
baking
sheet.
Bake
in hot oven (400°) for
to 45 minutes until puffs are dry.
Carefully remove from pan onto cake rack.	Carefully cut off top of each puff.
When cool, fill with cream puff filling.
Sprinkle tops with confectioners sugar. Makes 4 to 6.

title: scalloped parsley potatoes (vegetable)
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut into wedges or slices.
Cook potatoes in a little water for about 10 minutes.
They should not get mushy.
In a saucepan, combine butter, milk and flour.
Whisk together; bring to a boil, stirring.
Cook for about 5 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, parsley and potatoes.
Heat slowly.
Season to taste.
Sprinkle with extra parsley when serving.

title: mom's barbecue for a crowd
directions: Dice onion and celery.
Cook in small amount of water until soft.
Brown hamburger and drain grease off.
Combine all ingredients and simmer so flavor goes through.
Freezes well.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick oleo.
Spread evenly in 13 x 2 x 8-inch pan.
Mix Eagle Brand, eggs, sugar and 2 sticks oleo.
Beat 10 minutes.
Spread over cracker crumbs mixture. Spread crushed and drained pineapple over.
Slice crossway 3 or 4 bananas.
Cover with one large (903) Cool Whip.
Sprinkle pecans and maraschino cherries.
Chill in icebox.

title: macaroni salad
directions: In a bowl, mix mustard, sugar, salt, pepper, celery, pimento and onion with mayonnaise. Add to macaroni and chill overnight.

title: fudge
directions: Mix together the
first 3 ingredients.
Bring to a hard boil stage.
Remove from
heat and stir in butter and vanilla. Beat until you get
a
very
thick
consistency.
Pour
into a buttered platter.
Cut into squares when warm.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Mix together margarine and sugar; add eggs and mix well.
Mix flour and soda in separate bowl.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately, ending with flour.
Add orange rind, dates, nuts, orange slice candy and coconut; mix well.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 275° to 300° for 2 hours.
Cool on rack 15 minutes; invert cake on rack to cool.

title: cloud nine cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder and cream of tartar that has been sifted together well. Drop on cookie sheet in marble size; flatten with fork.
Bake at 325°.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in greased baking dish to cover bottom (1 layer), then cover generously with flour.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add onion, if desired.
Add several "butter pats" and then place another layer of same ingredients.
Continue until all potatoes are used.
Add milk to cover the layers and bake at 275° to 300° until tender and creamy, about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: date bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and soda.
Combine sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add to date mixture.
Add flour and nuts. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Makes about 4 to 5 loaves.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Fry out bacon or salt pork and add potatoes, cut in small cubes.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Add clams.
Add water and cover.
Let cook until tender.
Add butter and evaporated milk. Same recipe can be used substituting scallops for clams.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together for 4 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: country style chicken kiev
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In 2-quart saucepan melt butter. Meanwhile on piece of wax paper combine bread crumbs, cheese and spices.
Dip breasts in butter, then roll in crumbs to coat. Place skin side up in ungreased 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake near center for 50 to 60 minutes or until golden brown and chicken is tender.
Meanwhile add wine, green onion and parsley to remaining melted butter.
When chicken is golden brown, pour butter sauce mixture around and over.
Return to oven 3 to 5 minutes more or just until sauce is hot.

title: pecan cookie bars
directions: Melt butter slow and stir in sugar and vanilla.
Let boil for 2 minutes.
Stir in pecans.
Pour over graham crackers in lined pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Take off foil immediately or they will stick.

title: celery with mushrooms
directions: Clean celery and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Heat butter in large skillet.
Add celery, salt, pepper and paprika.
Cook over high heat
until
tender,
stirring about 8 minutes.
Add mushrooms (you may want
to
add
a
little more butter to the fresh ones).
Cook	a
couple of minutes longer to saute mushrooms.	Serves 6.

title: potato skins
directions: Boil or microwave washed whole potatoes until soft.
After potatoes cool, slice in half and core out potatoes, leaving 1/4-inch of potato and skin.

title: carrot ginger bisque
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat. Add carrots and onions. Cover pan and cook vegetables until they begin to soften, stirring occasionally, about 15 minutes. Mix in ginger and coriander. Add 2 cups broth; re-cover pan and simmer soup until carrots are very tender (about 20 to 30 minutes). Puree soup in blender or food processor (or even use a potato masher) until smooth. Add half and half and remaining broth to soup. If desired, season with salt (remember, though, the chicken broth is very salty) and pepper. Serve with parsley (or cilantro) on the side or sprinkled on top. This dish is better if prepared in advance, refrigerated and reheated over low heat before serving. Serves 8. Can do ahead.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening over low heat.
Cool.
Add next 3 ingredients. Beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Chill at least 1hour.
Shape in 1-inch balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake only until light brown and cracks appear, 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: heavenly cake
directions: Grease 2 (9-inch) layer cake pans.
Line bottoms with wax paper.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Add a little salt to noodles.
After noodles are done, drain them in strainer. Pour noodles in a bowl and cut up broccoli, tomato and onion; add to noodles.
Pour salad dressing over noodles and mix well. Refrigerate before serving.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Add 1 teaspoon baking soda to dates and cover with hot water. Cool.
Cream sugar and shortening until light.
Add eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with vanilla and date mixture. Stir until smooth after each addition.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips and nuts on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares and serve with whipped cream and cherries.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice and sugar.
Add drained pineapple.

title: frosted sugar cookies
directions: Beat brown sugar and margarine at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; mix. Combine 3 cups flour, baking powder and salt; stir.
Add flour little by little to mixture.
Chill 2 hours.
Divide dough in half.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon flour evenly on work surface and roll dough 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch cookie cutter.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheets coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes or until edges lightly brown.
Combine powdered sugar and water to make frosting.
Design cookie! Contains 1.4 g fat.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients; layer 1/2 in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Top with 1 cup Cheddar and 1 cup Monterey Jack cheese; then repeat layer.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Simmer together for 20 minutes all ingredients except hamburger; add hamburger.

title: e-z stroganoff
directions: Brown burger. Drain. Stir in cream of onion soup and 1/2 cup sour cream.
Heat 3 minutes.
Pour over cooked noodles.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill in refrigerator for at least 2 hours. Garnish with maraschino cherries and nuts.

title: karen's chili
directions: *For hot chili, add 1/3 cup ground cayenne pepper.
For hotter chili, add 16 ounces jalapeno peppers, chopped.

title: flake cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cream butter, then add sugars and cream until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add flour mixture and cereal, mixing just until blended. Shape dough into 1-inch balls with floured hands.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool, then store in tightly covered container.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: chris's cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350 degrees for approximately 35-40 minutes.
A bundt pan works well for this cake.

title: cioppino
directions: Clean shrimp, clams, and crab and cut fresh fish in bite-size pieces.
Saute onion and pepper in oil.
Add tomatoes with juice and wine, basil and mushrooms (that have been soaked in warm water).
Steam the clams, add the water from the clams and simmer 15 minutes.
Add shrimp, crab and fish.
Add oregano, salt and pepper and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Serve with Dino's French bread.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan to form crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; cool.
Mix 1 cup Cool Whip, sugar and cream cheese; spread over crust.
Mix the two puddings together with 3 cups of milk.
Add as next layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Chill 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: cheesecake dip
directions: Beat cheese, sugar and milk until well blended and smooth. Fold in Cool Whip and vanilla and store in refrigerator.
Use to dip fresh fruit, pretzels and pound cake cubes.
Makes 2 cups.
If you use lite ingredients, approximately 6 calories per teaspoon.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Stew the chicken in a Dutch oven until done.
Let cool and remove it from the bone.
Combine all the ingredients into the broth, except butter, and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until done.
Add butter or margarine.
Stir in thoroughly.
Serves 8.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Place in shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Spread onions on top.
Salt and pepper.
Spread soup over onions.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fry bread
directions: In small saucepan, heat buttermilk until bubbles form at edge of pan.
Set aside to cool.
When buttermilk has cooled, stir in egg, oil, sugar and yeast until well combined.
Set aside 5 minutes for yeast to soften.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: In a large pot or Dutch oven, add V-8 juice, soups, bouillon, mixed vegetables, onions and beef.
Add 3 soup cans of water.
Add more water, if desired.
Cook over low heat until vegetables are done.
Do not add salt.
Makes a lot and freezes well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package.
Drain.
Grate cheese, beat eggs and chop onions.
Mix all with soup and mayonnaise.
Add to broccoli and mix.
Put in casserole dish and top with Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: noodle kugel
directions: Mix eggs and cheeses together, combine with cooked, well-drained, noodles and margarine.
Place in one large (or two small) greased casserole.
Spread bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 30 minutes or until bubbly and lightly browned.

title: mexican taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off most of grease.
Add onion, and cook a few minutes more.
Transfer hamburger and onion to stock pot or large kettle; add all the other ingredients.
Cook slowly until the flavor strikes through and all ingredients are hot. Serve with crackers or tortilla chips.

title: bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: You will also need cooking spray, two 2-cup measuring cups and 2 large mixing bowls.

title: apricot salad
directions: Heat nectar.
Add lemon jello, pineapple, bananas and gelatin. Pour into mold, if desired.

title: waikiki meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, cracker crumbs, onions, egg, salt, ginger and milk.
Shape with tablespoon into balls.
Brown in shortening.
Set aside.
Pour out leftover grease.
Mix cornstarch and brown sugar. Stir in pineapple juice from pineapple bits, vinegar and soy sauce. Cook over medium heat until thickened; boil 1 minute.
Add green pepper, pineapple tidbits and meatballs.
Heat through.
Serve with rice.

title: no cook vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, cream, sugar, salt and vanilla in a bowl.
Mix with mixer and pour in ice cream can.
Finish with milk.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
While waiting on oven, cut peeled potatoes into large chunks.
Boil for 30 minutes.
While potatoes are boiling, melt 1/2 stick butter in saucepan on medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons butter and stir.
Add 2 cups milk and 6 slices of cheese.
Heat until sauce starts to thicken.
(If sauce seems too thick, add 1/2 cup milk until desired consistency is reached.) Remove from heat.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients and let marinate overnight.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: casserole fruit cake
directions: Squeeze 1 orange and combine juice and 1/2 cup sugar; set aside.
Put rind, nuts and dates through food chopper.
Blend Crisco, 1 cup sugar and eggs together.
Stir in fruit-nut mixture. Add sour milk and flour sifted with salt and soda.
Turn into greased casserole and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove and pour orange juice over cake at once.

title: veggie bars
directions: Roll out the crescent rolls and bake until brown (11 x 13-inch pan).
Mix the cream cheese, Ranch dressing mix and mayonnaise together.
Spread over cooked crust.
Top with chopped vegetables that you desire.
I use 2 to 4 chopped green peppers, 1 stalk chopped celery and broccoli and a bunch of green onions.
Top with shredded cheese and bacon bits.

title: cranberry cream cheese mold
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in a large bowl for 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in cold water and cinnamon. Pour 1-1/2 cup of mixed gelatin into medium bowl.
Refrigerate until thickened (spoon drawn through leaves a definite impression).
Reserve remaining 1 cup at room temperature.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Stir together the flour, granulated sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Mix in milk, oil and vanilla with a fork until smooth.
Spread evenly in a 9 x 9
x 2-inch ungreased pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour hot water over batter.
Bake for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Fill dessert dishes with a generous scoop of vanilla ice cream and cover with Hot Fudge Sundae Cake.

title: cornflake cabbage bake
directions: Mix melted margarine and crushed cornflakes, place in bottom of baking dish.
Add shredded cabbage on top.
Mix other ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Add cheese on top and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Frost with 2 cups of salad dressing.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons sugar over dressing. Let sit overnight.
Toss lightly.
Garnish with crushed bacon, grated cheese, chives and sliced boiled eggs.

title: grandma's goulash
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add chopped onion and seasoning.
Blend well.
Add tomato sauce and macaroni.
Simmer until tender.

title: old-fashioned chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa; separate eggs.
Beat egg yolks; add vanilla and milk.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Cook until thick.
Pour into crust.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Cut the wings into 3 sections; discard tips.
Mix soy sauce, sugar, ginger, mustard and garlic.
Blend thoroughly.
Add wings and marinate overnight.
Bake uncovered in a preheated 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Arrange pork chops in pan.
Place slice of lemon and onion on each.
Blend remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover and bake at 350° until tender, approximately 1 hour.

title: carrot spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth and spread on bread.
Makes 1 loaf of bread.

title: pork chops with apples and stuffing
directions: In a skillet, brown pork chops in oil over medium-high heat. Meanwhile prepare stuffing according to package directions.
Spread pie filling into a greased 13x9x2-inch baking dish.
Place pork chops on top; spoon stuffing over chops.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken, 1 teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon pepper and water to cover in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer 1 hour or until tender.
Remove chicken from broth, cool and debone.
Cut potatoes, celery and carrots into broth.
Simmer until tender. Drain vegetables, reserving 3 cups broth.
Combine chicken and vegetables and turn into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt butter; add flour, cook and stir 1 minute.
Gradually stir in milk, broth and bouillon cube; stir until thickened.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over chicken, vegetable mixture.
Place pastry crust on top and bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: zucchini-pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs and mix in sugar, oil, vanilla, zucchini and pineapple.
Sift dry ingredients and mix thoroughly with first mixture.
Add raisins and nuts and mix well.
Pour into 4 small oiled and floured loaf pans.
I spray mine.
Turn oven to 325° (do not preheat) and bake 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Allow to cool in pans.

title: creamy chicken and biscuits
directions: Cook biscuits using package directions.
Place both soups, milk and chicken in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until warm, stirring often.
On each plate place 2 biscuits covered with one-fifth of soup mixture.
Serves 5.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes.
Mix all ingredients in well drained potatoes. Must refrigerate.
Yields 15 to 20 servings.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Saute shrimp in garlic butter until the shrimp turns pink. Add wine and cook about 1 minute.
Add parsley and salt.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, if desired.

title: bubble & squeak
directions: Boil 4 peeled potatoes til soft, mash with butter or margarine.
Finely slice half a cabbage in grinder or processor. Cook and drain cabbage, cool and squeeze out moisture.
Mix with cool potatoes, salt, pepper and corned beef.
Form into 8 patties, dusting both sides of each with flour.
Fry in 1/4 inch of oil til brown on both sides.

title: sausage noodle bake
directions: Heat soup and milk in microwave.
Add 1 cup of cheese and stir until melted.
Add sausage, noodles, pepper and pimento.
Stir. Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with French fried onions and the rest of the cheese.
Bake, covered, 20 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes more.

title: easy cheesy chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 400°. In nonstick skillet over high heat, combine chicken, peppers and onion. Saute until cooked. Remove skillet from heat. Add 1/2 cup of cheese and 1/4 cup enchilada sauce to skillet; stir to combine.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Sprinkle chicken pieces with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in 6 to 8 quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook until browned on all sides, about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle in garlic salt, rosemary, oregano, tarragon, sage and flour.
Turn chicken pieces to coat evenly.
Stir in wine and onion.
Cover and simmer until meat is cooked, about 45 to 55 minutes.
With slotted spoon, remove chicken and onion pieces to serving bowl and keep warm. Bring wine broth in Dutch oven to boiling.
Add mustard and milk. Reduce heat to simmer.
Cook, stirring, until mixture thickens, about 10 minutes.
To serve, pour sauce over the meat and onions.

title: raisin bread pudding
directions: Melt margarine in 1-quart baking dish.
Add bread (cut into 1/2-inch squares) and raisins; toss to coat.
Beat eggs with milk, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Pour over bread and raisins in pan. Bake at 350° until puffy and golden, about 45 minutes.

title: tuna spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti as to directions.
Heat butter, garlic and green pepper; cook 5 minutes.
Blend in mixture of flour, salt and paprika.
Remove from heat; blend in Worcestershire sauce, mustard, soup and milk gradually and cook until sauce is smooth and thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon juice, olives, tuna and cooked spaghetti.
Turn into casserole; sprinkle top with melted butter, bread crumbs and cheese.
Heat in oven for 25 minutes at 350° and garnish with boiled eggs and paprika.

title: rice-pork chop casserole
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with flour, salt and pepper;
brown in fat.
Place chops in casserole dish.
On top of each pork chop place 1 slice onion and 1 tsp. rice.
Season with salt and pepper and sage.
Pour tomatoes over all.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate upside down cake
directions: Sprinkle pecans and coconut in buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Spoon into prepared pan.
Prepare cream cheese and confectioners sugar by beating with mixer until smooth.
Spoon evenly over cake, leaving 1-inch edge. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: zuppa di scalora(escarole soup)
directions: Bring the broth to boil.
Add the carrot, celery and onion. Simmer over low heat for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook slow all the ingredients, except peanut butter, until it forms a soft ball when tested in cold water.
Remove from stove. Add peanut butter while still hot.
Stir rapidly until it begins to thicken. Pour out on slightly greased pan.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions and let stand in water 2 hours; drain.
Put into large jar.
Put in vinegar, sugar and spices and boil 1 minute.
Pour mixture into jar with cucumbers and onions. Seal.

title: betty dessert
directions: Mix butter, flour and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 20-25 minutes or till brown.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool whip. Spread on cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk and spread on top of first mixture and let set 30 minutes in refrigerator.
Then spread on a layer of Cool Whip and sprinkle on a layer of crushed nuts.

title: chicken paprikash(microwave)
directions: In a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole, combine garlic, mushrooms, celery, onion and butter. Cover and microwave on High 3 to 5 minutes or until tender. Drain.
Mix in remaining ingredients except sour cream. Cover and microwave on High 2 to 5 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring once during cooking. Blend in sour cream.
Reduce power to 50% (Medium).
Microwave 30 seconds to 1 1/2 minutes to heat through, if needed. Serves 4.

title: almond chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in refrigerator overnight. Crumble potato chips over top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: custard rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add salt and vanilla. Stir in milk.
Add rice.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole, buttered.
Place casserole in pan of hot water and bake in 350° oven about 50 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean. May be sprinkled with nutmeg before baking.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream
sugar
and margarine.
Add flour, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Pour
into unbaked pie shell.
Preheat oven to 450°, but bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: potato salad for 50 people(this recipe can be doubled.)
directions: Shred the first 3 vegetables and then mix with your hands. Add vinegar, oil, salt, 3 pounds sugar and celery seed.
Mix very well.
Let stand for about 1/2 hour and then taste for sweetness. If desired, add 2 pounds more sugar.
Wait 1/2 hour and check taste again.

title: kelly's perfect pancakes
directions: You put the milk in.
You scramble the eggs up.
Then you put the eggs in the pancakes.
Then you put the baking powder in. Then you put the sugar in.
Then you put the oil in the pan.
Then you put it on 5°.
Take a cup and put the batter in the pan.
Let it cook for a few minutes.
Turn it over to the other side.
Then you put some more butter in, then you do the same thing.
Take them out, and they're ready to eat.
Put them on your plate, then my mommy calls us for breakfast.
We put syrup on them.
We eat with our forks.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookie recipe
directions: Cream sugars, shortening, butter, eggs, salt, baking soda and extracts.
Gradually add the 2 cups flour.
Next, add the oatmeal, chocolate chips and walnuts.
Drop on cookie sheet by spoonfuls. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put vegetables in gallon jar.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over vegetables.
Let stand one week in refrigerator before using.
Will keep in refrigerator up to 1 year.

title: applesauce cookies (mix in a jar)
directions: Combine flour, salt, cinnamon and baking soda - stir well. Place flour mixture in a clean mason jar. Pack down tight so everything will fit in jar. Add other ingredients, one item at a time, packing each layer. Put the lid on the jar and tie a ribbon around the lid. You can add a personalized label if you wish. As an added touch, tie a wooden spoon to the lid with a piece of ribbon. Attach to jar:

Applesauce cookies whip butter or shortening until light and fluffy. Add egg and applesauce and beat until mixed. Stir in ingredients from this jar until well combined. Drop teaspoons of dough on a greased cookie sheet. Bake for 8-12 min. at 350°.

title: three flavor pound cake
directions: Mix together the sugar, margarine and oil until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour alternately with milk, ending with flour.
Add flavorings.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a greased and floured tube pan.
Cool cake 20 minutes; turn out.
Heat 1/2 cup sugar and water to boiling.
After cooling, add almond flavoring.
Drizzle over cooled cake.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients, add egg and milk.
Cover opening of funnel with finger.
Pour 1/4 cup batter in funnel, release batter into hot oil, moving funnel in circular motion.
Fry 2 minutes or until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towel, sprinkle with powdered sugar and syrup.

title: chocolate on a stick
directions: *You can find it at Party City.

title: impossible ham and cheese pie
directions: Grease a large pie plate.
Layer ham, peas and onion.
Beat until smooth eggs, milk, Bisquick, Miracle Whip, mustard and pepper.
Pour over ham, peas and onion.
Sprinkle the cheese over top; bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate crackles
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix melted butter, melted chocolate and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well.
Add vanilla and stir.
Add dry ingredients and mix until combined. Dough will be soft.
Chill.
Drop by teaspoons into powdered sugar.
Shape into ball.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Boil 1 cup 7-Up; dissolve jello.
Add softened cream cheese (not melted).
Beat with mixer until smooth and blended.
Add one other cup cold 7-Up; blend.
Chill until soft set.
Fold in Cool Whip until smooth looking.
Very refreshing and lite.
Cool until set.
Store in fridge.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in punch bowl; stir gently until sherbet melts.
Prepare 15 to 20 minutes before using.
Can substitute with any flavor sherbet.

title: spicy chili toast
directions: Heat oven to 375`.
Melt butter; add chili powder.
Cut bread into 1/4-inch slices.
Spread each slice with chili mixture. Arrange slices on cookie sheet.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and flour; mix well.
Chill dough.
Roll out thin.
Brush cookie with egg whites.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on top or top with crushed nuts.
Cut into strips.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: feta-stuffed pita burgers
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine all meat mixture ingredients except beef.
Add meat and knead well.
Shape mixture into 8 (1/4-inch thick) patties (about 4 inches in diameter).

title: mexican salad
directions: Chop onion, tomato and lettuce.
Toss with cheese and dressing.
Add crushed tortilla chips.
Slice and add 1 large avocado.
Brown ground beef, add drained kidney beans and salt; simmer for 10 minutes and add to cold salad.
Decorate with tortilla chips, avocado and tomato slices.

title: paczki (jelly donuts)(polish)
directions: Sift 1 cup flour into boiling milk; remove from heat and beat until smooth.
Let cool.
Dissolve yeast in the 1/4 cup milk.
Add to flour mixture; stir and let stand a half an hour.

title: chicken broccoli dish
directions: Cook broccoli and
place
on bottom of casserole.
Boil chicken breasts for 1/2 hour,
then
place on top of broccoli. Mix soup, mayonnaise and Cheddar cheese together and pour over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water in a bowl.
Add marshmallows and dissolve. Stir in pineapple, cranberry sauce and nuts. Pour into a mold and refrigerate.

title: frozen fruit slush
directions: Mix ingredients.
Freeze
in Tupperware container.
Set out about 1 hour before serving.
Serve in sherbet dishes.

title: pork chops and apples
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Brown chops on all sides in frying pans. Place apple slices in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon; dot with butter.
Top with chops.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cool, peel and cube baked potatoes.
Place in a baking dish. Pour melted butter over potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add crumbled up bacon over potatoes.
Sprinkle with chopped onions. Spread Cheez Whiz over potatoes.
Place in a 450° oven and cook until cheese is melted.

title: lemon chicken pasta
directions: Marinate the chicken in wine, lemon and rosemary for 1 hour at room temperature.
Meanwhile, cut the asparagus and carrots into bite size pieces and steam until crisp-tender.
Drain the chicken and reserve marinade.
Saute the chicken in 1 tablespoon oil until golden.
Remove and wipe out pan.
Add reserved marinade, cream and chicken stock to pan.
Simmer over medium heat until thickened.
Add cooked chicken and vegetables to sauce until heated through.
Toss sauce with pasta and squeeze lemon over.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put bread crumbs in buttered 1-quart casserole dish.
Combine eggs, sugar, salt, cinnamon and vanilla. Gradually blend in milk. Pour over bread. Set bowl in pan of hot water and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mock sour cream
directions: Put ingredients in blender container; cover and run on high until completely smooth.
Makes 1 cup.

title: maryann sawyer's glogg(very alcoholic)
directions: Tie spices in a cheesecloth bag.
Simmer for 10 minutes in water.
Add almonds and raisins; simmer 10 minutes more.
Add remaining liquids; bring to boil and cool.
Store in refrigerator overnight (this step is essential).
Remove spice bag.
Heat, but don't boil.
Add sugar to taste (1 or 2 cups for those who like sweet drinks, 1/2 cup otherwise, but taste).
Serve in heated mugs (small amounts, as this is really potent) with a few raisins and almonds.

title: meat, cheese and tortilla casserole
directions: Combine meat, tomatoes, soup, beans and onion.
In a greased, deep dish casserole, layer meat mixture, cheese and tortillas, ending with layer of meat.
Reserve small amount of cheese to garnish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: thai style pumpkin soup
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large Dutch oven and bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Combine 1 c pumpkin mixture and peanut butter in a blender or food processor; process until smooth.
Return mixture to pan.
Stir in vinegar and next 5 ingredients (vinegar through garlic).
Cook 3 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Ladle into soup bowls and sprinkle with fresh cilantro.

title: turkey dressing
directions: On low fire, put Crisco in skillet.
Add raisins and chopped onion.
Mix well (watch so it doesn't burn).
Raisins must swell up.
Break bread, put in a large bowl.
Add water to wet it; mix. Drain bread in strainer.
Add chopped celery to bread.
Mix.
Add egg.
Mix.
Add raisin mix, salt and pepper.
Stuff turkey.
If dressing is leftover, put in greased casserole bowl.
Cover.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: hard candy
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup.
Place over low heat and stir constantly until it boils.
Put in candy thermometer and cook to 300°.
Remove from heat and add flavoring and coloring.
Pour into buttered pan and cut with buttered scissors.
Roll in bowl of powdered sugar.
Shake off excess powdered sugar.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream margarine and sugar and add pretzels and spread on bottom of baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inches).
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes. Cool completely.

title: iron skillet chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour in bowl and set aside.
Beat egg yolks and milk together in separate bowl.
In iron skillet, melt butter.
Add dry mixture.
Add eggs and milk mixture slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickens.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
This makes a small pie.

title: japanese cabbage salad
directions: Crush thoroughly the Top Ramen.
Brown the melted butter with sesame seed.
Set aside to cool.
Toss all together.
Add dressing.

title: garden vegetable pasta salad
directions: Cook all vegetables; drain.
Cook macaroni; drain.
Place on a platter.
Mix package of Italian dressing according to directions. Pour over pasta and vegetables.
Pour bottle of dressing over pasta and vegetables (according to taste).
Toss together. Serves many.

title: pickled beets
directions: Wash and cook beets in slightly salted water until skin slips off.
Save the water beets were cooked in.
Slip skins and slice beets.
Cover with solution of vinegar, sugar and 1 cup of water beets were cooked in.
Add mixed pickling spice to taste.
Makes enough to cover inch and simmer 20 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: spanish casserole
directions: Pour Mazola oil in a frying pan.
Add the garlic, onions and peppers.
Heat and add the meat rolled in the cornstarch.
Pour in the Karo and tomatoes.
Add salt and pepper and the grape juice. Transfer to a casserole.
Cover and bake 2 hours in a 350° oven. Add olives and serve with mashed potatoes.

title: irma's red bean special
directions: Saute onion, salt and pork chops in 1 teaspoon oil.
Add cans of red beans and 1 1/2 cans water.
(You may put as much water as you need to make gravy like you want it.) Let cook about 1/2 hour on medium heat, then add dash of garlic powder; stir it in beans. Cook rice.
Serve beans over the rice.
Add a vegetable, salad and cornbread and you are ready to eat!

title: assorted deviled eggs
directions: Peel and halve eggs lengthwise.
Remove yolk and mash thoroughly.
Blend with mayonnaise, butter, Dijon, onion, Worcestershire, salt and pepper.
Divide yolk mixture into four portions and blend one with capers, one with bacon, one with anchovies and one with Blue cheese.
Refill egg halves with fillings.
Chill before serving.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Measure dry ingredients and sift together.
Add alternately with pumpkin and vanilla.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour in Bundt pan or for 35 minutes in 9-inch pans.

title: thumbprint butter cookies
directions: Mix until pie crust consistency.
Roll in balls and dip in slightly beaten egg white.
Press thumb into center of cookies to make an indentation.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 15 minutes.
Fill indentation after baking with any kind of jelly.

title: butter pecan popcorn
directions: Discard unpopped popcorn kernels.
Spray a 17 x 12 x 2-inch roasting pan with nonstick coating.
Place the popped corn and pecans in the pan.
Keep popcorn warm in a 300° oven while making coating.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients and marinate chicken breasts overnight. Grill.

title: cucumber sour-cream salad
directions: Blend sugar, salt, sour cream, onion and vinegar.
Stir in cucumbers.
Chill at least
2 hours.
Serve in lettuce cups for salad or on the tray with other relishes.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour into large (15 x 24-inch) baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Spread with drained pineapple. Mix softened cream cheese, milk and pudding with egg beater or mixer.
Spread mixture over pineapple. Spread Cool Whip over all.
Sprinkle with coconut. Refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry creme salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in two cups boiling water.
Add 10 ounces frozen strawberries and stir until thawed.
Add crushed pineapple, drained and diced bananas.
Pour 1/2 mixture into 9 x 12-inch pan (metal or Pyrex) and chill until almost firm.
Then spread one cup sour cream on top, chill again.
Pour remainder of Jell-O mixture over sour cream and chill until firm (chilling process for first two layers can be hastened by putting in freezer).
Makes about 12 to 16 servings.

title: costatelle di maiale(pork chops)
directions: Marinate chops in vinegar, water and lemon juice for 2 hours in shallow pan.
Remove from pan and drain and dry.
Beat eggs lightly.
Mix garlic, bread, basil, parsley, cheese, salt and pepper.
Roll chops in flour, dip in eggs, then in bread crumb mixture.
Fry in hot oil for about 5 minutes on both sides or until brown.
Lower heat, cover pan and continue frying slowly for 20 minutes until tender.
Serves 4.

title: zesty italian supper
directions: Brown meat and drain. Add peppers, onion and garlic.
Cook until tender. Add tomato sauce and seasoning. Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Stir in Cheez Whiz until melted.
Add cooked pasta and toss thoroughly.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and butter or fat. Line pie pan with plain pastry.
Put in pecans in a layer.
Add mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
The nuts will rise to the top and form a crusted layer.

title: chicken pizza
directions: In a bowl mix chicken, mayonnaise, mustard,
pepper, 1 c. cheddar cheese and broccoli (if frozen thaw and drain well).
Put on top of pizza crust.
Bake at 425 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes. Top with remaining cheddar cheese.

title: mom's sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Blend sugar, cream and eggs.
Mix hot water and melted chocolate to form paste.
Add to sugar, cream and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients that have bene sifted together. Beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean, about 30 to 45 minutes.
I like to bake this in a tube pan.

title: "old timer's" chili sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Bring to boil and cook 2 hours on medium heat, stirring often to prevent sticking as it thickens. Makes 12 pints.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: apple pie filling
directions: In large saucepan stir first 4 ingredients.
Stir in 1 teaspoon salt and 10 cups of water.
Cook until thick and bubbly. Stir in lemon juice.
Pack sliced apples in jar and cover with syrup.
In hot water bath and can for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: chicken souffle(makes 10 servings)
directions: Butter one side of bread slices and remove crusts.
Cook, bone, skin and slice chicken breasts.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Line bottom with 8 slices bread.
Cover with sliced chicken. Spread chicken slices with mayo and sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese. Top with remaining 8 slices bread.
Beat together eggs, milk and salt.
Pour over entire casserole.
Refrigerate overnight or all day.

title: ambrosia cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix baking powder and salt with flour.
Add flour mixture and milk slowly.
Add vanilla.
Bake in three greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: marinade for venison
directions: Cover venison and refrigerate 1 to 3 days; turn.

title: macaroni and shrimp salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Clean and cook shrimp.
Cut up tomatoes and green pepper.
When macaroni is cooled, add shrimp and fresh vegetables.

title: baked cranberries
directions: Wash cranberries; drain. Place in 9 x 13 glass baking dish. Sprinkle sugar over berries. Cover with foil. Bake at 321° for 1 hour. Place nuts on foil last 10 minutes of baking to toast. After baking, stir in marmalade and nuts. Serve hot or cold.

title: texas cornbread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into lightly greased pan.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese dainties
directions: Mix together brown sugar, nuts and flour.
Stir in melted butter until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumb mixture.
Press into 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Beat cream cheese with sugar.
Beat in egg, lemon juice, milk and vanilla and blend well.
Pour on top of baked crust.
Top with reserved crumbs. Bake 25 minutes longer.
Cool and chill.
Cut into squares.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix.
Bake
at	300° for 1 hour or until firm.	Makes 2 pies.

title: nutty peach crisp
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Place undrained peaches in pan.
Put ingredients in pan in following order:
Sprinkle dry cake mix over peaches (do not mix in the dry cake mix), drizzle melted butter over dry cake mix and spread coconut on top of the butter.
Add nutmeats and bake 55 to 60 minutes in 325° oven.
Let stand at least 15 minutes before serving.
Serve warm or cold with Cool Whip or ice cream.
Makes 12 to 15 generous servings.

title: great russian borscht
directions: Saute the onions, mushrooms and ground beef with the butter in a large pot until browned.
Add the beef stock, Burgundy, thyme, chervil, pepper, garlic salt, bay leaf and Worcestershire.
Cover kettle and bring to a boil.
Add beets, cabbage, celery and carrots to kettle.
Bring to a boil for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and add corn syrup and catsup, stirring to mix well.
Serve hot garnished with sour cream and sprinkled with thyme or chervil. Freezes well and makes a lot.

title: spicy shrimp linguine
directions: In saucepan, heat olive oil over medium heat.
Add onion; cook until translucent, 5 minutes.
Stir in parsley, garlic, red pepper flakes, tomatoes with their juice, sugar, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat to low; cook 20 minutes or until sauce thickens, stirring occasionally.
Stir in shrimp; cook until shrimp turns pink, about 3 minutes.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain.
Saute onions in bacon grease. Drain beans thoroughly.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Stir brown sugar and catsup together.
Add onions and bacon grease. Mix together and pour over beans.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Bake for 2 hours, uncovered.

title: raw potato casserole
directions: Mix the ground meat with the tomato soup, salt and pepper. Work in the flour; form into meat balls about the size of golf balls.
Melt the butter in a skillet; brown the meat balls on all sides.
Place the meat balls on the bottom of a well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix the mushrooms, onion and raw potatoes very well; pour over the meat balls.
Cover with aluminum foil; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove the foil; continue to bake 15 minutes longer.
Serve piping hot.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift flour once; measure, add baking powder, soda and salt and sift again.
Cut in shortening; add milk gradually until soft dough is formed.
Turn on floured board and knead lightly, 2 minutes.
Roll to desired thickness; cut with floured cutter. Bake in shallow pan in hot oven at 450° for 12 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen biscuits.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix 10x sugar, butter and milk in saucepan.
Boil 4 1/2 minutes on medium heat.
Add peanut butter and marshmallow; beat rapidly.
Pour into pan and cool.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoonfuls into hot broth of any kind.
Cook, covered, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cookie dessert
directions: Mix ingredients as listed above.
Stir in crumbled cookies right before serving.

title: graham cracker crust(baked)
directions: Blend together and press in pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Cool before filling.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix vinegar, oil, salt and sugar until sugar dissolves (heat in microwave to melt sugar).
Slice onion and place on top of chopped cabbage.
Put celery seed in strainer.
Pour mixture over and stir.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: pineapple dream cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed.
Cool and slice layers to make 4 layers.
Combine pineapple, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until thick, stirring to prevent sticking.
Cool and add sour cream. Ice 3 layers with this mixture.
Put Cool Whip on top layer.

title: lime pie
directions: Beat well.
Put in baked crust or graham cracker crust.
Let chill before eating.

title: banana and strawberry shake
directions: Place the milk, banana, strawberries and date or fig in a blender.
Blend on medium for 10 seconds.
Add to oats and dry milk.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into a glass and top with a sprinkle of cinnamon.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Rinse broccoli under running cold water to thaw; drain thoroughly.
Mix broccoli and 2 cups cheese in plate.
Beat milk, eggs, Bisquick, salt and pepper until smooth, 1 minute with mixer.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake just until cheese is melted, 1 or 2 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: meat loaf
directions: Crumble hamburger and bread slices.
Chop onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spicy chicken and corn
directions: Put margarine in skillet; cook chicken until brown.
Cook onion and bell pepper with oregano, black pepper and paprika until tender-crisp.
Stir in soup, tomatoes and rice.
Heat to boiling. Return chicken to skillet.
Cover and cook over low heat for about 5 minutes or until chicken is done.
Makes four servings.

title: apple-raisin stuffed chicken breasts
directions: In saucepan over medium-high heat, heat chicken broth and 2 tablespoons of margarine until margarine melts.
Stir in stuffing mix, apples, raisins and pecans. Divide mixture evenly among 4 chicken pieces.
Roll up.
Secure with toothpicks.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Combine the flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool on a wire rack.
Spoon hot glaze over warm cake.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk on High in a 2-quart bowl for 2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute until smooth.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in a 9 x 5-inch pan.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Cut.

title: mushroom-rice soup
directions: Saute sliced mushrooms in melted butter in a skillet until tender (about 10 minutes).
Drain.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water; set aside.
Combine chicken broth, carrot, onion and celery in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Add rice; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add macaroni, parsley, bouillon and pepper; cook 10 minutes.
Stir in mushrooms and serve.
Yields 3 1/4 quarts.

title: italian fried cheese
directions: Dip cheese cubes in egg; cover with flour and dip again.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Place on wax paper and chill 1 hour.
Fry cheese cubes in deep, hot oil until golden brown.
Drain cubes on paper towels; serve immediately with sauce.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese over low flame; add chili.
Place in crock-pot and keep warm.
Serve on chips, crackers or vegetable pieces.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Mix lemon juice, cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk together. Add pecans and pour in crust. In separate bowl, combine cherry pie filling and sugar, then pour over cream cheese mixture. Chill for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: no cook pepper relish
directions: Chop this all up.
Put in dishpan.
Pour 1/2 cup plain salt over this; do not stir.
Let stand 4 hours.
Drain all water off. Mix 8 cups sugar and 8 cups vinegar cold; pour over vegetables. Mix up; put in jars.
Pressure cook at 5 pounds for 5 minutes.

title: baked idaho potato
directions: Bake potato in foil.
Before serving, cut the potato and slightly crumble meat.
Top with butter, sour cream and grated cheese.

title: no fry doughnuts
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk, sugar, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, eggs, shortening and 2 cups flour.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed.
Scrape bowl constantly.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Scrape bowl occasionally.
Stir in remaining flour.
Cover and let double in size, 50 to 60 minutes.
Turn dough onto well floured board.
Roll to about 1/2-inch thick; cut with 2 1/2-inch doughnut cutter.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Brush with melted butter.
Cover and let rise until double, 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 425°.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush again with butter and shake in cinnamon sugar.

title: potato soup
directions: Brown sausage and green onions. Drain off fat. Add celery and cook 2-3 minutes.
Add soups and chicken broth.
Cook until blended.
Add frozen hash browns and cook for about 1 hour.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put in crock pot for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot dressing for endive
directions: Mix the eggs, sugar and flour; beating well.
Add the vinegar and water.
Cook until desired thickness, about 5 to 7 minutes.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Place undrained pineapple in a blender container.
Cover and blend until finely chopped.

title: orange julius drink
directions: Place ingredients into blender.
Mix until frothy.

title: spanish rice
directions: In a frying pan; cook onion and green pepper in olive oil until tender.
Blend in rice, tomatoes and seasonings.
Cook slowly until thick.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: todd's mom's french salad dressing
directions: Throw it all in a food processor and mix it all up real good.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream peanut butter and margarine.
Add vanilla.
Gradually add powdered sugar and mix well.
Shape into balls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin wax in top of double boiler (about 10 minutes).
Dip peanut butter balls into chocolate mixture, using toothpicks.

title: vanilla torte
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together. Bake at 350° until brown.
Mix the vanilla pudding with the milk.
Refrigerate until set.
Add cherries on top.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix
cut-up
strawberries
and	glaze;	set aside.
Mix cream cheese,
condensed milk, Cool Whip and lemon juice until smooth. Layer
vanilla wafers, strawberries and filling until everything is used up.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix sugar and flour together in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add in drained pineapple and mix together.
Sprinkle with grated cheese. Sprinkle with crushed Ritz crackers and pour melted butter or margarine over top.
Bake until golden brown at 350°.

title: texas chili meat loaf
directions: Drain kidney beans; reserve liquid.
Stir together beans, oats, onion, green pepper, tomatoes and egg.
Add chili powder, garlic salt and red pepper sauce; mix well.
Add ground beef and 3/4 cup Cheddar cheese.
Pat mixture into a meat loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Pour reserved liquid over meat loaf.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup Cheddar cheese and corn chips.
Return to oven for an additional 10 minutes.

title: get well soon carrot custard
directions: Cover carrots with water (can use chicken stock to add flavor).
Slowly boil 20 to 25 minutes.
Puree carrots with butter and margarine until smooth.
Add other ingredients; puree 30 seconds or until smooth.
Preheat oven to 375° and grease a 9-inch round cake pan.
Scrape puree into the greased pan.
Boil water. Put 9-inch pan into a larger pan and put boiling water into larger pan, halfway up sides of smaller pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until custard is firm.
Remove; let sit 15 minutes.
Loosen edges and invert pan on plate.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Layer first 8 ingredients in baking dish (one 8 x 5-inch and one 13 x 9-inch).
This recipe makes both.
(May half recipe, if desired.)
Mix mushroom soup, celery soup, tomato soup and water. Pour over layered dishes.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Turn down to 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Top with grated American cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large pot.
Simmer.
Do not cook on high, will burn.

title: ritz fried shrimp
directions: Combine egg, milk and pancake mix as you would prepare for pancakes.
Crush about 3 or 4 cups of Ritz crackers in food processor and place in a separate bowl.
One at a time, dip shrimp into pancake mix, then roll shrimp into cracker crumbs.
Place on tray.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Make sure that both the chicken and yogurt are very cold (soak the chicken in ice cubes).

title: green rice(makes 10 servings)
directions: Mix rice, parsley, cheese, onion, green pepper and garlic in greased 2-quart casserole. Blend rest of ingredients; mix into rice. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until like a soft custard.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Blend in vanilla and chocolate. Sift flour with soda and salt. Add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture, beating after each addition until smooth. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into three 9-inch layer pans, lined on bottoms with waxed paper. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Frost tops only with coconut-pecan frosting.

title: chicken pasta primavera
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain.
Combine pasta and 1/2 cup salad dressing, tossing to coat; cover and chill for 3 hours.
Combine chicken, remaining 1 cup salad dressing and remaining ingredients except tomatoes, tossing well.
Cover and chill 3 hours.
When ready to serve, combine pasta mixture, chicken mixture and cherry tomatoes, tossing well.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water and salt.
Cook until clear.
Add jello and gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Pour over berries in a baked crust.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients together, adding milk until batter consistency.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Melt butter.
Add garlic; saute 2 minutes.
Stir in broth and tortellini.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Add grated cheese, salt and pepper; simmer until tortellini are tender (about 5 minutes).
Add tomatoes, spinach and cut up fresh basil leaves. Simmer until heated through.

title: french toast
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Dip bread in mixture, coating both sides.
Melt butter in frying pan.
Fry slices until brown. Serve with syrup.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl stir and let stand the 1 cup water and the brown sugar or molasses and honey.
In a small bowl sprinkle the yeast over the 1 cup warm water and the 2 tablespoons of honey. Add to the first mixture and beat well the 3 cups warm water, salt, white flour and the yeast mixture.
Stir in, then knead on floured surface, whole wheat flour and (optional) 1 cup cracked wheat. Cover, then let rise in a warm place until double in size.
Punch down.
Shape into loaves and place in greased bread pans.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 loaves.

title: banana crush punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water and juice.
Mash bananas and stir into the preceding juice mixture.
Pour into large container and freeze until ready to serve.
(Will freeze for months.)

title: bolavian coconut cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
In a saucepan, mix sugar and flour; add milk and vanilla and cook until custard is medium thickness.
Fold gelatin (that has been dissolved in the water) and beaten egg whites.
Slice angel food cake about 1/4-inch thick and line bottom of large Pyrex.
Pour custard over cake.
Repeat until dish is full.
Set in refrigerator overnight. Cover top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Arrange cherries on top to center each square.
Score into squares.

title: really delicious turkey or chicken dressing
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Bake in greased pan until brown. In a large bowl, tear up bread; add onions, celery, eggs, pepper and margarine.
Mix well.
Add
hot corn bread which has been crumbled.
Mix well.
Add broth.
Bake at 350° until brown. Remove from oven; pour turkey or chicken broth over dressing and return to oven for a few minutes.

title: herbed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender.
Meanwhile, thoroughly blend cream cheese, 1/4 c. milk, chives and lemon juice and set aside.
When potatoes are done, drain well.
Mash with mixer on lowest speed.
Add remaining milk, butter, garlic salt and pepper.
Blend in cream cheese mixture.
Pour into casserole dish and garnish with additional chives and butter.
Microwave 5 to 10 minutes if serving immediately.
You may cover with foil and freeze up to 4 weeks.
Reheat at 350° for 1 hour.

title: room scent
directions: Dig a big hole in garden of your thoughts.
Into it put all your disillusions, disappointments, regrets, worries, troubles, doubts and fears and forget.
Cover well with the earth of fruitfulness.
Water it from the well of content.
Sow on top the seeds of hope, courage, strength, patience and love.

title: cheese balls
directions: Cook rice to equal 2 cups.
While rice is hot, stir in Cheddar cheese.
Make into small balls.
Roll in bread crumbs lightly. Drop in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain and serve.
The kids love it!

title: paella
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces and fry in butter.
Add rice after chicken is fried and stir for approximately 3 minutes.
Add chicken broth.
Chop onion and ham into small pieces, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix together and cook on stove range over low heat.
Cover and stir occasionally until cooked.
(Do not add any salt!)

title: tempting turkey casserole
directions: Melt and combine Cheez Whiz with milk in microwave.
Toss spaghetti with margarine.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Spoon into a 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Stir before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onions.
Add with other ingredients to crock-pot.
Cook 4 to 6 hours.
If meat is raw, cook 8 to 10 hours.

title: coffee cake gems
directions: Cream 1/2 cup sugar and shortening; add egg, vanilla and salt. Beat well.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour, baking powder and milk; mix well.
Pour into well-greased muffin tins.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly; sprinkle over muffins.
Bake at 375° until well done.

title: skillet hamburgers
directions: Shape ground round into 4 patties; place on wax paper. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place patties in medium-hot skillet.
Sear 3 minutes on both sides.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes. Transfer to platter.
Add onions to drippings; stir 30 seconds. Add flour, soy sauce and water; stir.
Add any juices from platter.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes until thick.
Spoon over patties.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat until smooth.
Dip fruit or use as topping for pie.

title: spam casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a greased 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange a layer of potatoes and a layer of Spam (chopped or cubed). Layer until all are used. Sprinkle on Cheddar cheese. Mix spices with the mushroom soup and spoon over the top. Cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: boneless chicken wrap
directions: Wrap chicken with bacon and dried beef.
Mix sour cream, soup and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone and chop.
Mix together all ingredients and combine with chopped chicken.
Crush 1 package of Ritz crackers; add this to 1 stick melted butter.
Put this on top of casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cream pralines
directions: Mix sugar, salt, oil and milk in medium-sized heavy pot. Stir with a wooden spoon over low heat until sugar is dissolved.

Add pecans and cook over medium heat to soft ball stage or 234°. Turn off heat and let cool for 5 minutes. Beat with wooden spoon until mixture begins to thicken and coat nuts slightly. Rapidly drop from a spoon to form patties. Makes 90.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla and beaten egg.
Beat well.
Sift flour with spices and soda, then add to cream mixture alternately with applesauce.
Add nuts and dates.
Bake in loaf pan or tube pan 1 1/4 hours at 350° or until done when tested.

title: mandarin rice pudding
directions: In medium saucepan, combine milk and rice.
Bring to boiling. Reduce heat; cook, covered, over low heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Uncover; cook the rice mixture for 5 minutes more.

title: baked glazed ham
directions: Mix together all but ham. Pour ingredients over ham and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours. Line pan with foil. Put 1-inch water in roaster under foil.

title: home cookin' spinach cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into a greased 10-inch square Pyrex dish.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in preheated 400° oven. (Makes a thick, cake-like bread, great with soups.)

title: savory baked fish
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Prepare Savory Crunch.
Arrange onion rings in ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch ungreased square baking dish. Drizzle with margarine.
Arrange fish on onions; drizzle with lemon juice.
Sprinkle Savory Crunch evenly over fish.
Bake, uncovered, until fish flakes easily with fork, about 30 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in baking dish.
Pour orange juice over apples. Combine remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 4.

title: low-fat corn bread muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 375° for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: overnight cabbage slaw
directions: Shred all vegetables.
Mix vinegar, vegetable oil, sugar, salt and pepper; pour over vegetables.
Stir to combine.
Cover; refrigerate 8 hours before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Mix water, sugar, pickling spice, vinegar and salt.
Boil for several minutes.
Put some dill in the bottom of each jar.
Pack cleaned cucumbers in the jars.
Put one slice of garlic in each jar and put some dill on top of cucumbers.
Pour boiling brine over the cucumbers and seal jars.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix first four ingredients until moist.
Add poppy seed and water.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in 10-inch tubepan, 50 to 55 minutes in 3 loaf pans or 45 to 50 minutes in 4 to 5 mini pans.

title: chicken italiano
directions: Combine all dried ingredients.
Dip chicken in butter, then in dry mixture.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until tender.

title: pumpkin or zucchini cake
directions: Mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry apple drink
directions: Pour over cracked ice.
Each serving contains 55 calories.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins, slice; dice bacon and fry until brown and crispy.
Remove; drain on paper towels.
Saute onion in bacon grease, stir flour into onion mixture.
Gradually add vinegar, water, salt and pepper; stir constantly to thicken.
Add bitters, cook until smooth and glossy.
Add potatoes; heat through.
Add bacon bits.
Garnish with parsley.
Serve warm.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening, sugar and salt together with a fork. Combine mixtures.
Chill for 15 minutes.
Makes 2 double 9-inch pie shells.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cook carrots, drain and mash, about 1 cup.
Cool.
Cream butter, sugar, egg and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Stir in carrots.
Stir together dry ingredients.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 12 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: chicken tortillas
directions: Mix chicken, onions, sour cream and 1 can of mushroom soup. Place mixture in tortillas and roll up.
Place in baking dish and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix salsa and other can of cream of mushroom soup.
Pour over tortillas.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Bake another 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: italian chicken breasts
directions: Pound chicken until 1/2-inch thick.
Dip in egg white and roll in crumbs.
Saute in oil about 3 minutes per side until done.

title: *date-nut balls
directions: Combine butter, sugar and dates in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cook, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes.
Stir in cereal and pecans.
Cool to the touch.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll each in coconut or powdered sugar.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Grind the shrimp.
Mix with cream cheese that has been blended with enough mayonnaise to make soft.
Add other ingredients. Serve with Fritos or your favorite crackers.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix butter or oleo, sugar, cocoa, milk, salt and vanilla. Bring to boil 3 to 5 minutes.
Add oats, peanut butter and pecans. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: veggie chili
directions: In large pot, saute onion and garlic in olive oil until soft. Mix in next 4 seasonings.
Stir in zucchini and carrots until well blended.
Cook 1 minute over low heat, stirring occasionally. Stir in chopped tomatoes and kidney beans.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes or until thick.
Top with garnish. Serves 8.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix ingredients and chill for at least 2 hours.

title: apricot bread
directions: Pour boiling water over chopped apricots and soda.
Let stand until cool.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add beaten egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add apricot mixture and nuts.
Mix and bake in greased bread tins.
Bake at 350°.
Baking time will depend on the size tin used.

title: cellophane pickles
directions: Wash and slice thin the cucumbers.
Soak 24 hours in salt water (1/2 cup salt to 1 quart water), then drain.
Cover with fresh water for 24 hours, then drain.
Simmer in weak vinegar water with 2 tablespoons alum for 3 hours.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Place meat in slow-cooking pot; cover with sliced onion. Combine garlic, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, salt, paprika and mustard.
Cover and cook on low for 9 to 10 hours. Turn control to high.
Dissolve flour in small amount of cold water.
Stir into meat mixture.
Cook on high 10 to 15 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Put corn in buttered casserole.
Add beaten eggs to corn.
Add margarine, crackers, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat butter over low heat until melted.
Stir in flour, onions, soup base, salt and pepper until smooth. Add water and milk, stirring constantly.
Heat to boiling and boil 1 minute while stirring. Stir in chicken and frozen vegetables. Set aside. I usually add 2 to 3 cooked and diced potatoes, also.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Grind oranges, apple and cranberries together.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Soak gelatin in cold water; add to jello.
Add sugar, lemon juice and other ingredients.
Mold.

title: orange refrigerator salad
directions: Mix ingredients and store in refrigerator.

title: plum bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients, then add remainder.
Put into 2 (1 pound) coffee cans or two loaf tins, greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pepper relish
directions: Boil this for 5 minutes.
Add to peppers and onions; heat to boiling.
Seal in sterilized jars.
Yields approximately 3 pints.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground chuck in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Add garlic, seasoned salt and pepper.
Simmer for 10 minutes; drain. Add tomatoes and tomato sauce; mix well.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Reserve 1/3 meat sauce.
Layer remaining meat sauce, noodles, Mozzarella cheese and cottage cheese, 1/2 at a time in 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Top with reserved meat sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: porcupine-meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, rice, milk, minced onion, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Mix lightly, but well.
Drop rounded tablespoonful of mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Grease and flour a 13 X9 pan. Mix sugar, oleo, vanilla and egg. Stir in dry ingredients. Mix in nuts and chips. Spread in pan. Bake at 375 degrees for 12-14 minutes or until golden brown.

title: gazpacho style shrimp
directions: In large saucepan, combine water and salt.
Bring to boil. Add shrimp.
Simmer 1 to 3 minutes; drain.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook beef, onion and pepper.
Drain.
Add the rest of the ingredients except cheese.
Microwave 15 to 17 minutes on High, covered.
Stir 2 to 3 times during cooking time.
Top with cheese; cover.
Let stand 3 to 5 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery and grapes in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add mayonnaise and sour cream; mix thoroughly.
Chill.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Grease 9 x 13 pan well. Sprinkle cheese on bottom of pan, then the onion bits. In bowl, beat eggs, milk and seasoning. Pour over the cheese and onion bits. Bake at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes. Be sure the center is done.

title: cream of peanut soup(a smooth and creamy peanut butter soup)
directions: Melt
butter
in
large
saucepan
over
low heat.
Add celery and
onion.
Cook
until
tender
but not browned.	Add flour and stir until mixture is smooth.
Gradually add chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Blend in peanut butter and simmer 15 minutes. Stir
in
cream, salt and pepper.
Heat and serve in soup bowls. Garnish with paprika.
Yields 8 servings.

title: no bake marshmallow bars
directions: Combine chocolate chips, margarine and peanut butter in heavy saucepan.
Put on low heat and melt.
Cool partly so marshmallows don't melt.
Add marshmallows and stir until all are covered.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan or cookie sheet and place in refrigerator.
When cold, cut into bars and store in refrigerator or cool place.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add the egg (beaten), sour cream and milk.
Beat well and bake in shallow pans in a hot oven at 450° for about 1/2 hour.

title: mother's blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add eggs, one at a time, to butter and sugar mixture.
Blend flour and spices.
Add alternately with milk to butter and sugar mixture. Add vanilla, jam, raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Batter will be thick.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Roll out each biscuit until flat and large enough for pie. These will need to be rolled in flour before rolling.
Mix sugar and spice together in bowl large enough to put fried pie in; coat each side of pie.
Fry pies in hot melted shortening; immediately coat with sugar mixture.
Each pie will hold approximately 2 tablespoons applesauce.

title: nancy welch's clam chowder
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Heat until piping hot and serve.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Put pie filling in 9 X 9 baking dish.
Mix other ingredients to form crumbly mixture.
Sprinkle over cherry pie filling.
Bake at 400 for 25 minutes or until top is crisp and golden brown.

title: blt salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let blend in refrigerator at least 1 hour prior to serving.
Mix in lettuce or serve dressing on side.
Top salad with bagel chips.

title: blue cheese meat balls
directions: Combine beef, cheese, salt, garlic, bread crumbs, oregano, rosemary, parsley and 1/2 cup of the dry white wine; mix well. Shape mixture into small balls.
Brown well in heated oil; drain on Scott towel.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 325° for about 10 minutes until lightly browned.
(Don't let them get very brown or they will taste burned.)
Roll in powdered sugar while they are still warm.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar. Add eggs and beat well. Add baby food. Sift together flour and cinnamon and gradually add to wet ingredients. Bake in tube pan at 350° until done. Top with frosting.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti according to package.
Cook off hamburger, season to taste.
Add the rest of the ingredients, stir thoroughly.
Stuff noodles, put in pan, cover with your favorite prepared spaghetti sauce or your own.
Cover with about 2 more cups of cheese, more or less to your own taste.
Serves 7.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375° (quick moderate).
Mix shortening, sugar, egg and flavorings thoroughly.
Measure flour by dipping method or sifting.
Mix flour and salt; stir into shortening mixture.
Divide dough in half.
Blend red food coloring into one half.
Roll a 4-inch strip (using 1 teaspoon dough) of each color.
For smooth, even strips, roll them back and forth on lightly floured board. Place strips side by side; press lightly together and twist like rope.
For best results, complete cookies one at a time.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Curve top to form handle of cane.
Bake about 9 minutes until lightly browned.
While still warm, sprinkle with mixture of peppermint candy and sugar.
Makes about 4 dozen candy canes.

title: pineapple glazed cake
directions: Bake cake in oblong pan as directed.
Combine crushed pineapple with 1/2 cup brown sugar (packed).
Bring to boil.
With point of sharp knife, mark cake into 1-inch squares, cutting 1/2-inch deep.
Spoon hot pineapple mixture over hot cake.
Allow to cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and mix with 1/3 cup softened (melted) oleo.
Press into 9 x 13-inch dish and freeze.
Spread softened ice cream over crust and freeze again.

title: company chicken salad
directions: Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seed and alum until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over cucumbers.
Put in jug and keep refrigerated. You may add peppers and squash, if desired.

title: asparagus puffs
directions: Blend together cheeses, mayonnaise and egg.
Cut crust off bread and roll thin.
Spread with cheese mixture.
Top with 1 stalk asparagus each.
Roll up and cut in 3 pieces.
Dip in melted butter.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes (until browned).
May be frozen unbaked.

title: rizzi aspro, greek rice
directions: Wash rice in very hot water; drain and let dry for half an hour to one hour.
Heat oil or margarine and fry rice in it, turning constantly, until rice is golden.
Add onion and saute just for a minute or two.
Add chicken stock, salt and pepper; bring to boil, then turn heat on low.
Cover and simmer until all liquid is absorbed and rice is done.
Add a little more water if necessary.

title: homestyle bread bowls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Cut shortening into flour, baking powder and salt with pastry blender in large bowl until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in yeast mixture and just enough buttermilk until dough leaves side of bowl and forms a ball.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface, gently roll in flour to coat.
Knead about 1 minute until smooth.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Grease outsides of 6 (10 ounce) custard cups.
Place cups upside down on ungreased jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 x 1-inch.

title: pecan pie
directions: Unfold and stack pie crusts one on top of the other.
Gently roll or press together.
Fit into 9-inch pie plate; fold edges under and crimp.
Stir together eggs, sugar, corn syrup, butter, vanilla and salt.
Add pecans.
Pour into pie crusts.
Bake at 350 degrees for 55 minutes or until set.
Serve warm or cold.

title: cherry almond cake
directions: Spread cherry pie filling in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Sprinkle dry powder cake mix over top of cherries.
Melt margarine and pour over dry cake mix.
Sprinkle almonds over melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour, until almonds are golden brown.

title: corn and green chili casserole
directions: Mix corn, cream cheese, garlic, milk and butter in a saucepan. Cook until cheese is melted and starts to bubble.
Add chilies and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Add grated Cheddar cheese and Doritos.
Bake at 350° just until bubbly.

title: cranberry juice sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and allspice in small saucepan.
Stir in cranberry juice and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in raisins.
Serve sauce hot with ham or pork.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg white until it stands in soft peaks.
Gradually beat in brown sugar and vanilla.
Fold in pecan halves.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Turn off oven and let pecans sit in oven for 30 more minutes.
Do not open oven until after 30 minutes.
Store in airtight container.
These also freeze well.

title: 15-minute beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into thin short strips and cook in oil quickly.
Add water and mushrooms (including the liquid); stir in soup mix and heat to a boil.
Turn heat down and simmer a minute or two while you blend sour cream and flour.
Add to mixture, cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Serve over hot cooked egg noodles.
Makes 5-6 servings.

title: impossible cookies
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° until done.

title: butternut squash
directions: Blend well.
Spoon lightly into a lightly-buttered greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven approximately 1 hour or until firm in center.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Mix well white and powdered sugars, butter, oil and eggs.
Mix well vanilla, salt, cream of tartar, baking soda and flour.
Blend all ingredients together and then chill.
With floured hands, shape into balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with the bottom of a chilled glass dipped in sugar.
Sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake at 350° in oven for about 15 minutes or until edges are slightly browned.
Do not overbake.
Makes good Christmas cookies and they freeze well.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix together cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Stir in fruit cocktail.
