Add jello. Serve and enjoy.
Cover and refrigerate any leftover.

title: pork chop marinade(fulton county fair butterfly pork chop)
directions: Mix all together and marinate pork chops overnight or at least 6 hours.

title: vanilla texas sheet cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and set aside. Bring to a boil the margarine, water and 4 tablespoons flour.

Pour this over the first mixture and mix well. Beat in the sour cream, baking soda and eggs. Bake on a large cookie sheet (sprayed with Pam) at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool cake and top with the following ingredients which have been beaten smooth.
Bring to a boil the margarine. Add the 4 tablespoons flour and milk.
Beat until smooth,
then add vanilla and 10x sugar.

title: chicken delight
directions: Place stick of margarine in a baking pan and place in oven until margarine is melted.
Pour rice over melted margarine evenly.
Season chicken and place chicken on top of rice.
Mix together water and Lipton onion soup mix; pour over chicken.
Cook at 350°, uncovered, for 15 minutes, then cover with foil and cook another 45 minutes.
Can use beef stew.

title: grape and blueberry salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and congeal. Best overnight.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on top.

title: watermelon rind preserves
directions: Trim green skin and red flesh from thick rind.
Cut into 1-inch cubes.
Cover with water.
Boil until fork-tender.
Drain. Add sugar to 7 cups water.
Boil 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add rind to syrup.
Boil 30 minutes.
Add lemon, thinly slices.
Continue cooking until rind is clear.
Pack into hot jars.
Process pints and quarts 20 minutes at simmering (180° to 185°) in hot water bath.

title: gingerbread boys
directions: Raisins for eyes, chocolate chips for buttons.

title: deep sea delight
directions: Mix all together.
Top with French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a large 9 x 13-inch glass casserole.
Top with 1/4 cup margarine, melted and tossed with 2 cups corn flakes.
Bake at 325° until hot through.
Brown at a higher temperature for eye appeal.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mix jello with bananas, pineapple and strawberries.
Pour half into dish and congeal. Crumble cream cheese into Cool Whip.
Whip until fluffy.
Put this on top of congealed mixture.
Pour other half on top and congeal.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and milk; mix well.
Blend in flour and baking powder.
Stir in berries.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Pour mixture into pan and bake at 375° for 40 minutes, or until done.
Top with frosting or powdered sugar if desired.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift all ingredients and mix.
Combine eggs and cream-style corn and the cup of liquid.
Add together with dry ingredients. Mix until flour is moistened.
Drop from full teaspoons in deep, hot fat at 375°.
Fry until golden brown, about 3 minutes.
Makes about 18.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve with vegetables or syrup and sausage.

title: pea salad
directions: Layer lettuce, frozen peas, water chestnuts, onion and celery in a large bowl.
Cover completely with mayonnaise, sealing to the edges.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry "pizza"
directions: Spread cookie batter out on large round pizza pan.
Bake according to directions.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese, Cool Whip and confectioners sugar with hand mixer until smooth.
Smooth this mixture onto cookie crust.
Prepare strawberries (or other fresh fruit).
Mix glaze into strawberries.
Top off the "pizza" with a layer of this strawberry-and-glaze mixture.
Keep refrigerated.

title: fresh fruit pizza
directions: Mix all ingredients; press into a 12-inch pizza pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until crust begins to brown.
Allow to cool.

title: fruit punch
directions: Makes 160 (4 ounce size) servings.

title: strawberry preserves muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Combine liquids and add all at once. Stir only until dry ingredients are moistened but not smooth. Fold in the strawberry preserves.
Do not beat.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full and bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: muffins
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. In a small bowl, beat egg, milk and oil with a fork.
Add egg mixture into the flour mixture.
Stir just until flour is moistened.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Put vanilla wafers in cupcake pan with baking cup cake papers inside.
Mix together ingredients and put over vanilla wafers. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool 1/2 hour and put pie filling over top (cherry).

title: pumpkin cupcakes
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add beaten egg and pumpkin.
Sift soda, baking powder and flour together.
Add vanilla, dates and nuts.
Fill muffin tins 1/2 to 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes in 325° oven.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: sonia's muddy hens
directions: Cream butter and add white sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Add vanilla and blend.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Cover with topping made by beaten egg white and brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.
Serve while warm.

title: date nut bread no. 2
directions: Mix nuts, dates, baking soda and salt.
Add shortening and boiling water.
Let stand 20 minutes, then add beaten eggs, vanilla, sugar and flour.
Grease and flour loaf pans or use Pam. Bake in 350° oven 1 hour.

title: "cooling salad"
directions: Mix all together and chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Can be served on lettuce leaf.

title: oven barbecued potatoes
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups of cheese, soup, milk, barbecue sauce, oregano, salt and pepper; blend thoroughly.
Add potato slices; toss until well coated.
Spoon mixture into a greased 9-inch square pan, cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil.
Bake about 30 minutes longer or until tender.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and paprika on top.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: sweet-sour meatballs
directions: Mix top 5 ingredients; make small meatballs and roll in flour. Fry in 1/4 cup oil.

title: italian meatball soup
directions: In large soup kettle or pot, combine chicken, onion, carrot and celery.
Cover with cold water and bring to boil.
Season with salt and pepper to taste; simmer 2 hours or until stock is reduced and chicken is very tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles until done.
Mix all ingredients and cook in a casserole dish at 350° for 40 minutes (until bubbly).
Top with grated cheese.

title: barbecue
directions: Trim fat from meat.
Cook all together on simmer 6 to 8 hours. Can be frozen.
Serve on buns.

title: chicken delight
directions: Cut chicken in serving pieces.
Place in cake pan, skin side up (can be skinned).
Sprinkle the onion soup mix over all.
Put a generous dollop of apricot
preserves
on each piece.
Pour Russian dressing on all.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add mashed bananas and pecans. Add eggs and mix well.
Then add flour.
Add milk and vanilla. Pour in greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour to 1 hour 10 minutes at 325°.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Steam broccoli, celery and onion in water in a 3-quart saucepan until tender.
Dissolve flour in milk in measuring cup.
Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a scald.
Garnish with a few almonds, if desired.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Blend one-third sugar and peanut butter.
Alternately add remaining sugar and milk.
Add vanilla.
Yield: frosting for two (2)
9-inch round layers.

title: caramel icing - mom's recipe
directions: Combine sugar and buttermilk in an iron fryer and cook until soft ball forms when dropped in cold water.
Add soda and stir until it gets brown.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Beat until margarine has melted.
Quickly spread on cake.
It will harden quickly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken tenders. Tear the pieces apart when done into smaller pieces. In a bowl, mix the chicken pieces, green chili peppers and mushroom soup together. Layer in a casserole dish the Doritos and cheese on chicken mixture. Continue layering. Make sure cheese is on top. Place in oven to melt all of the cheese.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts like pie dough.
Spread in pie pan and bake 15 minutes at 375° or until brown.
Let cool slightly.

title: seaside candy roll
directions: Chop 1/2 cup nuts finely and 1/2 c. coarsely.
Mix together margarine, syrup, maple flavoring and salt. Add sugar all at once. Mix thoroughly.
Knead in finely chopped nuts. Shape into two rolls. Brush with syrup and roll in coarsely chopped nuts.
Wrap, chill, slice and serve.

title: butterfinger pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add graham cracker crumbs.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer crust with crushed candy bars.
(Reserve some for top.)
Put pudding, then Cool Whip on top of crust and candy. Put remaining candy on top of Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brush bottom of crust and sides evenly with egg yolk.
Bake on a baking sheet about 5 minutes until lightly brown.
Remove from oven.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Combine apples, lemon juice, 2/3 cup sugar, 1/3 cup brown sugar, 1/4 cup flour, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Spoon into crust. Mix remaining flour, sugar, brown sugar and butter with fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle streusel mixture over apples.
Bake on baking sheet until streusel is golden and filling bubbles, about 55 minutes.

title: choereg
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix lukewarm milk, melted butter, beaten eggs and yeast.
Add salt and sugar.
Blend in flour to make a soft dough. Let stand until it doubles in size.

title: moist coconut cake
directions: Bake cake by package directions in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Punch holes in cake when cool.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over the top of cake.
Add 1 small can Baker's coconut.

title: creamy chicken breasts
directions: Cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with chicken breasts.
Mix sour cream, soup and sherry together in separate bowl.
Pour evenly over chicken.
Spread onion on top of mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika, parsley and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 4 to 6.

title: no sugar cookies
directions: Boil raisins and dates in 1 cup of water.
Add oleo; cool slightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: curried chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Put rice on bottom of long Pyrex dish. Cube chicken (place on top of rice).
Combine remaining ingredients and pour on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix cottage cheese, muffin mix and broccoli; add eggs and butter.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Blend; add honey and oil, then poppy seed.
Refrigerate.

title: shoe-peg salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Italian dressing.
Add the Italian dressing and mix together well.

title: blakies cheese balls
directions: Mix all cheeses, onion flakes, garlic salt, and dried parsley flakes.
Form into 2 balls and roll in chopped pecans.

title: pickled okra
directions: Pack in 5 pint jars small tender okra, 1 garlic clove and 1 pod hot pepper.
Place remaining ingredients in heavy saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over okra.
Seal.
Process in hot water bath for 10 minutes.
Let stand for 2 weeks before opening.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add egg and pineapple.
Add vanilla.
Mix flour, salt, baking powder and soda; mix.
Then add nuts.
Drop on oiled cookie sheet by teaspoonful.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: crunchy veggies
directions: Mix all and place in baking dish. Top with mixture of 1/2 cup melted margarine and 1 1/2 cups of crushed cheese and some sliced almonds. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fire company barbecue
directions: Brown hamburg and onions.
Add remaining ingredients to meat and onions; simmer about 30 minutes or longer.

title: "sis' swiss cheddar chicken"
directions: Bread and fry chicken cutlets 2 minutes on each side (cut cutlets in half).
In saucepan, melt butter; blend in flour.
Add salt, pepper and milk until bubbly and thick.
Remove from heat. Stir in wine.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Break up lettuce and cauliflower.
Layer all the items in the order given.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Mix in sugar, flour and oil.
Will be stiff.
Add squash, nuts, spices, baking powder and soda.
Then it will soften some.
Put in two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: creamy chicken and vegetable chowder
directions: Combine chicken, soups, undrained mushrooms, undrained green chilies, corn, milk, chicken broth and green onions in heavy saucepan; mix well.
Cook over medium heat for 5 to 8 minutes, or until heated through; remove from heat.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Serve immediately.

title: taboulli salad
directions: Pour boiling water over cracked wheat in bowl.
Let stand for 1 hour. Drain well into colander.
Return to bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill for 2 hours or longer.
Serve on lettuce-lined salad plates.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: shake and bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a fork in a large bowl. Store in a container with tight fitting lid, preferably in the refrigerator. Use to coat chicken,fish, or pork.
Moisten the meat or fish with water or milk before coating.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes depending on thickness.

title: macaroon fudgies
directions: In large saucepan over low heat, melt the chocolate and butter.
Remove from heat and add sugar, flour, salt, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well.
Spread half of batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Reserve remaining batter.
In a medium bowl, combine coconut, milk, vanilla and almond extract.
Mix well and spread evenly over chocolate batter.
Spread remaining chocolate batter evenly over coconut filling.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate pieces over hot bars and let stand one minute.
Spread evenly over bars.

title: sausage strudel
directions: Remove sausage from casing; scramble and brown.
Drain fat. Chop mushrooms very fine; saute in 1/4 cup butter until all liquid has evaporated.
Add shallots.
Prepare filo dough according to directions.
Use 2 sheets filo each buttered and bread crumbled. Spread sausage, mushrooms and pieces of cream cheese over 2/3 of the length of dough.
Roll up with empty dough end on top.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned (35 minutes).
Cut 8 pieces per roll for appetizer or 4 per roll for lunch.
Makes 2 rolls.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain grease.
Add soups and green chilies.
Pour picante sauce into empty green chilie can and add to beef.
Stir to mix completely.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix at low speed until dough forms. Shape into balls using a rounded teaspoonfuls.
Roll balls in sugar on a plate.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.
When cookies are light brown, remove from oven and immediately press a candy kiss in the center of each cookie.
Press down firmly so cookie cracks around edge.
Cool.

title: ranch rice
directions: Place all ingredients in a large pan with cover.
Stir, cover and place in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
All ingredients, except margarine, can be increased to create larger recipe.

title: new orleans pecan pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Cook until thick on medium for 5 minutes.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites.
Gradually add the brown sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Put on top of pie.
Add pecans. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Cream 1/2 cup
butter and Oreos together; pat into an 8 x 8-inch and a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
Melt chips and 1/2 cup butter together.
Gradually add milk and powdered sugar, stirring constantly.
Boil for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Place ice cream on top of cookie base.
Pour hot chocolate sauce over ice cream.
Top with chopped nuts.
Freeze.

title: angel hash
directions: Drain fruit and set juice aside.
Combine cornstarch, sugar, eggs and 1 cup reserved juice in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Cool to room temperature.
Fold in whipped cream and marshmallows.
Add drained fruit.
Fold until well mixed.
Chill in refrigerator overnight. Add bananas before serving.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
May saut an onion in hamburger, if desired.
Mix in cream of mushroom soup.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place meat mixture in pie plate.
Makes mashed potatoes and ice the meat mixture with mashed potatoes.
Grate Cheddar cheese on top of pie and bake until cheese is melted.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until crisp-tender, but still dark green (about 5 minutes).
Drain and place in bottom of Pam-sprayed 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Spread boned chicken over this.

title: bake while you sleep cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy; gradually add sugar and cream of tartar.
Continue beating until stiff.
Add salt, vanilla, chips and nuts.
Mix together well.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop dough on ungreased foil topped cookie sheet by teaspoon.
Place cookies in oven (2 cookie sheets on 2 levels) and immediately turn oven off. Leave cookies in closed oven overnight.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: pecan chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix sugar and flour; add melted butter and stir with a fork or wire whisk.
Add egg, milk and vanilla. Pour in uncooked pastry and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add cocoa. Add flour and milk alternately.
Cook in tube pan well greased and floured at 325°.
Check after 1 hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into 1/4 pieces.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture and place in greased Bundt pan.
Bake about 15 minutes at 400°.
Turn out of pan; cover with powdered sugar glaze.

title: texas hash
directions: Heat oil and saute onions and green pepper. Add ground beef. Brown well. Add remaining ingredients. Stir and cover tightly. Cook over high heat until steaming. Reduce heat. Simmer for 30 minutes or until rice is cooked, stirring occasionally.

title: dutch cracked wheat bread
directions: Stir all ingredients except flour in the boiling water. Add flour until moist. Grease and flour loaf pan. Add mixture and cover with second loaf pan upside down. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: low carb hollandaise with steamed asparagus
directions: Steam the asparagus and set aside.

title: peach punch
directions: Boil hot water and sugar until dissolved.
Mix jello, drink mix and cold water and let blend.
Serve chilled.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix margarine and shortening together after both have softened.
Add sugar and mix well!
Add eggs, one at a time, and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add all ingredients together and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Roll in balls and dip in sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: tex-mex meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine ground beef, crumbs, 1/4 pound Velveeta Mexican, egg, onion, 2 tablespoons cilantro, and pepper. Mix well. Shape into an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or to desired doneness. Let stand 5 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla; add flour until dough is dry enough for rolling.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas and add lemon juice; mix well.
Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Alternately add flour and milk.
Beat after each addition.
Fold in bananas. Pour into two 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: shrimp cheese balls
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients well.
Drain shrimp; break into pieces.
Chill.
Form 1/2-inch balls; roll in nuts.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.
Delicious!

title: mississippi mud
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1/2 pound of butter with cocoa and sugar over low heat until sugar starts to melt but does not caramelize, about 5 minutes.
Mix in eggs, flour, salt and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Bake in a greased (bottom only) 13 x 9-inch pan for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: caramel pie
directions: Mix and press into pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: pineapple breeze dessert
directions: Prepare crust mixture according to your favorite recipe.
Pat into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
(I always bake my crust for 8 minutes at 350°.)

title: tomorrows potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes, in skins, until tender. Drain, cool, peel and shred. Combine potatoes, cheese, onion and sour cream. Butter a shallow casserole. Pour in mixture. Chill until next day. Bake, uncovered in 350° oven for 1 hour. Sprinkle with paprika. Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy italian chicken
directions: Pat chicken dry with paper towels.
Thoroughly combine butter and salad dressing mix.
With spatula, spread butter mixture over chicken pieces.
Roll in corn flake crumbs; sprinkle with paprika. Place pieces skin side up (not touching) in shallow pan.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for about 1 hour or until tender; no need to turn. Makes 4 servings.

title: roux
directions: Melt Crisco in a heavy cast-iron pot over medium heat; add flour, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until roux is light brown.
Add onions; cook until onions are brown, stirring constantly.
Add parsley, as desired; stir well.
Roux is done when it is the color of a copper penny. Yields 1/2 cup.

title: garbage dump
directions: In top of double boiler, melt margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Mix together in large bowl cereal, peanuts and raisins.
Pour sauce over this and toss together.
Pour all this in a garbage bag and add powdered sugar.
Shake well and put in refrigerator to chill.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: To brown meat, crumble ground beef; add onion.
Place in 1 3/4-quart casserole.
Cook, covered, on 100% power (High) for 4 to 5 minutes or until meat is no longer pink, stirring once.
Remove, drain and wipe out casserole.
Transfer cooked meat and onion to casserole.
Stir in enchilada sauce, garlic powder and pepper. Gently fold in tortilla wedges and cheese.
Cook uncovered on High for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: hot chocolate base
directions: Mix together in a large bowl.
Put in a tightly covered container.
Use 1/3 cup per cup of hot water.
Makes about 30 cups of cocoa.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring to a boil: sugar, milk and margarine. Boil 9 minutes on medium-high. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter or chips and Marshmallow Creme.
Stir until dissolved. Pour into a buttered 13 x 9 pan. Let cool and cut into squares.

title: sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch slices.
Layer half the potatoes in a buttered shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with apples.
Top with remaining potatoes.
Combine butter, sugar and water in saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: tuna-cashew casserole
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Set aside 1/2 cup chow mein noodles.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine rest of noodles with soup, water, tuna, nuts, celery, onions and pepper.
Taste; add salt if nuts were unsalted.
Sprinkle reserved noodles over top.
Bake, uncovered, 40 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: date pinwheel cookies
directions: Roll into 3 rolls.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator until firm.
Slice and bake in a 350° oven until lightly browned.
I freeze mine and bake as needed.

title: one pan tomato basil chicken
directions: In a large skillet, saute rice-vermicelli as directed.
Add 2 cups water, chicken and special seasonings.
Cover.
Simmer 10 minutes. Stir in broccoli, tomato and basil.
Cover and simmer 5 to 10 more minutes. Sprinkle with cheese before serving.

title: yeast rolls(makes 70)
directions: Dissolve yeast in the warm water; set aside.
Pour hot milk over shortening, sugar and salt.
Let cool.
Beat eggs; add to milk mixture.
Add yeast.
Blend well and sift in flour.
Turn dough on board and knead, adding more flour, if needed.
Place in well-greased bowl and let rise until doubled.
Knead and shape into rolls or cut with biscuit cutter, place in pans and refrigerate.
Let rise again for 1 hour before baking at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Pour butter over after baking.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream oleo, sugar, brown sugar, eggs, peanut butter and vanilla.
Then add flour, salt and oats.
Mix well and spread onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in oven at 375° for 20 minutes. Don't overbake.

title: dad's famous fried egg sandwiches
directions: Preheat small saucepan on 2nd highest setting.
Melt small amount of butter or margarine in pan.
Crack eggs into pan and break yolks, stirring slightly.
Cover pan with loose-fitting lid. Toast bread while eggs cook.
After 1 to 2 minutes, check egg to see if it is more than half cooked.
With a spatula, flip egg in pan and cook until done (approximately 1 to 2 more minutes). Place cooked egg on toast; add cheese and ketchup and/or mayonnaise as desired.

title: freezer tomato soup
directions: Simmer tomatoes and onion in butter over low heat.
Put in blender and mix well.
Pour into container; cool and freeze.
To make soup, thaw and heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat and serve.

title: coconut pecan cake
directions: Beat cake mix, eggs, oil and water well. Fold in coconut/pecan frosting. Bake in Bundt pan in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes. May drizzle confectioners sugar, milk and oleo icing over cake.

title: granny's applesauce cake
directions: Grease and flour one tube pan or 3 medium foil loaf pans. Heat oven to 350°.	First, mix applesauce with the soda.
Then add sugar, cinnamon, cloves, oil, and salt. Reserve 1/2 cup flour to mix with raisins and chopped nuts.	Add remaining flour to applesauce mixture.
A small hand mixer is useful in blending flour in well.
Add floured nuts and raisins.
Pour into pan or pans and bake approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: pecan pie #2
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and corn syrup.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: queen of muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°.
Adjust the rack to the middle of the oven.
Grease 14 muffin cups.

title: crabmeat lasagna
directions: Combine crabmeat and soup, then combine cream cheese, cottage cheese, egg, onion, parsley and seasonings.
Arrange 1/2 of noodles in lasagna pan.
Top with 1/2 of cheese mixture and all of crabmeat mixture.
Top with remaining noodles, then remaining cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Or freeze for later use.
If lasagna has been frozen, increase baking time to between 45 minutes and 1 hour.
Layer sliced tomatoes on top.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Return to oven for 15 more minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim fat from meat; slice in thin narrow slices.
Dredge in flour.
In heavy skillet, brown meat in butter.
Remove meat to dish and brown onions and mushrooms slightly.
Add meat to pan and all liquids and seasonings except sour cream.
Simmer on low for about 2 hours, adding more water as needed and stirring frequently.
At serving time, thicken juices in pan with a bit of flour and water; turn up burner and blend in sour cream quickly but do not boil.
Serve over cooked broad noodles or rice.

title: tortellini spinach soup
directions: Heat oil in a 4-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Add carrots, onion and garlic; cook and stir until onion is tender.
Add broth; bring to a boil.
Add tortellini; boil gently 4 to 5 minutes or until tortellini is almost tender.
Add spinach and oregano; simmer 2 to 3 minutes or until spinach is tender, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle each serving with cheese.
Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.
Can also add some diced, cooked chicken meat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Add soups, water, rice, salt and pepper together.
Mix and place in long casserole dish.
Place uncooked chicken pieces around.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Add water as needed while baking.

title: mastacotti
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain fat.
Heat pasta sauce; put in sausage, onion and Parmesan cheese.
Boil water; add pasta and cook until tender.
Mix all together in large pan.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Put in freezer overnight.
Stir the next morning.
Remove from freezer to get slushy.
Serve slushy.

title: nutty banana pops
directions: You will need 8 flat wooden sticks.

title: spinach soup
directions: In skillet, melt margarine on low heat and add potatoes, onions and mushrooms.
Cover pan and cook 8 to 10 minutes, until soft and translucent.
Wash spinach; pick off tough stems and chop finely. Pour stock into large pan and add potatoes, onions, mushrooms and spinach.
Season with salt, pepper and cloves.
Add oatmeal. Simmer 20 minutes.

title: peach's hamburger stroganoff(peach temmler)
directions: Saute beef and onions until onion is translucent and pink is gone.
Add veggies.
Stir and brown, then add paprika and flour. Mix in and add water.
Put bouillon cube in and break up.
Simmer at least 45 minutes, adding water so it won't stick.
One and one-half hours makes it taste better.
Add herbs such as bay leaf, marjoram, thyme, basil, oregano and dill; also wine, 1/4 to 1/2 cup, if desired.
Just before serving, add sour cream or substitute.
Do not allow to boil or simmer; just heat and stir. Serve over your choice of noodles or rice.

title: deer pot roast
directions: Wipe meat with damp cloth and with 3/4 of the salt pork.
Rub with flour, salt and pepper.
Fry remaining salt pork in kettle and brown meat in this fat.
Remove meat and brown 2 tablespoons flour in kettle.
Set meat on low rack in kettle.
Add water and seasonings.
Cover pan and simmer until meat is nearly tender. Place vegetables around and over meat and continue cooking until vegetables are tender, about 45 minutes.
Serve roast surrounded with vegetables.
Thicken the gravy if necessary and serve with meat.
Serves 4.
Add dumplings 15 minutes before vegetables are tender.

title: pork chops with pineapple sauce
directions: Brown chops; drain.
Place a slice of pineapple on top of each chop.
Mix all ingredients.
Cover chops and cook on low heat for 45 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese. Bake in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with cheese and bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook all ingredients, except for soup, for 5 minutes.
Add the chicken soup and 1/2 can water.
Sprinkle with a little cayenne pepper.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: custard for pies
directions: Heat milk.
In a separate bowl, beat egg yolks very light. Add sugar and flour and beat again.
Mix with a little hot milk and stir.
Add this mixture to the rest of milk.
Cook until thick, stirring all the time.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Add meringue and brown in oven.

title: wispride cheese spread
directions: In mixer, blend cream cheese and butter.
Add cheese gradually.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Serve at room temperature (at least one hour out of refrigerator).

title: sweet pickles
directions: In 3 quart churn; soak cucumbers in water for 10 days. Then drain and slice. Soak overnight in alum water. Rinse off the alum. Soak overnight in pure vinegar. Then take out of vinegar, Don't rinse! Then layer cucumbers and sugar in churn and put spices in center. You can stir every once in a while to mix the spices.

title: the best rice pudding ever
directions: Mix quart of milk, water, rice, salt and sugar together.
Bring gently to boil and simmer 45 minutes.
Add 3 cups milk, beaten eggs and vanilla.
Bring to a boil.
Cool and refrigerate.
Add raisins, if desired, when adding the 3 cups milk.

title: choco-peanut butter bars
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, peanut butter and egg.
Stir in water, flour, soda, baking powder, salt and 1 package chocolate bits. Spread in pan.
Bake for 20 minutes, or until light brown.
Remove from oven; sprinkle remaining chocolate bits evenly over baked layer.
Contained heat will soften morsels.
Spread softened chocolate evenly; sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Cut into bars.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Bake cake.
Pour pineapple with juice as soon as you take it from the oven. Refrigerate until cold.
Mix cream cheese, milk and dry pudding.
Fold in whipped topping.
Ice cake.
Can mix coconut in icing or sprinkle on top.
Top with nuts and cherries.

title: sugared walnuts
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Add brown sugar, vanilla and walnuts. Melt the margarine on cookie sheet in a 250° oven.
Pour walnut mixture on cookie sheet and turn with spatula every 15 minutes until dry, approximately 1 hour.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Stir together margarine, sugar and milk in a 3-quart saucepan; bring to a full boil, stirring constantly to prevent scorching. Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in chocolate until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in pan.
Drain water.
Add the soup and onion; mix well.
Pour crumbs over mixture, dot with butter, then top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork in oil.
Add water; simmer 1 hour.
While pork is cooking, drain juice from pineapple chunks into a saucepan.
Add brown sugar, cornstarch, salt and vinegar.
Cook until sauce has thickened.
Stir in soy sauce, pineapple chunks, vegetables and cooked meat.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Serve over steamed rice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: walnut cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and set aside to cool.
Cream butter; gradually add 2 cups sugar, beating well.
Add 3 eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir melted chocolate into mixture.
Add flour, salt, walnuts and 1 teaspoon vanilla, mixing well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan and set aside.

title: artichoke pie
directions: Saute garlic in oil.
Drain artichokes and chop.
Mix with Mozzarella grated cheese and egg.
Bake at 350° for thirty minutes in pie shell.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, milk, sugar and salt.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Stir several times. Add nutmeg.
Continue baking 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in garlic powder in oleo or in meat juice, as you brown the meat.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms; cook 5 minutes.
Add soup; simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; heat through.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: dump cake
directions: Place pineapple in loaf pan.
Add pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix over top.
Add sliced butter over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: everybody's favorite brownies
directions: Melt together oleo and cocoa, then add rest of ingredients. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: In large bowl, mix sugar and flour, then add melted oleo and eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 10 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° (glass) or 350° (tin pan) for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix together in blender and serve.

title: sugared walnuts
directions: Cook sugar, water, cinnamon and salt to a soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir until nuts are coated and mixture becomes creamy.
Pour on a cookie sheet and separate nuts as they cool.

title: pumpkin pie biscotti
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; stir well. Combine pumpkin, eggs and vanilla, stirring well with a wire whisk.
Slowly add pumpkin mixture to flour mixture, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Mixture will be very crumbly, but will gradually become moist after stirring.

title: crawfish fettuccine
directions: Melt margarine.
Saute celery, onion, green onion and bell pepper.
Add flour and water.
Mix well.
Cook 15 minutes on low fire.
Cook noodles separately.
Add crawfish tails and parsley; season to taste.
Cook 15 minutes.
Cut cheese in chunks and add, stirring, until melted.
Add drained noodles.
Add water or milk, if needed.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil, and sugar together.
In separate bowl, mix all dry ingredients;
add to egg mixture.
Add walnuts and apples. Spread in a greased 13 x 9 inch pan.
Sprinkle chips on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 55 to 60 minutes.
Bake one day before serving.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; cut bread into 1-inch thick slices and arrange slices in a single layer over bottom of dish. Beat eggs, milk, sugar, salt and vanilla together; pour over bread and dot with butter.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight. Bake in 350° oven, uncovered, for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve and top with syrup or powdered sugar; cinnamon can be sprinkled over bread before baking, if desired.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: russian tea cakes(cookies)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix margarine, 1/2 cup powdered sugar and the vanilla.
Stir in flour, nuts and salt until dough holds together.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake until set, but not brown for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheesy chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine first 8 ingredients and place in 2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese and potato chips.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put cake mix in bowl.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sour cream, pudding mix, oil and vanilla.
Mix well.
Divide batter in half.
To one half, add brown sugar, Kahlua and pecans.
In a greased Bundt pan, place half of pecan mixture, then all of plain mixture, then remaining half of pecan mixture.
Run knife through batter to marbleize slightly.
Bake at 350° for one hour and fifteen minutes. Use any kind of glaze such as coffee glaze or buttermilk glaze. Makes a dense, rich, flavorful dessert or coffee cake.

title: spanakopita(greek spinach pie)
directions: Cook spinach; drain thoroughly.
Finely chop small onion and saute in vegetable oil until limp.
Add spinach to onion; cook until dry.
Melt butter; combine with vegetable oil.
Add rest of ingredients to dry spinach and onion mixture (important to be dry, or pie will be runny).

In an 11 x 14-inch baking pan, begin to layer fillo dough, brushing each layer with butter-oil combination (important to use combination butter-oil, or pie will be greasy). Use only half pound of fillo dough for the bottom of the baking pan, then add spinach mixture.
Layer rest of fillo dough on top of spinach mixture, brushing each with butter-oil combination.

title: kay's salad
directions: Wash lettuce, tomatoes and cucumbers off in sink.
Tear lettuce into mouth size pieces.
Cut tomatoes into medium wedges.
Slice cucumbers into thin circles.

title: chalupa
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in slow cooker.
Cover with water (reduce water slightly if beans have been soaked overnight). Cook on high 5 hours.

title: corn relish
directions: Bring to a boil and pour in the jars to fill:

title: ham pinwheels
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on each ham slice.
Trim ends of pickled okra and lay 2 or 3 end to end on short side of ham.
Roll up and chill; slice.

title: pecan toffee
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until it boils. Cook, without stirring, to 236° or soft ball. Add chopped pecans; continue cooking to 290°, soft-crack stage, stirring constantly. Remove form heat. Mixture changes to a deep caramel color. Stir in soda. Turn out onto greased cookie sheet. Spread until even. Immediately spread with chocolate pieces. Spread chocolate over top as it melts. Sprinkle with 1 cup chopped pecans. Cool. Break into pieces.

title: nectar mince pie
directions: Combine sugar, Karo, salt and Crisco; bring to boil.
Beat eggs; add raisins, mincemeat, nuts, vanilla and fruit juices. Gradually add to hot syrup; cool.
Pour into large unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: berdena's sherbet punch
directions: Place frozen sherbet in punch bowl.
Pour soda over sherbet. Add ice to chill.
Serve chilled.

title: sin pie
directions: Combine flour, butter, and pecans; press into an 8x8-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Combine powdered sugar, 1 cup Cool Whip and cream cheese and blend until smooth. Spread over first layer in pan.
Combine pudding and milk; mix together and spread on top of Cool Whip layer.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken-broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Place cooked chicken pieces over the broccoli.
Combine the next four ingredients and spread on top.
Next, sprinkle cheese on top. Combine butter and bread crumbs and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: mom's sauteed crabmeat
directions: Toss crabmeat with juice of lemon and set aside.
Saute garlic cloves, parsley and oregano in 4 tablespoons of butter.
Add crabmeat and saute just until well heated.
Serve on rounds of toast with a tossed salad and parslied noodles.

title: micro-magic milk chocolate almond bars
directions: Combine butter and sugar until creamy.
Sift the flour and salt together and blend into butter and sugar mixture.
Press evenly into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes.
Rotate dish after 2 minutes.
Sprinkle milk chocolate morsels over top and return to microwave for 1 minute on High.
Spread evenly over top.
Sprinkle with chopped almonds. Cool before cutting.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat the eggs and add milk, flour, sugar and flavoring.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and bake until double in 350° oven. Makes 3 pies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Microwave chicken breasts for approximately 3 minutes, then dice.
Cook 2 cups of rice until tender.
Mix all ingredients together and cook.
Microwave on High for 30 minutes or until carrots and broccoli are tender or bake in a 400° oven for 1 hour or until carrots and broccoli are tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish; put in chicken that has been cut into small serving pieces.
Add the soups, broth and stuffing mix.
Dot with butter.
Cook in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: layered pretzel jello salad
directions: First Layer:
Mix pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar together.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then cool.

title: "crazy" chocolate cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add the vinegar, vanilla, oil and water.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes. Makes 1 layer.

title: chicken celebrate
directions: Mix soup and sour cream together.
Put mixture on top of bacon-wrapped chicken in a baking or glass casserole dish.
Bake 2 hours at 350°, covered, taking cover off last 15 to 20 minutes. This dish is best served with a rice dish, green vegetable or salad and tastes very expensive.

title: great spaghetti sauce
directions: Remove casings on sausage.
In a large skillet, brown and crumble ground beef and sausage until done.
Remove from skillet with slotted spoon and put in large stock pot or two large saucepans.
Add onion and mushrooms to grease in skillet and cook until slightly limp.
Remove onions and mushrooms with slotted spoon and add to beef and sausage.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to mix.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat to a simmer. Simmer on low heat for 3 hours.
Makes about 1 gallon.
Freeze some for later.

title: punch
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil, then add jello and let dissolve.
Add the next 5 ingredients.
When serving, add 1 quart of ginger ale to each gallon of mix.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream sugar, oleo, eggs, vanilla, flour and salt.
Add milk.
Dip bread into filling and place in an 11 x 13-inch pan.
Repeat with another layer.
Pour any leftover filling on top layer (2 layers).
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes until browned around edges.

title: country pork stew
directions: Prepare and cut vegetables.
Wipe pork with damp paper towels; cut into 2-inch pieces.
In Dutch oven, saute onion, carrot and celery for about 5 minutes in butter and oil; remove.
Saute pork and sausage; brown on all sides.
Add salt, bay leaf, flour, pepper, wine and water.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables; cook for 1/2 hour.
Cook cabbage wedges in 1 cup water and salt for about 8 minutes.
Arrange cabbage around edges of platter of stew.
Serve with biscuits.

title: florentine stuffed shells
directions: Mix Ricotta cheese, cottage cheese, spinach, Parmesan cheese and eggs and stuff into cooked shells.
Pour 1/2 jar of sauce into bottom of casserole dish.
Add stuffed shells and pour rest of sauce over shells.
Sprinkle Mozzarella on top.
Bake covered 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 10 more minutes.

title: melissa's mud slide
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to directions. When brownies are done, cool for 20 minutes. While brownies are still warm, put 1 scoop
coffee ice cream in center of brownie. Put a drop of Cool Whip in each corner of the brownie. Drip hot fudge over the top of ice cream. Sprinkle nuts on top and place a cherry in the center. Enjoy.

title: scaloppini di vitello alla francese
directions: Pound veal with a mallet until very thin.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Blend.
Dip veal in egg to coat both sides.
Note: dredging in flour first before dipping in egg mixture, gives the veal a nice puffy texture when fried.
After egg dip, coat with flour both sides.
Heat butter in a very heavy skillet (or electric frying pan).
Add veal. Cook about 2 minutes on one side, or until golden brown. Turn and cook on the second side until golden.
Remove veal.
Add lemon juice to skillet.
Pour over veal.
Garnish with lemon slice and sprinkle with parsley.

title: cypress gardens pecan pie
directions: Place chopped pecans in bottom of unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Blend remaining ingredients together; pour over pecans.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 40 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix spinach with remaining ingredients.
Put into shallow buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chitterlings(better known as chittlin's!)
directions: Pressure cook these for 45 minutes.
Drain and snap into 3 to 4-inch sections.

title: autumn fruit salad
directions: Toss banana and apple pieces with orange juice to prevent discoloration.
Drain any excess juice.
Toss with all remaining ingredients. Chill.
Yields 6 servings.

title: date nut cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except the coconut in a large bowl.

title: never fail chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat
oven
Combine flour, baking soda and salt. In	large mixing bowl beat oleo, Crisco and both sugars until fluffy.
Beat
in
eggs
and vanilla.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Stir
in
chips
and
nuts.	Drop
by
rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet pans. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: french onion soup
directions: Heat oil and butter in a large, heavy skillet; saute onions until tender, but do not brown.
Sprinkle onions with seasonings and flour; stir until flour is absorbed.
Add stock and simmer, partially covered, until onions are cooked.
Just before serving, stir in vermouth.
Pour soup into individual crocks.
Arrange toast and Swiss cheese on soup.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Broil until cheese is melted.

title: million dollar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients
in a bowl.
Make into little balls and place on lightly
greased
pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fried cabbage
directions: In wok or large skillet, stir-fry chicken in hot oil until browned.
Add chopped onion, pepper, cabbage and soy sauce to taste.
Cook quickly.
Serve hot.

title: 3 corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and sprinkle with extra cheese.
Bake 1 hour on 375°.

title: caramel layer choco-squares
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted.
Set aside.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix, melted butter, nuts and 3 tablespoons evaporated milk.
Stir until dough holds together.
Press half into pan; reserve other half.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine in a Pyrex dish.
Add to this 1 can of squash.
Mix well.
Leave no lumps.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients well and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cream cheese cookies(makes 3 dozen cookies)
directions: Cream shortening until fluffy.
Gradually work in cream cheese and sugar.
Make sure mixture is creamy and smooth.
Beat in egg yolk, vanilla and flour.
Drop onto a greased sheet and bake for 15 minutes at 375°.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Mix in small bowl the cream of mushroom soup, beef stew, seasoning mix and water. Stir well. Put roast in crock-pot and pour mixture over it. Put onion slices on top and cook until done (8 to 10 hours).

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Grind together carrots, celery, green pepper and onion and drain well.
(Can be done in blender with small amount of water and drained well.)
Mix with cream cheese and enough sour cream to make spreading consistency.
Add vinegar and salt and pepper to taste.
Blend together.
Refrigerate about 2 days.
Make sandwiches.
(This makes a different sandwich for a shower or WCG meeting.)

title: an unusual meat loaf
directions: Combine meat with seasonings.
Beat eggs and add to tomato juice. Cube bread and soak in liquid mix; beat well. Add to meat and mix lightly. Pack into a 5 x 9-inch loaf pan and bake for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Let loaf stand for 10 minutes, then drain off liquid and turn out of pan.
Spread with catsup or if desired, spread catsup on before baking.
This adds moisture and a different flavor.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Beat margarine, sugar and eggs together well; add baking chocolate, flour and chopped nuts.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients with cold water; cook until comes to boil.
Fold in Cool Whip until firm.
Add mandarin oranges.

title: corn salad
directions: Salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste.
Place oil in skillet; set over low heat.
Add corn and cook for 2 minutes or until just tender.
Scrape the corn into bowl and cool.
Stir in chopped pepper (or ripe tomato).
Combine vinegar, mustard, parsley, basil, savory and hot pepper sauce, then blend into corn and pepper or tomato.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: mock lobster casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish and place thawed fish in bottom. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add lemon juice to soup and pour over this.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Combine beef and onion in skillet.
Cook until meat is slightly browned; drain fat and add salt and pepper.
Stir in catsup and tomato sauce.
Heat thoroughly.	Put into 8-inch square or 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Put meat in dish and cover with cheese; put biscuits on top.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lemon basil chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour into large oven bag.
Place in baking pan.
Add lemon juice to bag.
Squeeze bag to blend ingredients.
Remove skin from chicken.
Place chicken in bag. Turn bag to coat chicken with sauce.

title: stackables
directions: Cut circles as large as possible out of the bread.
(You can use a glass or cup if you don't have a sandwich cutter.)
Spread each circle lightly with mayonnaise.
Cut same size circles out of cheese, ham and chicken slices.
Make a sandwich layering in the following order:
bread, circles of cheese, leaf of lettuce, circles of chicken, bread and circles of ham.
Top stack with bread and anchor with a toothpick.

title: egg sausage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, brown sausage over medium heat.
Drain well and set aside.
In large bowl, combine milk, eggs, mustard and salt.
Beat one minute at medium speed. Stir in cheese, bread and sausage.
Pour into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted into the center comes out clean.
Serves 12.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk; mix thoroughly until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping and pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle peanuts on top. Freeze.
Take out of freezer a few minutes before serving.

title: jello fruit salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add crushed pineapple and chill.
Dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Chill until set.
Cut in cubes.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Mix and bring to boil for about 1 minute. Add 1 spoon peanut butter and 3 cups Minute oats.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown rice, onion and sweet pepper in oil.
Add 2 cans tomato sauce and water (but boil water first).
Add salt, mustard and pepper; bring to a boil, then simmer for 5 minutes.
Do not dry. Remove from heat; cover and let stand for 10 minutes.

title: brisket of beef with hunter sauce
directions: Prepare day before:
Place meat in 2 sheets of heavy-duty foil in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix and dribble 1/4 cup water over it.
Seal tightly.
Bake 4 hours at 300°.
Let meat cool, open and transfer to refrigerator after straining juices.
Skim off fat.

title: fried rice
directions: Prepare and measure the vegetables.
Use only the white part of the onion. Slice and save the green part until later.
Beat egg and egg white together.
Pour egg into a nonstick skillet and cook. Remove from pan. Cool and cut into strips.
Heat 1 teaspoon oil. Add garlic, celery, onion and pepper. Stir constantly for about 2 minutes. Add second teaspoon of oil, then add cooked rice. Now add the meat.
Stir constantly until heated through. Stir in bean sprouts.
Mix the soy sauce, lemon juice and ginger and stir into the vegetables.
Place on a platter and put egg strips and green onions over over top.
Serves 4.

title: bavarian
directions: Mix the flour, margarine and pecans.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Make the pudding as directed; set aside.
Mix the remaining ingredients and spread on crust after it cools.
Then top with pudding mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and more chopped nuts if desired.

title: lasagna with meat sauce
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Stir in onion soup mix, water, tomato paste, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Cook lasagna according to directions.
Drain and place in cold water.
Remove as needed.
Place 2 tablespoons meat sauce in bottom of 12 x 8-inch baking pan, then single layer of lasagna, placed lengthwise, layer of mozzarella, layer of cottage cheese, meat sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat ending with sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat sweetened condensed milk and peanut butter until smooth. Add Bisquick and vanilla; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with fork. Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes, until lightly browned.
Store tightly covered.

title: spicy carrots in wine
directions: Boil water; add wine and simmer 5 minutes.
Add spices and simmer 5 more minutes.
Add carrots and cook on medium heat 10 to 15 minutes (until cooked but firm).
Drain and toss with melted oleo.
For spicier carrots, add spice mix after draining.

title: oat bran muffins(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 12-cup muffin tin with margarine.
Combine oat bran, flour, brown sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine apple juice, skim milk, egg whites, oil and honey.
Add flour mixture, bananas and raisins.
Combine until just moistened.
Fill tins and bake at 400° for about 20 minutes, until golden brown and a cake tester comes out clean.

title: sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Heat oil; brown meat.
Remove and drain.
Add onion and pepper; cook until tender.
Add pineapple, pineapple juice, water, vinegar, catsup, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce and garlic.
Blend in brown sugar and cornstarch.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; add meat.
Cook, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours or until tender, stirring occasionally.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Drain pineapple.
Put juice in heavy saucepan.
When hot, add the flour, sugar, salt and eggs which have been beaten together. Attention, mix the dry ingredients together before adding to beaten egg.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Remove from heat and cool. Now mix together pineapple, orange sections, miniature marshmallows and nuts.
Now mix the egg mixture with your fruit, nuts and marshmallows and fold in the whipped cream.
Chill several hours before serving.
Good light dessert, serve with cookies.

title: orange date cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a tube pan. Bake one hour at 350 degrees. Pour glaze over cake while cake is still hot.

title: simple sweet and sour chicken(low-fat)
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Place chicken in 9 x 12-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Pour dressing mixture over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and top with pineapple slices and bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Melt butter, paraffin, add syrup, sugar and peanuts.
Cook until turns a little brown (around 15 to 20 minutes on medium heat).
Put in baking soda, remove from heat and make sure you stir the soda in real good.
Pour in buttered, non-stick pan. After cools, break up in pieces.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly and add garlic, 1 tablespoon parsley, basil, 1 1/2 teaspoon salt, tomatoes and paste and simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until thick.
Cook lasagna noodles until tender, drain and rinse in cold water.
Combine Ricotta cheese, eggs, remaining salt, pepper, parsley and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese. Place half the noodles in a 13 x 7-inch baking dish.
Spread 1/2 cheese mixture over noodles.
Spread 1/2 Mozzarella cheese over cheese mixture and cover with 1/2 meat sauce.
Repeat layers and garnish with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 370°.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Preheat preferably 2 frying pans with dash of margarine in each.
Have plenty of ventilation as it may get smoky.
Pour batter in frying pan and tilt pan until you obtain a thin layer covering.
Cook quickly at medium temperature. Store in warm pan in oven until all done.
Serve with your choice of toppings.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding apples last.
Mix well. Bake in greased and floured pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate pudding fudge cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine cake mix, pudding mix, sour cream, milk, oil, water and eggs. Beat 4 minutes, then mix in 2 cups chocolate chips.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Make crust of pretzels, margarine (melted) and 1/2 cup sugar. Place in 13 1/2 x 9-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add ingredients except sour cream. Mix well.
Pour half of gelatin mixture into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Spread sour cream evenly over mixture. Cover with remaining gelatin mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Soften butter and cream cheese.
Cream the butter and cheese together, gradually adding sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla, flour and salt.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour batter in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: cocoa gravy
directions: Mix all ingredients in a pan.
Heat until the mixture reaches desired consistency.

title: carbonara sauce
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, over medium heat, heat soup, ham, parsley and half and half until hot, stirring frequently.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Serve over hot, cooked pasta.
Makes about 2 cups, 4 servings.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare brownies as directed on package. Bake and cool.

title: pizza things
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Add all seasonings.
Add cheese to meat mixture and stir until melted.
Place rye bread on baking sheet and spread mixture on bread slices.
Place under the broiler until the bread is lightly toasted and meat mixture bubbles.
These may be frozen before broiling for later use.
Freeze on a cookie sheet, then store in a freezer bag.
Makes about 75.

title: chicago cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in tube pan at 350° until done.

title: tender baked cajun chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In small bowl, blend mayonnaise and Cajun seasoning. Coat chicken with mayonnaise mixture, then with bread crumbs. On baking sheet, arrange chicken. Bake chicken 20 minutes or until chicken is golden brown and thoroughly cooked.

title: waldorf salad(mom)
directions: Pour lemon juice over apples.
Add pineapple tidbits, grapes, marshmallows and walnuts.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook chopped broccoli in boiling water 3 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain and plunge into cold water; drain again.
Set aside.
Melt 1 tablespoon plus 1 teaspoon margarine in a medium saucepan over medium heat; add onion and saute 3 minutes or until tender.
Add flour and mustard; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly with a wire whisk.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook additional 2 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in pepper.

Combine broccoli, milk mixture, rice, cheese and mayonnaise in bowl; stir well. Spoon into a shallow 2-quart casserole coated with cooking spray. Melt remaining teaspoon margarine; combine with melba toast crumbs and sprinkle over broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yield:
8 servings (about 170 calories per 1/2 cup serving).

title: good vegetable dip
directions: Mix and let stand a while before serving.

title: chicken kona
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper to taste.
Place in crock-pot.
Combine the rest of the ingredients, except honey and pour over chicken.
Cover and cook on low for 3 to 4 hours, until chicken is brown and tender.
Remove chicken from pot and arrange on broiler pan.
Brush with honey.
Broil until golden brown, brushing with honey several times.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy shrimp dip
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, onion, Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder.
Mix well.
Stir in shrimp, breaking up shrimp lightly.
Form mixture into a ball.
Refrigerate, covered, until ready to serve.

title: fish casserole
directions: Thaw fish; place in buttered baking dish.
Pour undiluted soup over fish; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until fish is done.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all but Cool Whip in a pan until thick on medium/high heat.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add Cool Whip.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: caramel pie
directions: Put condensed milk (in the can) in a saucepan and cover with water.
Boil slowly for 1 hour.
Allow can to cool thoroughly or it will explode.
Line bottom of pie shell with bananas.
Pour cooled condensed milk over bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with pecans.
You can store the cooked cans of condensed milk in your refrigerator for 6 months.

title: chocolate glaze
directions: In small saucepan bring sugar and water to boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat, add chocolate chips, stirring with a fork until chips are melted and mixture is smooth. Cool to desired consistency, drizzle over cake.
Use immediately, about 2/3 cup glaze.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Thaw frozen strawberries
and
then add instant vanilla pudding and strawberry jello.
Stir
until mixed and then fold in marshmallows and
whipped topping.	Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: barbecue or sloppy joes
directions: Add all to meat mixture and simmer 1 hour. (Also good with cooked, cubed pork.)
* This recipe was used for great sandwiches at the Eldorado Ice Cream Factory.

title: apple dessert
directions: Put apple pie filling in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over the filling.
Drizzle butter over cake mix, then sprinkle over the nuts.

title: chinese barbecued pork
directions: Combine all ingredients except pork.
Rub into pork loin and marinate 3 to 4 hours.
Roast in a 350°
oven on rack for 25 minutes.
Turn and bake 25 minutes more.
Serve with hot mustard and sesame seed.

title: white crisco icing
directions: Put flour and milk in saucepan and cook until thickened.
Set aside and let cool.
Cream together white sugar and shortening; add vanilla and beat well again.
Add to flour and milk mixture. Beat until cool.
Add coconut, if desired.

title: irish treacle bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in large bowl.
Add milk, molasses, melted shortening and raisins; let stand 20 minutes so oatmeal will absorb some liquid.
Put in greased bread loaf pan. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat
eggs, sugar, flour, milk and yeast.
Add corn and stir. Lay butter	pats
on
top and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: stir-fried strawberries, mandarins and kumquats
directions: Mix strawberries, mandarins, kumquats, lemon juice and ginger. In a cup, combine the liqueur and water.
Heat oil to the smoking point in a wok; add the strawberry mixture and stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Pour into a bowl, stir in the liqueur mixture.
Serve as dessert or side dish with curry.
Serves 4.

title: beef teriyaki
directions: Slice beef into very thin strips. Mix cornstarch, broth, soy, sugar, and garlic. Stir-fry beef in non-stick skillet until browned and juices evaporate. Add broccoli and cornstarch mixture. Cook and stir until mixture boils and thickens.

title: fruit smoothy
directions: Put sliced frozen banana in blender; add strawberries and blend.
Add other ingredients until smooth.
This is an excellent after school treat, and the best way to use "old bananas".
If bananas become too ripe to eat fresh, just freeze them in the peel. The peel will turn black, but just peel and use!

title: caramel corn
directions: Put corn in large pan.
Boil sugar, oleo, syrup, salt and vanilla together for 5 minutes; add soda.
Stir quickly; pour over popcorn and stir to coat.
Put on 2 large cookie sheets and bake in a 250° oven for 35 minutes.
Stir often while baking.
You may add peanuts, pecans or walnuts, if you like.
Preheat nuts in oven while popping corn and cooking syrup, especially if you are keeping nuts in the freezer.

title: wild duck dressing
directions: In a
3-quart
saucepan,
add
duck, trimmings, peppercorns, garlic and
enough water to completely cover.
Bring to a boil; cover, lower
heat
and simmer 3 hours.
Remove duck. Strain broth and set aside.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix together.
Do not beat.
Bake in greased, floured tube or Bundt pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet n sour pork
directions: Cut pork into cubes and marinate in the next 3 ingredients for 10 minutes.
Dip in cornstarch, then deep fry until golden brown.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Boil the butter and sugar together for 3 minutes.
Add the nuts.
Pour over crackers.

title: "in a hurry" chicken curry
directions: In a large skillet, saute chicken, mushrooms and onions in oil until chicken is lightly browned on all sides.
Stir in flour, broth and curry powder (optional).
Add parsley, then pour in milk and water.
Simmer, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes, or until chicken pieces are tender.

title: pig-out cake
directions: Preheat oven.
Make cake mix according to directions. However, substitute liquid for oranges and liquid.
Bake cake.

title: cinnamon apple rings
directions: Place butter in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Microwave on High for 50 seconds or until butter melts.
Stir in lemon juice, honey and cinnamon.
Place apple slices in butter mixture, turning to coat both sides.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap. Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until apples are tender, giving dish a half-turn after 2 minutes.
Let stand 2 minutes before serving.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows over bottom of pan.
Combine thawed strawberries and jello; set aside.
Blend cake mix, water, oil and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes at highest speed.
Pour batter in pan over marshmallows. Spoon strawberries evenly over batter.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes. Cool.

title: pasta salad
directions: In large bowl, combine mayonnaise, mustard, tarragon, salt and pepper.
Add seashells, green beans, tuna and onion; toss gently to coat.
Cover; chill to blend flavors.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Microwave onion and butter for 2 min.
Mix all ingredients, hash browns last. Put into a 9x12 pan.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple and mix cheese into this.
Mix sugar and flour and coat chunks.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with Ritz crackers and drizzle butter over this.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: autumn beef vegetable soup
directions: In a large pot brown meat with onion.
Cook until onion is tender.
Drain.
Salt and pepper to taste, if desired.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Serves 8.

title: apple pie
directions: Place 2 1/2 c. flour and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Cut small teaspoon sized pieces of lard into the flour, about 5 pieces at a time, with a hand pastry cutter or fork.
When all the lard is worked into flour, should have a crumble like look, start adding cold water, 2 tablespoons at a time, until flour mixture pulls away from sides of the bowl.
Separate dough into 2 equal parts, cover, and refrigerate while preparing apples.

title: caramel dip for apples
directions: Melt butter and stir in sugar while butter is warm. After sugar melts, stir in sour cream and mix until dip is all the same color.
Dip your apple and enjoy!

title: polynesian wedding cake
directions: Combine all ingredients into large mixing bowl; mix with wooden spoon. Do not use mixer. Put batter in a greased spring form pan and bake on the bottom shelf of oven at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or bake for 60 minutes in 9 x 13-inch, greased pan. Cool and refrigerate overnight. Frost next day.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Put Jell-O and undrained pineapple in a pan and heat. Do not boil. Remove from heat and add buttermilk, pecans and Cool Whip. Mix well. Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate.

title: sausage goodies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by spoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pecan pie(you won't believe how good this is with no pecans!)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 1 tortilla in 9-inch pie plate sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Spray tortilla and sprinkle with Molly McButter.
Repeat with second tortilla.
Using another 9-inch pie plate, spray outside bottom and place on top of tortillas.
This helps press and form pie crust.
Bake crust with pie plate on top at 350° for 7 minutes.
Cool slightly while preparing filling.

title: oatmeal breakfast bar
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in rectangle pan. Cut into bars.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles.
Place triangles with points toward center in greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Press to form a crust; seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over dough; sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over sausage. Top with mushrooms, green peppers and onions.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375° (don't let crust get too brown).
This is good served with picante sauce.

title: pineapple mint freeze
directions: Drain pineapple; soften gelatin in syrup.
Add jelly and dash of salt.
Heat mixture and stir until gelatin is dissolved and jelly is melted.
Stir in pineapple.
Chill until mixture is thick and syrupy.
Whip cream with sugar.
Fold in thickened gelatin and tint with food coloring.
Spoon into 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch dish and freeze until firm.

title: crab rangoon
directions: Cream first 6 ingredients with mixer.
Drop by teaspoonful into center of wonton.
Seal edges with egg whites and roll all corners to center.
Freeze for at least an hour for best results. Deep fry.

title: almond crescents
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add almonds with salt to the creamed mixture.
Work in the flour.
Chill dough thoroughly. Pinch off pieces of dough and roll in the palm of your hands, then pull ends around to form crescents.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 15 minutes in slow oven at 325°.
Let them cool a minute on the pans to crisp up.
While still warm, lift off pans and roll in sifted confectioners sugar and cool on racks.
This makes about 30 cookies.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix together and serve cold.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine chopped meat, rice, salt and pepper.
Form into small balls about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Place in baking dish.
In a skillet, brown onion and green pepper in shortening.
Add tomato juice, nutmeg and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over meat balls. Cover baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 1 hour or until rice is very tender.
Makes 8 porcupines.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Put into a loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Preheat oven and keep the juices drained.

title: green rice
directions: Add ingredients together.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour in oven at 350°.

title: mock chow mein
directions: Braise beef cubes until just tender.
Add water, celery and remaining ingredients, except cornstarch.
Cook 20 minutes. Thicken with cornstarch.
Serve over steamed rice and top with chow mein noodles.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine the first 3 ingredients until smooth.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil oleo, milk, sugar, cocoa for 2 minutes; remove from heat and stir in oatmeal, peanut butter, vanilla.
Drop on wax paper. Yields approximately 3 dozen.
Before you start measure the oatmeal and peanut butter and place wax paper as these set up fast.

title: deer roast
directions: Cook deer roast, soup and soup mix in crock-pot until meat comes apart.
Cook rice according to box recipe.
Serve meat over rice.

title: sugar cream cake
directions: Beat cake mix, 2 eggs and margarine; mixture will be stiff. Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat sugar, cream cheese and other 2 eggs.
Put on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.
Does not need icing.

title: watergate salad
directions: Fold dry pudding into whipped topping; fold in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight for best flavor.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix coconut and pecans; sprinkle in bottom of a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make cake following package directions and pour over the coconut and pecan mixture.
Mix vanilla, cream cheese and sugar.
Pour into the pan over cake mixture.
Cut up stick of oleo and put on top of the cheese-sugar mixture.
Cook at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Cake will crack when done.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in milk.
Add other ingredients.
Use enough of the flour to make soft dough.
Let rise nearly double.
Then use.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add egg and beat well.
Mix flour, salt and soda together and add alternately to creamed mixture with milk.
Stir in rhubarb.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured cake pan.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Cream together margarine or butter and sugar.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda, Rice Krispies and pecans.
Mix all together.
Make into small balls.
Press down.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: asparagus and pine nut pizza
directions: Cook asparagus in a bit of water until soft.
In one tablespoon of olive oil, toast the pine nuts.
In food processor, put the pine nuts with the olive oil.
Add basil, rest of the olive oil, Parmesan, aspatita and salt.
Blend until well mixed.
Take asparagus from pot and drain.
Do not overcook.
Put pita breads on cookie sheet.
Pour sauce over each pita bread, spreading evenly, leaving a border.
Top each bread with a few asparagus pieces. Sprinkle each with bell pepper.
Top with Mozzarella then Parmesan. Bake in 350° oven for a few minutes.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, vanilla and lemon flavorings. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together the flour, salt, baking soda and cream of tartar. Combine preserves, sour cream and pecans.
Add alternately with dry ingredients and beat thoroughly.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured 5 x 15-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in smaller loaf pan.

title: hot beefy dip
directions: Chop everything up; mix into sour cream, cream cheese and milk and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until edges turn brown.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crush cookies and mix with melted butter.
Pat 3/4 of the mixture into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding with milk, add cream cheese and mix well.
Pour this mixture over cookies. Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle rest of cooked mixture over Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.

title: coconut-pineapple slush
directions: Blend all ingredients together in blender on high. Speed until ice is crushed and mixture is thick. Serve immediately. Yield: 1 serving.

title: lemon chiffon loaf
directions: Line 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with foil extending 1 inch beyond sides.
Line bottom and sides of loaf pan with ladyfingers (18). In large bowl, combine milk, lemon and food coloring, if desired; mix well.
In small mixer bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff but not dry.
Fold into condensed milk mixture. Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into prepared pan.
Cover filling with remaining 6 ladyfingers.
Cover and chill for 4 hours.
Invert onto serving platter; peel off foil.
Serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken alfredo
