directions: Cut chicken tenderloins into bite-size pieces.
Brown in skillet. Add seasoning, then 2 jars alfredo. Boil noodles as directed. Drain. Pour sauce over noodles and serve.
Add garlic bread and salad.

title: chewy pecan pie bars
directions: Pour butter into a 9 x 13 pan. Set aside. In a mixing bowl, combine brown sugar, flour, eggs, vanilla, baking soda and salt. Mix well. Stir in pecans. Spread over butter. Bake 350° for 30-35 minutes. Remove from oven. Immediately dust with confectioners sugar. Cool before cutting.

title: pineapple cake from texas
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 35 minutes in preheated oven at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Pour icing over cake; sprinkle with coconut (and nuts if desired) while cake is warm.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon over high heat.
Remove bacon and reserve bacon grease.
Saute onion in grease until tender. Add sugar, flour, salt and pepper. Stir until smooth. Gradually add water and vinegar.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Add to potatoes and bacon.
Serve warm.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and sugar together. Add eggs and fruit. Mix well for 30 or 40 minutes. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes. Test with toothpick.

title: tomato pie
directions: Cook pie shell halfway.

Layer sliced tomatoes and sprinkle with basil, thyme, salt and pepper. Top with dash of cayenne pepper. Spread mayonnaise over top and sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool 15 minutes before serving. Great hot or cold.

title: hot huckleberry cake with sauce
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Stir in molasses and beat in eggs. Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat them into first mixture, then slowly add boiling water.
Beat thoroughly.
Fold in berries. Pour into greased, floured 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serve hot with sauce.

title: avocado soup
directions: Peel and pit avocados and cut into pieces.
Put flesh of avocados into container of blender or food processor.
Add a little chicken broth to aid processing.
When very smooth, pour and scrape avocado into a bowl.
Add chicken broth, sour cream and seasonings; blend well.
May be strained through a fine sieve for an even smoother soup.
Chill thoroughly.

title: ham and egg omelet
directions: Mix all together.
This may be fried or baked at 350° for about 1 hour or until set.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco seasoning.
Spread in 9 x 9-inch pan. Top with remaining ingredients.
Serve with taco chips.

title: southern gal biscuits
directions: Sift baking powder, flour, salt, sugar and cream of tartar into a large bowl.
Add shortening to flour mixture.
Slowly add egg and milk and stir until stiff.
Knead dough 5 times.
Roll to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with a 1 1/2-inch cutter.
Bake on aluminum pan (cookie sheet).
Bake at 450° for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook ingredients except for hash browns and Velveeta on low for 1 hour.
Half way through the hour, add hash browns.
At 1 hour, add Velveeta in mixture.
Use pepper to taste.
Do not salt.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites and sugar until stiff.
Add the nuts, chocolate chips, and dates.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets. Preheat oven to 300° for 15 minutes.
Place cookies in oven; turn off oven.
Leave 12 hours (overnight).
Remove from sheets and store in air tight container.

title: pretzel snacks
directions: Mix the dressing with Old Bay, dill and oil.
Pour on cookie sheet and bake at 250° for 50 minutes.

title: skillet pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in a large covered skillet.
Place rings of lemon, onion and green pepper on top of chops.
Sprinkle with salt. Pour tomato juice on top and dot with butter.
Cover and cook on top of stove (or in electric skillet) 1 1/2 hours or until tender. Serve hot.
Keep rings in place to make an attractive dish.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients (except pecans) thoroughly and form into ball shape.
Crush pecans in blender and roll cheese ball in crushed pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: peas and mushrooms
directions: Cook peas, fresh or frozen.
Drain well. Cook mushrooms and onion in butter until tender.
Stir in sugar, salt and a dash of pepper.
Add peas and pimiento.
Cover and heat.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar in a sauce pan.
Boil for 3 minutes. Add jello and let cool.
Add cream cheese, apples, celery and pecans to mixture.
Add cool whip and refrigerate.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach; squeeze out all water.
Add Ranch and mayonnaise.
Mix together; chill.
Serve with celery and carrot sticks.

title: spinach salad
directions: Tear spinach and put in bowl.
Add bean sprouts, green onions and mix well.
Sprinkle eggs and bacon on top.

title: ann turley's dressing
directions: Melt butter in skillet and saute onions, celery, and parsley. Pour over bread crumbs in very large bowl. Add all seasonings and toss together well. Pour in enough broth to moisten. Add beaten eggs and mix well. Pack lightly into crockpot. Cover and set to high for 45 minutes then reduce to low to cook for four to eight hours.

title: kay becker's onion soup
directions: Cook onions slowly in butter and oil in covered saucepan for 15 minutes.
Uncover and raise heat to moderate; stir in salt and sugar.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes, stirring frequently, until onions are deep golden brown.
Sprinkle in flour and stir for 3 minutes. Take off from heat and blend in boiling bouillon.
Add wine. Season to taste and return to heat.
Simmer partially covered for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit pie
directions: Put pie filling in a pie plate.
Trim bread, then place on top of filling.
Melt the margarine; add sugar, flour and egg.
Mix well.
Pour on top of bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Combine first five ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle 1 box yellow cake mix over pumpkin mixture. Drizzle oleo (melted) over cake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a knife comes out clean.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: great dressing for sliced cucumbers
directions: Blend well and add sliced cucumbers.
Will keep for a week or more in refrigerator.
Be sure to store in a sealed container.

title: jerky recipe
directions: Cut meat into 3/8-inch to 1/2-inch strips.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight or up to 2 days.
Lay meat on foil-covered oven
racks
and let dry at less than 150°.
Drying will take approximately 6 to 8 hours.
Store in airtight containers (Mason jars)
at
room
temperature.
It
can also be frozen. Teriyaki sauce can be substituted for the Worcestershire for a sweeter version.

title: cherry cha cha
directions: Make graham cracker crumb crust. Put in an 8 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Must be cold before you put in mixture.

title: east texas stew
directions: Brown and drain beef. Add spuds, chopped onion, bouillon cubes and enough water to cook potatoes.
Cook vegetables until tender, then add tomato juice, brown sugar, butter and chili powder.
Let simmer for 15 minutes, then add corn and cooked macaroni.
Let simmer slowly for 10 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O as directed on package.
Put in refrigerator until almost jelled.
Stir in blueberry pie filling.
Chill until set.
Slice bananas and put on Jell-O, then sprinkle nuts over bananas and add Cool Whip on top.

title: ribbon cake
directions: Crust: Mix butter, flour and nuts together. Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: sweet dough pie and filling
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until smooth.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Add dry ingredients (flour, baking powder and salt) alternately with liquid until well mixed.

title: golden peach pie(family favorite!)
directions: The flavoring is what makes this pie.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients
together and make small balls.
In double boiler, melt 1/2
cake
paraffin.	Stir
in
ounces chocolate bits (melted, may require more chocolate bits).
Dip peanut butter balls in mixture and cool on rack.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Add strawberries, pineapple and bananas; stir well.
Put half the mixture in refrigerator until congealed.
(Leave other half on counter.)

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites.
Slowly add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Fold in crackers and pecans.
Pour into buttered pan and bake for 30 minutes at 300°.
Serve with whipped cream on top.

title: orange cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream sugar and butter.
Blend in eggs. Add flour and milk alternately; blend in rind and juice.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Frost with orange icing, if desired.

title: spinach and zucchini gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix Parmesan, bread crumbs and pine nuts together with 1 tablespoon olive oil for topping.
Set aside. Steam spinach; drain and set aside.

title: texas special
directions: Brown together hamburger, onion, green pepper and celery; salt and pepper to taste.
Add the remaining ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Cover with additional grated cheese and bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: broccoli and cauliflower soup
directions: Cook cauliflower
with
of
the
broth for 5 to 10 minutes.
Cook
broccoli,
mustard seed and dill weed with the rest of the broth until tender.
Put cooked cauliflower, broth and mace into blender.
Blend until smooth.
Pour this mixture and broccoli
mixture
into
big
soup
pot.
Fry onions in butter in frying pan.
Add to soup.
Add salt.
Shake 1 cup of milk with flour in gravy mixer.
Add slowly.
Add the remaining milk.
Cook until
thick
and
bubbly.
Add
cheese right before serving. Serve after cheese melts.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Cream melted shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs.
Mix. Add bananas.
Stir baking soda and warm water together and add to mixture.
Add plain flour, salt and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.
Insert toothpick in center to check if done.

title: beth's taco casserole
directions: Combine soup and sour cream in a flat bowl large enough to hold a flat corn tortilla.
Combine olives, onion and cheese.
Pour enough sour cream mixture to sparsely cover bottom of Pam-sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Fry each tortilla soft, blot on paper towels.
Dip each tortilla, both sides, in soup/sour cream mixture and place 2 tablespoons of cheese/onion/olive mixture in middle.
Roll and place in pan.
Bake at 350° until bubbling (about 30 minutes).

title: bonnie hawkins' biscuit pie
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Take off heat.
Add broken pieces of biscuits in it.
Let soak.

title: raisin pie
directions: Boil water in saucepan.
Add raisins and simmer until tender (3 to 5 minutes).
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; stir into hot raisins.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, to a full rolling boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Blend in lemon rind and juices.
Pour hot filling into pastry-lined pie pan; dot with butter and cover with remaining pastry.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm, plain or with ice cream.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly butter, shortening, sugar, egg and flavorings.
Blend in flour and salt.
Divide dough in half.
Blend food color in 1/2 of dough.
Shape a teaspoon of dough from each half into 4-inch rope-like dough.
Roll them on lightly floured board.
Place ropes side by side; press together lightly and begin twisting.
Complete each candy cane cookie, one at a time.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Curve top of cookie to form the handle of the cane.
This is fun to do with children for the holidays.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix flour and dry yeast together. Mix egg and sugar together. Add water and margarine to flour and yeast mixture. Add egg and sugar mixture. Let set for 15 to 30 minutes. Refrigerate. Can be refrigerated for one week. Bake rolls at 400° until brown.

title: 2-step chicken-broccoli divan
directions: In 9-inch pie plate or shallow casserole, arrange broccoli; top with chicken.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix butter with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until hot.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: corn salsa
directions: Saute onions about 3 minutes in oil, then add peppers and garlic; saute 2 more minutes.

title: sesame-pecan wafers
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat butter on medium-high for 30 seconds. Add the sugar and the vanilla; beat until combined. Beat in as much of the flour as you can with the mixer. Stir in remaining flour, sesame seeds and pecans. Divide dough in half. If dough is too sticky, wrap each piece in plastic wrap and chill in refrigerator about 1 hour.

title: everything pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk together.
In oven, toast the coconut, pecans and stick of margarine at 350° until brown; stir occasionally.
In microwave, heat the caramel topping.

title: cheese-chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup, garlic and Cheez Whiz together.
Add chicken.
Cook noodles.
Combine all ingredients; put in casserole dish.
Top with crushed onion rings or corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: egg souffle
directions: Mix in 9 x 9-inch pan, reserving 1/2 cup cheese for later. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes (until solid).
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: zesty macaroni salad
directions: Combine macaroni and vegetables.
In small bowl, mix remaining ingredients well.
Pour over macaroni mixture and toss well. Cover and refrigerate until chilled.

title: tuna bunwiches
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients.
Separate biscuits.
On floured surface, roll into 5 x 3-inch ovals.
Spoon tuna mixture into 4 ovals.
Top with 4 ovals.
Moisten between edges with a little milk; seal them by pressing with fork.
Cut desired shapes from remaining ovals.
Place on top; brush surface with egg.
On ungreased baking sheet, bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes, or until browned.
Serves 4.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Combine oleo, sugar, flour, vinegar and eggs, add coconut. Blend well. Pour into pie crust. Bake at 300 degrees for 45 minutes or until it does not shake.

title: cheesecake recipe
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and butter. Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Beat in eggs and lemon juice.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 45 minutes or until center is set.
Top with sour cream.
Bake 5 minutes at 425°.
Cool.
Top with pie filling.

title: tomato aspic salad
directions: Remove 1 cup V-8 juice.
Dissolve gelatin in juice.
Heat to boiling point the remaining V-8 juice.
Remove from heat.
Pour into a mold or casserole.
Add gelatin mixture.
Add bell pepper, celery, Lea & Perrins and lemon juice.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Stir well.
Cover with foil.
Cool 8 to 12 hours.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Add Cool Whip and nuts. Mix well.
Chill.

title: caramel cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add egg yolks. Mix dry ingredients together.
Add to batter alternately with sour cream, mixing well. Add vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Mix well.
Pour in 4 prepared round cake pans.
Bake in preheated 315 degree oven for 15 to 30 minutes or until cake springs back when touched with fingers in center.

title: old henry bars
directions: Mix (margarine) butter, brown sugar and oats together.
Bake in a greased jelly roll pan (15 x 18 x 2-inch) or on a cookie sheet with 1-inch sides at 350° for 15 minutes.
While still warm, spread peanut butter over baked mixture.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over peanut butter.
Cool in refrigerator.
Cut into squares.

title: pizza alla siciliana
directions: Brush the dough with a little olive oil.
Spread tomato sauce over the dough to within 1/2-inch of the edge.
Distribute olives, anchovies and capers over sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Drizzle with the remaining olive oil.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets, cool and slice.
Fry bacon.
Add onion and bacon to potatoes.
In small amount of bacon grease, blend in sugar, flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Remove from heat and add vinegar and water, stirring until well blended and smooth.
Pour over potatoes and mix.
Best if not refrigerated.

title: chewy nut bars
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan; stir in brown sugar.
Stir in oats, salt, baking powder and almond extract; mix well.
Stir in walnuts.
Pat into 10 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 22 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars.
Makes 2 to 4 dozen cookies, depending on bar size.

title: orange pineapple sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: cheese straws
directions: Combine cheese and butter in a large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and gradually add to cheese mixture until dough is no longer crumbly.
Shape into a ball.
Use a cookie press to shape dough into straws.
Cut into 2 inch lengths.
Bake at 375° for 10 to12 minutes until lightly browned.
Store in air tight containers with wax paper between layers.

title: easy marshmallow four layer bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix cake mix, margarine and water until blended.
Pat into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes.

title: hash brown potatoes casserole
directions: Thaw the frozen hash browns.
Cut the onion in small chunks. Mix all the ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 11-inch glass Pyrex dish. Top with Parmesan cheese and a dab of butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 10.

title: ole suzanna pie
directions: Bake pie shells.
Mix chopped pecans, coconut and margarine. Cook on stove until lightly toasted.
Set aside to cool.
Mix the cream cheese, Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Put 1/2 of cream cheese mixture in pie shells.
Drizzle caramel syrup and top with 1/2 of pecan mixture.
Repeat and top with pecan mixture.
Freeze overnight; thaw about 20 minutes before serving.

title: bacon wraps
directions: Cut crust off bread slices, then cut slices in half (rectangles).
Mix chives in cream cheese.
Spread mixture on each bread slice.
Roll bread up, then wrap 1/2 slice of bacon around rolled bread.
Secure with toothpick.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Check after 10 to 15 minutes and turn wraps over to prevent overbrowning on bottom.
Drain on towels and serve warm.
Enjoy!

title: chocolate dream pie
directions: Blend margarine, flour and pecans well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Blend cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip; spread over crust.
Mix small packages of instant pudding and milk; chill for about 5 minutes.
Spread over cream cheese mixture, spreading carefully to make smooth layer.
Do not stir.
Spoon Cool Whip on top of chocolate layer. Garnish with almonds.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.

title: fruit and nut ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cut up cream cheese and add to gelatin.
Add half and half and pour into ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on serving dish.
Mix fruit and nuts together and place in the center of jelled ring.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: beef noodle chop suey
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook meat and onion until meat is brown. Drain meat.
Stir in water, noodles, sauce mix, water chestnuts and vegetables.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: Chop cabbage for cole slaw.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand 1 hour before squeezing out
the liquid.
Add the green pepper and celery.
Mix the vinegar, water, sugar and celery seed in a saucepan; boil 1 minute. Cool and pour over vegetables. Freeze in plastic containers. Tastes just like fresh cole slaw when thawed.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour with baking soda.
Cream butter or margarine, gradually adding sugars and creaming until very light and fluffy. Blend peanut butter into creamed mixture and then beat in the eggs. Stir in flour mixture.
Form dough into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten slightly with tines of fork. Bake in 350° oven for about 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 to 6 dozen.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain sweet potatoes; mash with electric mixer; add remainder of ingredients to potatoes and beat mixture until smooth. Pour into greased oblong or square 2-inch glass baking dish.
Sprinkle with topping and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: spiced peaches
directions: In saucepan, combine 2/3 cup of syrup with the remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Pour over peaches; cool, then cover and chill at least 24 hours.
Serve at room temperature.

title: pecan-cooky pie
directions: Beat egg and sugar until fluffy.
Add cocoa and mix well. Now add oleo and beat thoroughly.
Fold in pecans and wafer crumbs.
Put in an 8-inch pie pan and chill several hours.
When ready to serve, garnish with Cool Whip.

title: special hamburger sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Put in tightly covered container and refrigerate.
Makes 2 cups.
Use within a month. The sauce and finely cut lettuce is all you need to go on your hamburger.

title: 1-2-3 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs, one at a time.
Cream sugar and eggs until they are light and fluffy.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour and milk with vanilla into sugar mixture alternately.
Bake in 350° oven in 3 (8-inch) layer pans for 30 minutes until done.

title: salsa
directions: Crush tomatoes; chop cilantro and onions.
Remove all seeds from peppers and chop finely.
Combine all ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients well. Roll in small balls.
Bake at 400° about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cookie recipe
directions: Sift sugar, baking powder, salt and vanilla into medium bowl. Cut
in
shortening
with
pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse
cornmeal.
Add
eggs;
mix	with fork until dough holds together and becomes smooth.
Mix with hands until well combined. Wrap in waxed paper; refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain peas and carrots.
Add milk and onion salt.
Peel potatoes; cream well.
Pour over peas.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with pepper.
Pour grated cheese over all.
Cook in a 6 x 10-inch baking dish for 10 minutes in a 300° oven.

title: tiger butter candy
directions: Melt chocolate and peanut butter in double boiler.
Pour on wax paper on cookie sheet.
Put chocolate chips in and mix until melted.
Chill.

title: candied yams
directions: Boil yams until done but firm.
Peel and slice, then place into semi-deep pan.
Slice butter or margarine over yams.
Add sugar evenly on top of yams.
Pour syrup even with top layer of yams. Cook/bake at 325° uncovered until syrup is thick.

title: pecan topped chocolate pound cake
directions: Combine butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour and cocoa; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Pour batter into a well-greased 10-inch tube pan. Sprinkle pecans over batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan about 15 minutes.
Remove and let cool.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cut each breast into 12 pieces.
Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt, thyme and basil.
Mix well.
Dip chicken in margarine.
Roll in crumb mixture.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 400°.

title: spoon bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in a 9-inch iron skillet at 450° for 35 minutes.

title: baked seafood casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato chips.
Place into greased casserole.
Cover with chips and sprinkle with paprika. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Whip the cream and add softened cream cheese and salad dressing; blend.
Add pineapple, marshmallows and drained oranges. Mix well and let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.
Makes 20 servings.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies and mix.
Put half of mixture in 8 x 8-inch dish and chill.
Melt chocolate chips, powdered sugar, butter and water.
Pour over Rice Krispies mixture.
Put the remaining Rice Krispies mixture on top and chill.
Cut into squares before it gets firm.

title: barbecued steakers
directions: Shape meat into 8 to 10 small balls.
Saute in hot fat in skillet until lightly browned.

Add bread crumbs to meat first. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat balls. Continue cooking over medium heat, basting frequently with sauce for about 15 minutes. Serve over cooked spaghetti or rice.

title: herbed rice puffs
directions: Beat egg; stir in rice, poultry seasoning, salt and cheese. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Shape by rounded teaspoonfuls into fifteen 1-inch balls.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Heat oil (2 to 3 inches) in a 2-quart saucepan to 375°.
Fry rice balls until golden brown; drain.
Makes 15 Rice Puffs.

title: baked pork chops and rice
directions: Brown chops in fat.
Spread rice in 13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch deep baking dish.
Spread all but 1 tablespoon of the dry onion soup mixture over rice.
Drain mushrooms and reserve liquid.
Spread mushrooms and pimento over rice.
Add enough hot water to mushroom liquid to total 3 cups liquid.
Pour over rice.
Arrange chops on top and sprinkle with remaining 1 tablespoon onion soup mix. Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove foil and continue cooking for about 10 minutes or until the excess liquid evaporates.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate over very low heat.
Cool.
Sift flour with sugar, soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir butter in mixer bowl to soften.
Add flour mixture, 3/4 cup buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix to dampen flour.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed on mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add melted chocolate, eggs and remaining buttermilk.
Beat 1 minute longer.
Pour batter into three 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: quick rolls
directions: Melt yeast in water.
Mix all ingredients and make a workable dough.
Knead slightly and roll over to 1/2-inches thick on floured board.
Cut in desired shapes.
Brush with melted butter. Cook at 325° for about 20 minutes.
Refrigerate unused dough until ready to cook.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Cook ground beef and onion together and drain.
Mix spaghetti sauce mix, tomato sauce, mushrooms, cheese, sour cream and half of the melted margarine together and pour in a baking dish.
Unroll the crescent rolls over the mixture.
Pour remaining margarine over the rolls.
Bake until brown at about 400°.

title: pecan tasses
directions: Crust:
Blend and chill first 3 ingredients for 1 hour. Divide dough into small balls; put in small cupcake pan.
Shape into crust with knuckle and finger.

title: pumpkin spice muffins
directions: You will need 15 baking cups (optional).

title: norwegian buttons
directions: Mix all together and roll in small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet and flatten slightly with a fork.
Bake 10 minutes at 325°.
Roll in powdered sugar when cool.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat bananas very fine and add soda.
Cream butter and sugar in a separate bowl and add egg; beat well.
Mix bananas with butter mixture.
Beat well.
Add nuts.
Cook in a greased loaf pan in 325° oven for 45 minutes or until toothpick stuck in middles comes out dry.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Cut vegetables finely and saute in part of sausage drippings.
Bring 4 1/2 cups water to boil.
Add rice and packages of soup (dehydrated).
Cook until rice is done. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
The last 15 minutes, spread cream of mushroom soup over top and cover with slivered almonds.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: celery seed french dressing
directions: Mix the sugar, dry mustard, salt and onion and add 1/2 of the vinegar.
Add oil gradually.
Beat in remainder of vinegar.
Add celery seed last.
Mix all together in blender or food processor. The dressing becomes very thick and is excellent for cole slaw. Add to slaw
just before serving.
Keeps in refrigerator very well.

title: strawberry - cottage cheese fruit salad(easy)
directions: Thaw strawberries.
Mix jello package with thawed Cool Whip. Add cottage cheese and strawberries.
Mix or fold all together. Enjoy.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook frozen broccoli according to package directions in salted water until tender, drain.
Arrange stalks in greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs and butter; sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes or until heated.
Trim with pimento strips if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: molded banana cream salad
directions: Soften cream cheese; add mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt. Beat until creamy.
Add fruit and nuts; fold in whipped cream. Put into dish or mold and refrigerate.
May substitute Dream Whip for heavy cream.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients in given order.
Do not be afraid to heap cups of zucchini.
Pour mixture into 3 greased and floured medium size loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour in a preheated 350° oven.

title: zucchini soup
directions: In large saucepan, heat the oil over high heat.
Add onion, cook 5-7 minutes.
Add zucchini and cook until soft.
Stir in chicken broth, lemon juice and spices.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Process in blender until pureed. Serve either hot or cold.
May use more zucchini, or broth. Parsley gives the soup a light green color.
This soup freezes well.

title: champagne salad
directions: Blend cream cheese with sugar well.
Mix all ingredients together well.

title: quick green beans
directions: Wash green beans; trim ends and remove strings.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Place beans and onion in a 1-quart baking dish. Add broth and pepper. Cover and microwave on High 11 to 13 minutes or until beans are tender, stirring twice.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: zesty meatballs
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Cook meatballs in skillet until lightly browned; drain. Place meatballs in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: frozen strawberry cookie pie
directions: Mix ice cream with strawberries and cookies.
Pour into pie shell.
Place in freezer; cover tight.
Freeze firm.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before slicing.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and 2 eggs.
Make a paste of coloring and cocoa; add to shortening mixture.
Add milk alternately with flour and salt.
Add vanilla.
Fold in vinegar over soda; make paste.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, vanilla, flour, soda, pineapple and nuts. Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring the milk to a boil.
Add sugar and lemon peel next.
Add round grained rice.
Stir and return to the boil.
Leave oven on low heat to absorb the milk.
Cooking time:
approximately 40 minutes.
Add melted brown butter, sugar and cinnamon.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute onions and celery. Drain and add mushrooms. Cook broccoli as directed on package. In double boiler, mix cheese and mushroom soup; melt. Add all ingredients. If a casserole is made, add 2 tablespoons flour to cheese and soup. Bake at 350° until hot. If is made, bake before putting in chafing dish. You can add seasoning but not too much is needed.

title: spudnuts
directions: Scald milk.
Add shortening, sugar, potatoes and water.
Cool until lukewarm.
Add yeast.
Mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add salt and baking powder to flour and add to egg mixture.
Mix well. Knead 5 to 7 minutes.
Place in greased container.
Brush the top of dough with melted butter.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk (about 1 hour).
Punch down; roll out to about 1/4-inch thickness and cut out donuts.
Place on wax paper or greased cookie sheet.
Let rise until double in bulk, about 1/2 hour.
Fry in deep well at 375°.

title: chinese chicken slaw
directions: In a small bowl, whisk together dressing and soy sauce; set aside.
In a large bowl, toss remaining ingredients except chow mein noodles.
Pour dressing over salad and toss to coat well. Chill until ready to serve.
Top with chow mein noodles before serving.

title: strawberry bread(for use with stars and hearts mold)
directions: In medium bowl stir together drained strawberries, slightly beaten eggs and salad oil.
In large bowl combine other ingredients.
Mix contents of medium bowl into dry ingredients.

title: chicken portland
directions: Put chicken in casserole.
Add lots of paprika, salt and pepper.
Pour mushroom soup over it.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: tuna cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chopped pecans.
Put mixture in a bowl and store in refrigerator overnight.
Form mixture into a ball and cover with chopped pecans.
Serve on Ritz crackers.

title: "low carb cabbage soup"
directions: In a large microwavable container, combine the beef broth and tomatoes.
Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes.
While the broth and tomatoes are heating through, start browning and crumbling the beef in the oil.
Use a large soup kettle.
When the beef is about half done, add the onion and garlic.
Continue cooking until the beef is entirely browned.
Add the cumin and oregano.
Stir in the broth mix.
Add the coleslaw mix and bring the whole thing to a simmer.
Cook for another minute or so, then serve.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Peel and pare apples; cut in eighths and arrange in a 9-inch pie shell.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar with cinnamon; sprinkle over apples. Shake pan so mixture settles.
Sift 1/2 cup sugar (may be less if apples are sweet) with flour; pour over apples.
Shake.
Cut up butter and dot over pie.
Bake in hot oven, 400°, for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine, and pecans together.
Press into bottom of 13 x 9 inch. oblong casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix whipped topping according to package directions.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Blend into whipped topping.
Spread over pastry.
Spoon pie filling over top.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Use the other 2 egg whites for meringue.
Mix all ingredients and cook in double boiler until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell. Cover with meringue and brown.

title: w.w. new snickers(weight watchers)
directions: Mix ingredients and put into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Freeze and cut into 8 equal slices.
Counts as 1/4 milk, 1/2 fruit, 1/2 fat, 1/2 protein, 1/2 bread and 29 optional calories.

title: chocolate chip cookie pizza
directions: On a prepared pizza pan, press cookie dough from the center to within 1-inch of the edge of pan.
Pour the brownie batter over the cookie dough and bake at 350° on the upper rack of a preheated oven.
Test for firmness in center of pan at 25 minutes as ovens may vary.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook the macaroni.
Mix in a large bowl the macaroni, onion, pepper and tomato.
Add mayonnaise, cheese, salt and pepper, and you are ready to eat.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Combine hot water and jello.
Refrigerate until syrupy.
Add pineapple and blueberries.
Refrigerate until congealed.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: poppy seed egg bread
directions: In bread machine pan, place all ingredients in order suggested by the manufacturer.
Select basic bread setting and crust color. Makes 1 (2 pound) loaf.

title: diabetes forecast french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 375° and place the fries (do not overlap) on large nonstick baking sheet or one covered with foil.
Bake 1 hour. Turn fries over at 20 minute intervals for even browning.
One serving (8 fries) equals 1/2 bread exchange, 35 calories, 8 g carbohydrates and 1 g protein.

title: popeye patties(makes about 10 tiny patties)
directions: Put all ingredients, except oil, into a food processor and process until finely ground.
Heat the oil in medium skillet over medium-high heat.
Drop 1 tablespoon of the mixture into the skillet for each patty and saute until brown on one side, about 1 minute.
Flip patties and saute until brown on the other side, about 1 minute.
Serve when cool enough to eat.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Break up cornbread in large pot. Add croutons and bread. Saute vegetables with chicken broth. Add chopped boiled eggs to cornbread, croutons and bread. Add cooked rice. Add some turkey stock. Add sauteed vegetables and seasonings. Bake.

title: seafood stuffed mushrooms
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Marinate mushrooms overnight. Remove mushrooms.
Mix cream cheese, crab or shrimp, spinach and onions together.
Stuff mushroom.
Moisten with reserved marinade. Serve immediately.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef with 2 tablespoons taco seasoning and 2 tablespoons taco sauce.
Wash and tear lettuce; put in large container.
Add onion, cheese, tomatoes and ground beef.
Just before serving, add chips and dressing.
Mix well.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Pick over popped popcorn.
Melt butter.
Add molasses and sugar.
Boil to 270°.
Pour over popcorn.
Put butter on your hands and mold into balls.
When cooled, put in a sandwich baggie and tie with red or green yarn.
Nice gift at Christmastime.

title: zucchini pepperoni casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with no-stick spray.
Combine zucchini, onion, cheeses, pepperoni and spices in a large bowl.
In another bowl combine eggs, oil and Bisquick. Add to zucchini mixture and stir well until all ingredients are coated.
Spread in prepared baking dish.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Serve with marinara sauce or spaghetti sauce on the side.

title: chocolate coke cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, marshmallows and soda in a large bowl. Set aside.
Bring margarine, shortening, cocoa and Coke to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour over the flour mixture.
Add buttermilk and eggs.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken cordon bleu(weight watchers)
directions: In small skillet, heat half of the margarine over medium heat until bubbly and hot.
Add chicken; cook briefly on each side (just until no longer pink).
Transfer chicken to plate; top with ham, then cheese.
Starting from narrow end, roll chicken to enclose filling.
Secure with toothpick; transfer to shallow individual baking dish.
Set aside.

title: light as a cloud dessert
directions: Heat the oven to 400°.
Beat 6 egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff.
Gradually beat in 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Beat until very stiff and glossy.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put in preheated oven.
Shut the door, then turn off the oven.
Leave in oven at least 8 hours or overnight and do not open the oven door.

title: winter fruit salad
directions: Soak apricots in water overnight.
Drain water into measuring cup and add enough orange juice to equal 3/4 cup liquid.
Boil raisins, juice and apricots 5 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Combine all ingredients.
Toss together.
Chill before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: curried mayonnaise
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients until bouillon dissolves.
Mix thoroughly with sour cream and mayonnaise.
Let sit several hours; mix again.
Serve with fresh veggies or with shrimp and mandarin orange slices on toothpicks.

title: kid's tortilla crisps
directions: Cut tortillas, using any shaped cookie cutter. Paint melted butter on the tortilla shapes with a pastry brush. (Just spray on the cooking spray.) Combine sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl and sprinkle over the butter-covered tortilla shapes. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Mix with mixer (not blender) until smooth.

title: mayonnaise or boiled salad dressing
directions: Slowly add vinegar and water to other ingredients which have been mixed.
Cook over low heat, stirring until it thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute.

title: crock-pot chicken in wine
directions: Put carrots, celery and onion in bottom of crock-pot.
Add chicken, top with salt, pepper and wine.
Sprinkle basil over chicken.
Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or cook on high 3 1/2 to 5 hours (use 1 cup of wine for cooking on high).
Yields 4 servings.

title: pork chops
directions: Mix all ingredients except pork chops; pour into baking dish. Place pork chops on top and pull some of rice on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fancy banana pudding
directions: Mix milk with pudding until smooth.
Use mixer.
Add sour cream, Eagle Brand milk and vanilla and mix well.
Add Cool Whip. Mix well.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding.
Top with Cool Whip and crushed wafers.

title: hot tuna salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
Toss together remaining ingredients and place in 2-quart dish.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Debone.
Set aside.
Over medium heat, in large saucepan, mix both cans of soup, chopped onion, Cheez Whiz, half of the Longhorn cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes (drained) until all ingredients are blended.
Soak tortillas in chicken broth.
Layer bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with tortillas.
Next, put one layer of chunk chicken pieces.
Top with layer of sauce.
Repeat each layer.
Top with remainder of cheese, grated.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients in order listed and mix well.
Pack firmly into loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Slice and serve hot or cold.

title: strawberry glaze pie
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine cornstarch and sugar.
Add water; stir until smooth.
Add lemon juice.
Cool until thick and clear. Add red food coloring, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add strawberries to mixture and put into pie crust.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Serve.

title: sourdough or yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; combine all ingredients.
Place dough in covered bowl in refrigerator.
No need to let rise before baking.
Bake as you would do biscuits.
Dough keeps well in refrigerator for about a week.

title: raisin tart
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Roll the pastry dough very thin.
Cut into 2 1/2-inch rounds, 48 in all.
Mix the raisins, citron, honey, butter, orange peel and brown sugar in a bowl.
Place a rounded teaspoonful in the center of half the pastry rounds. Moisten the edges with milk and place an unfilled round on top of each filled one.
Seal the edges with the tines of a fork and prick the top.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes, or until golden.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and cook in boiling salted water until tender. Drain well.
In a large bowl, mix squash and remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased 2-quart casserole at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 8.
